KeySegment.name: KeySegment
KeySegment.description: The total length of the key is 1024 characters, it is divided into 8 parts and stored in 8 separated mib variables as below: Key1: part 1 of the key (1-128) Key2: part 2 of the key (129-256) Key3: part 3 of the key (257-384) Key4: part 4 of the key (385-512) Key5: part 5 of the key (513-640) Key6: part 6 of the key (641-768) Key7: part 7 of the key (769-896) Key8: part 8 of the key (897-1024) Please note that if the key string is less then 1024 characters, the remaining part of the string will be filled by a zero-length string. For example, if the length of the key is 129, we will get a string of length 128 in Key1, and a string of length 1 in Key2, moreover, Key3 to Key8 will all be zero-length strings.

ValidStatus.name: ValidStatus
ValidStatus.description: A simple status value for the object to create and destroy a table entry. This is a simplified variant of RowStatus as it supports only two values. Setting it to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting it to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

StaPathCostMode.name: StaPathCostMode
StaPathCostMode.description: The path cost mode of a spanning tree algorithm, short(1) indicates that we retrieve/configure the spanning tree path cost as a 16 bit value and long(2) indicates that we retrieve/configure the spanning tree path cost as a 32 bit value.

switchNumber.name: switchNumber
switchNumber.description: The total number of switches present on this system.

switchInfoTable.name: switchInfoTable
switchInfoTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the switch units in this system.

switchInfoEntry.name: switchInfoEntry
switchInfoEntry.description: Table providing descriptions and status information for switch units.

swUnitIndex.name: swUnitIndex
swUnitIndex.description: This object identifies the switch within the system for which this entry contains information. This value can never be greater than switchNumber.

swHardwareVer.name: swHardwareVer
swHardwareVer.description: Hardware version of the main board.

swMicrocodeVer.name: swMicrocodeVer
swMicrocodeVer.description: Microcode version of the main board.

swLoaderVer.name: swLoaderVer
swLoaderVer.description: Loader version of the main board.

swBootRomVer.name: swBootRomVer
swBootRomVer.description: Boot ROM code version of the main board.

swOpCodeVer.name: swOpCodeVer
swOpCodeVer.description: Operation code version of the main board.

swPortNumber.name: swPortNumber
swPortNumber.description: The number of ports on this switch.

swPowerStatus.name: swPowerStatus
swPowerStatus.description: Indicates the switch using internalPower(1), redundantPower(2) or both(3)

swRoleInSystem.name: swRoleInSystem
swRoleInSystem.description: Indicates the switch is master(1), backupMaster(2) or slave(3) in this system.

swServiceTag.name: swServiceTag
swServiceTag.description: Service tag serial-number of the switch.

swEpldVer.name: swEpldVer
swEpldVer.description: The EPLD version of the switch.

switchOperState.name: switchOperState
switchOperState.description: Global operation state of the switch.

swProdName.name: swProdName
swProdName.description: The product name of this switch.

swProdManufacturer.name: swProdManufacturer
swProdManufacturer.description: The product manufacturer of this switch.

swProdDescription.name: swProdDescription
swProdDescription.description: The product description of this switch.

swProdVersion.name: swProdVersion
swProdVersion.description: The runtime code version of this switch.

swProdUrl.name: swProdUrl
swProdUrl.description: The URL of this switch, which we can connect through a web browser.

swIdentifier.name: swIdentifier
swIdentifier.description: A unique identifier of which switch in the chassis is currently being looked at.

swChassisServiceTag.name: swChassisServiceTag
swChassisServiceTag.description: The service tag of the chassis this switch resides in.

switchIndivPowerTable.name: switchIndivPowerTable
switchIndivPowerTable.description: Table about the status of individual powers.

switchIndivPowerEntry.name: switchIndivPowerEntry
switchIndivPowerEntry.description: Table about the status of individual power.

swIndivPowerIndex.name: swIndivPowerIndex
swIndivPowerIndex.description: 1 means internal power, 2 means external power.

swIndivPowerStatus.name: swIndivPowerStatus
swIndivPowerStatus.description: notPresent(1) means not present, green(2) means up, red(3) means down.

switchJumboFrameStatus.name: switchJumboFrameStatus
switchJumboFrameStatus.description: enable(1) means the Jumbo Frame has enabled, disabled(2) means the Jumbo Frame has disabled.

amtrMacAddrAgingStatus.name: amtrMacAddrAgingStatus
amtrMacAddrAgingStatus.description: If this is enabled(1), the MAC address table will age out according to its timer. If this is disabled(2), the MAC address table will not age out.

switchRenumberUnitID.name: switchRenumberUnitID
switchRenumberUnitID.description: The value renumber will automatically assign an ID to units in the stack; all UNIT IDs will be contiguous. The system configurations are not changed but the system will restart after renumbering is completed.

switchPDPowerSourceCheck.name: switchPDPowerSourceCheck
switchPDPowerSourceCheck.description: A value of true(1) will enable the power souce check. A value of false(2) will disable the power souce check.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information describing the configuration of each switch port. This table also contains information about each trunk.

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: An entry in the table, describing the configuration of one switch port or trunk.

portIndex.name: portIndex
portIndex.description: The port and the trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

portName.name: portName
portName.description: The name of the port or trunk. This is the same as ifAlias in the IF-MIB (RFC2863 or later).

portType.name: portType
portType.description: Indicates the port type of the configuration of the switch.

portSpeedDpxCfg.name: portSpeedDpxCfg
portSpeedDpxCfg.description: Configures the speed and duplex mode for a port or trunk, according to: halfDuplex10(2) - 10Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex10(3) - 10Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex100(4) - 100Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex100(5) - 100Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex1000(6) - 1000Mbps and half duplex mode fullDuplex1000(7) - 1000Mbps and full duplex mode halfDuplex10g(8) - 10g and half duplex mode fullDuplex10g(9) - 10g and full duplex mode hundredBaseTX port can be set as: halfDuplex10(2) fullDuplex10(3) halfDuplex100(4) fullDuplex100(5) hundredBaseFX port can be set as: fullDuplex100(5) thousandBaseSX port can be set as: fullDuplex1000(7) thousandBaseLX port can be set as: fullDuplex1000(7) thousandBaseT port can be set as: halfDuplex10(2) fullDuplex10(3) halfDuplex100(4) fullDuplex100(5) thousandBaseGBIC port can be set as: fullDuplex1000(7) thousandBaseSfp port can be set as: fullDuplex1000(7) hundredBaseFxScSingleMode port can be set as: fullDuplex100(5) hundredBaseFxScMultiMode port can be set as: fullDuplex100(5) thousandBaseCX port can be set as: fullDuplex1000(7) tenG port can be set as: halfDuplex10g(8) fullDuplex10g(9) The actual operating speed and duplex of the port is given by portSpeedDpxStatus.

portFlowCtrlCfg.name: portFlowCtrlCfg
portFlowCtrlCfg.description: (1) Flow control mechanism is enabled with tx and rx pause mechansim. If the port type is hundredBaseTX or thousandBaseSX: When the port is operating in halfDuplex mode, the port uses backPressure flow control mechanism. When the port is operating in fullDuplex mode, the port uses IEEE 802.3x flow control mechanism. If the port type is hundredBaseFX: When the port is operating in halfDuplex mode, the port uses backPressure flow control mechanism. When the port is operating in fullDuplex mode, Flow control mechanism will not function. (2) Flow control mechanism is disabled. (5) Flow control mechanism is enabled with tx pause mechanism only. (6) Flow control mechansim is enabled with rx pause mechansim only. Fast ethernet ports can be set as: enabled(1), disabled(2). Gigabit ethernet ports can be set as: enabled(1), disabled(2), tx(5), rx(6). The actual flow control mechanism is used given by portFlowCtrlStatus.

portSpeedDpxStatus.name: portSpeedDpxStatus
portSpeedDpxStatus.description: The operating speed and duplex mode of the switched port or trunk. If the entry represents a trunk, the speed is that of its individual members unless the member ports have been inconsistently configured in which case the value is error(1).

portFlowCtrlStatus.name: portFlowCtrlStatus
portFlowCtrlStatus.description: (2) BackPressure flow control mechanism is used. (3) IEEE 802.3 flow control mechanism is used. (4) Flow control mechanism is disabled. If the entry represents a trunk and the member ports have been inconsistently configured then this value is error(1).

portTrunkIndex.name: portTrunkIndex
portTrunkIndex.description: The trunk to which this port belongs. A value of 0 means that this port does not belong to any trunk. A value greater than zero means that this port belongs to a trunk in the trunkIndex, defined by the corresponding trunkPorts.

portComboForcedMode.name: portComboForcedMode
portComboForcedMode.description: This determines the running mode of a combo port. For a non-combo port, this variable has a value of none(1), and setting this variable to none(1) has no effect. For a combo port, this has its own valid values not equal to none(1), and setting this variable to none(1) is not allowed. copperForced(2) is set if user want to force this combo port running in copper mode. copperPreferredAuto(3) is obsoleted, and user shall not set this state. sfpForced(4) is set if user want to force this combo port running in fiber mode. sfpPreferredAuto(5) is set if user want to change copper or fiber mode automatically by SFP transceiver present state. If SFP transceiver is present, this combo port will run in fiber mode, and if SFP transceiver is not present, this combo port will run in copper mode.

portMasterSlaveModeCfg.name: portMasterSlaveModeCfg
portMasterSlaveModeCfg.description: Configures the PHY mode when auto negotiation is disabled and speed-duplex is 1000full for giga copper port.

portMacAddrLearningStatus.name: portMacAddrLearningStatus
portMacAddrLearningStatus.description: Set this variable to enabled(1) to start to learn MAC addresses. Set this variable to disabled(2) to stop to learn MAC addresses.

portMacAddrLearningCount.name: portMacAddrLearningCount
portMacAddrLearningCount.description: The current number of learned MAC addresses.

portUpTime.name: portUpTime
portUpTime.description: The port up time (in hundredths of a second).

portShutdownReason.name: portShutdownReason
portShutdownReason.description: The reason of port shutdown. The value is 0 if no shutdown action is applied to this port.

cableDiagCtlAction.name: cableDiagCtlAction
cableDiagCtlAction.description: To execute cable diagnostics on a port, assign cableDiagCtlAction to the value of ifIndex defined by the ifIndex in the IF-MIB. When read, this object always returns 0.

cableDiagResultIfIndex.name: cableDiagResultIfIndex
cableDiagResultIfIndex.description: This is defined as the ifIndex.

cableDiagResultStatusPairA.name: cableDiagResultStatusPairA
cableDiagResultStatusPairA.description: The result of cable diagnostics. Value notTestedYet(1) means the pair is not tested yet. Value ok(2) means the pair works well. Value open(3) means there is a lack of continuity between pins at each end of the pair. Value short(4) means conductors are short-circuited together on the pair. Value impedanceMismatch(8) means different quality cables connected together. Value failed(9) means test failed. Value notSupported(10) means cable diagnostics is not supported. Value noCable(11) means there is no connected cable. Value underTesting(12) means cable diag is still running. Value unknown(7) means pair has an error matching none of the above.

cableDiagResultStatusPairB.name: cableDiagResultStatusPairB
cableDiagResultStatusPairB.description: The result of cable diagnostics. Value notTestedYet(1) means the pair is not tested yet. Value ok(2) means the pair works well. Value open(3) means there is a lack of continuity between pins at each end of the pair. Value short(4) means conductors are short-circuited together on the pair. Value impedanceMismatch(8) means different quality cables connected together. Value failed(9) means test failed. Value notSupported(10) means cable diagnostics is not supported. Value noCable(11) means there is no connected cable. Value underTesting(12) means cable diag is still running. Value unknown(7) means pair has an error matching none of the above.

cableDiagResultStatusPairC.name: cableDiagResultStatusPairC
cableDiagResultStatusPairC.description: The result of cable diagnostics. Value notTestedYet(1) means the pair is not tested yet. Value ok(2) means the pair works well. Value open(3) means there is a lack of continuity between pins at each end of the pair. Value short(4) means conductors are short-circuited together on the pair. Value impedanceMismatch(8) means different quality cables connected together. Value failed(9) means test failed. Value notSupported(10) means cable diagnostics is not supported. Value noCable(11) means there is no connected cable. Value underTesting(12) means cable diag is still running. Value unknown(7) means pair has an error matching none of the above.

cableDiagResultStatusPairD.name: cableDiagResultStatusPairD
cableDiagResultStatusPairD.description: The result of cable diagnostics. Value notTestedYet(1) means the pair is not tested yet. Value ok(2) means the pair works well. Value open(3) means there is a lack of continuity between pins at each end of the pair. Value short(4) means conductors are short-circuited together on the pair. Value impedanceMismatch(8) means different quality cables connected together. Value failed(9) means test failed. Value notSupported(10) means cable diagnostics is not supported. Value noCable(11) means there is no connected cable. Value underTesting(12) means cable diag is still running. Value unknown(7) means pair has an error matching none of the above.

cableDiagResultDistancePairA.name: cableDiagResultDistancePairA
cableDiagResultDistancePairA.description: Displays the fault distance of pair A of the cable in meters. 0 will be displayed if cableDiagResultStatusPairA equals to Value underTesting(12).

cableDiagResultDistancePairB.name: cableDiagResultDistancePairB
cableDiagResultDistancePairB.description: Displays the fault distance of pair B of the cable in meters. 0 will be displayed if cableDiagResultStatusPairB equals to Value underTesting(12).

cableDiagResultDistancePairC.name: cableDiagResultDistancePairC
cableDiagResultDistancePairC.description: Displays the fault distance of pair C of the cable in meters. 0 will be displayed if cableDiagResultStatusPairC equals to Value underTesting(12).

cableDiagResultDistancePairD.name: cableDiagResultDistancePairD
cableDiagResultDistancePairD.description: Displays the fault distance of pair D of the cable in meters. 0 will be displayed if cableDiagResultStatusPairD equals to Value underTesting(12).

cableDiagResultTime.name: cableDiagResultTime
cableDiagResultTime.description: Displays the last time of cable diagnostics. For example, 'Jan 1 02:03:04 2002'.

loopInternalCtlAction.name: loopInternalCtlAction
loopInternalCtlAction.description: To execute internal loopback test on a port, assign loopInternalCtlAction to the value of ifIndex defined by the ifIndex in the IF-MIB. When read, this object always returns 0.

loopInternalResultTable.name: loopInternalResultTable
loopInternalResultTable.description: Table for internal loopback test result.

loopInternalResultEntry.name: loopInternalResultEntry
loopInternalResultEntry.description: Entry for internal loopback test result.

loopInternalResultIfIndex.name: loopInternalResultIfIndex
loopInternalResultIfIndex.description: This is defined as the ifIndex.

loopInternalResultTime.name: loopInternalResultTime
loopInternalResultTime.description: Displays the last time of internal loopback. For example, 'Jan 1 02:03:04 2002'.

portUtilTable.name: portUtilTable
portUtilTable.description: Dispalys port utilization during recent 300 seconds.

portUtilEntry.name: portUtilEntry
portUtilEntry.description: Dispalys port utilization during recent 300 seconds.

portUtilIfIndex.name: portUtilIfIndex
portUtilIfIndex.description: The port and trunk interface of the portUtilTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

portInOctetRate.name: portInOctetRate
portInOctetRate.description: The input octet rate (kbits/sec) of the port.

portInPacketRate.name: portInPacketRate
portInPacketRate.description: The input packet rate (pkts/sec) of the port.

portInUtil.name: portInUtil
portInUtil.description: The input utilization of the port, in one per hundred.

portOutOctetRate.name: portOutOctetRate
portOutOctetRate.description: The output octet rate (kbits/sec) of the port.

portOutPacketRate.name: portOutPacketRate
portOutPacketRate.description: The output packet rate (pkts/sec) of the port.

portOutUtil.name: portOutUtil
portOutUtil.description: The output utilization of the port, in one per hundred.

portVlanTrunkingIfIndex.name: portVlanTrunkingIfIndex
portVlanTrunkingIfIndex.description: The port and trunk interface of the portVlanTrunkingTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

portHistControlTable.name: portHistControlTable
portHistControlTable.description: A list of history control entries.

portHistControlEntry.name: portHistControlEntry
portHistControlEntry.description: A list of parameters that set up a periodic sampling of statistics.

portHistControlIndex.name: portHistControlIndex
portHistControlIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the portHistControl table.

portHistControlName.name: portHistControlName
portHistControlName.description: A textual name of the entity. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

portHistControlDataSource.name: portHistControlDataSource
portHistControlDataSource.description: This object identifies the source of the data for which historical data was collected and placed in a media-specific table on behalf of this portHistControlEntry. This source can be any interface on this device.

portHistControlInterval.name: portHistControlInterval
portHistControlInterval.description: The interval in seconds over which the data is sampled for each bucket in the part of the media-specific table associated with this portHistControlEntry. This interval can be set to any number of seconds between 1 and 86400 (1 day).

portHistControlBucketsRequested.name: portHistControlBucketsRequested
portHistControlBucketsRequested.description: The requested number of discrete time intervals over which data is to be saved in the part of the media-specific table associated with this portHistControlEntry.

portHistControlBucketsGranted.name: portHistControlBucketsGranted
portHistControlBucketsGranted.description: The number of discrete sampling intervals over which data shall be saved in the part of the media-specific table associated with this portHistControlEntry.

portHistControlStatus.name: portHistControlStatus
portHistControlStatus.description: The status of this portHistControl entry.

portHistCurrentTable.name: portHistCurrentTable
portHistCurrentTable.description: A list of Ethernet history entries.

portHistCurrentEntry.name: portHistCurrentEntry
portHistCurrentEntry.description: An historical sample of Ethernet statistics on a particular Ethernet interface. This sample is associated with the portHistControlEntry which set up the parameters for a regular collection of these samples.

portHistCurrentIndex.name: portHistCurrentIndex
portHistCurrentIndex.description: The history of which this entry is a part. The history identified by a particular value of this index is the same history as identified by the same value of portHistControlIndex.

portHistCurrentSampleIndex.name: portHistCurrentSampleIndex
portHistCurrentSampleIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the particular sample this entry represents among all samples associated with the same portHistControlEntry. This index starts at 1 and increases by one as each new sample is taken.

portHistCurrentIntervalStart.name: portHistCurrentIntervalStart
portHistCurrentIntervalStart.description: The value of sysUpTime at the start of the interval over which this sample was measured.

portHistCurrentInOctets.name: portHistCurrentInOctets
portHistCurrentInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

portHistCurrentInUcastPkts.name: portHistCurrentInUcastPkts
portHistCurrentInUcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer.

portHistCurrentInMulticastPkts.name: portHistCurrentInMulticastPkts
portHistCurrentInMulticastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

portHistCurrentInBroadcastPkts.name: portHistCurrentInBroadcastPkts
portHistCurrentInBroadcastPkts.description: The number of packets, delivered by this sub-layer to a higher (sub-)layer, which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer.

portHistCurrentInDiscards.name: portHistCurrentInDiscards
portHistCurrentInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

portHistCurrentInErrors.name: portHistCurrentInErrors
portHistCurrentInErrors.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of inbound transmission units that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

portHistCurrentInUnknownProtos.name: portHistCurrentInUnknownProtos
portHistCurrentInUnknownProtos.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces that support protocol multiplexing the number of transmission units received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. For any interface that does not support protocol multiplexing, this counter will always be 0.

portHistCurrentOutOctets.name: portHistCurrentOutOctets
portHistCurrentOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

portHistCurrentOutUcastPkts.name: portHistCurrentOutUcastPkts
portHistCurrentOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were not addressed to a multicast or broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

portHistCurrentOutMulticastPkts.name: portHistCurrentOutMulticastPkts
portHistCurrentOutMulticastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a multicast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

portHistCurrentOutBroadcastPkts.name: portHistCurrentOutBroadcastPkts
portHistCurrentOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

portHistCurrentOutDiscards.name: portHistCurrentOutDiscards
portHistCurrentOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

portHistCurrentOutErrors.name: portHistCurrentOutErrors
portHistCurrentOutErrors.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of outbound transmission units that could not be transmitted because of errors.

portHistCurrentInUtilization.name: portHistCurrentInUtilization
portHistCurrentInUtilization.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this sampling interval, in hundredths of a percent.

portHistCurrentOutUtilization.name: portHistCurrentOutUtilization
portHistCurrentOutUtilization.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this sampling interval, in hundredths of a percent.

portHistPreviousTable.name: portHistPreviousTable
portHistPreviousTable.description: A list of Ethernet history entries.

portHistPreviousEntry.name: portHistPreviousEntry
portHistPreviousEntry.description: An historical sample of Ethernet statistics on a particular Ethernet interface. This sample is associated with the portHistControlEntry which set up the parameters for a regular collection of these samples.

portHistPreviousIndex.name: portHistPreviousIndex
portHistPreviousIndex.description: The history of which this entry is a part. The history identified by a particular value of this index is the same history as identified by the same value of portHistControlIndex.

portHistPreviousSampleIndex.name: portHistPreviousSampleIndex
portHistPreviousSampleIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the particular sample this entry represents among all samples associated with the same portHistControlEntry. This index starts at 1 and increases by one as each new sample is taken.

portHistPreviousIntervalStart.name: portHistPreviousIntervalStart
portHistPreviousIntervalStart.description: The value of sysUpTime at the start of the interval over which this sample was measured.

portHistPreviousInOctets.name: portHistPreviousInOctets
portHistPreviousInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

portHistPreviousInUcastPkts.name: portHistPreviousInUcastPkts

portHistPreviousOutBroadcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted, and which were addressed to a broadcast address at this sub-layer, including those that were discarded or not sent.

portHistPreviousOutErrors.name: portHistPreviousOutErrors
portHistPreviousOutErrors.description: For packet-oriented interfaces, the number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors. For character-oriented or fixed-length interfaces, the number of outbound transmission units that could not be transmitted because of errors.

portHistPreviousInUtilization.name: portHistPreviousInUtilization
portHistPreviousInUtilization.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this sampling interval, in hundredths of a percent.

portHistPreviousOutUtilization.name: portHistPreviousOutUtilization
portHistPreviousOutUtilization.description: The best estimate of the mean physical layer network utilization on this interface during this sampling interval, in hundredths of a percent.

portMediaInfoTable.name: portMediaInfoTable
portMediaInfoTable.description: This table lists the information of the media device (SFP/XFP/Copper) installed in the physical port. Only the ifIndices of Ethernet ports those are associated with the operational cards will be included in this table.

portMediaInfoEntry.name: portMediaInfoEntry
portMediaInfoEntry.description: An entry in the Interface Media Information table. The ifIndices of ethernet interfaces will be used to index this table.

portMediaInfoVendorName.name: portMediaInfoVendorName
portMediaInfoVendorName.description: The media vendor name, full name of the corporation.

portMediaInfoRevision.name: portMediaInfoRevision
portMediaInfoRevision.description: The media vendor product version number.

portMediaInfoSerialNumber.name: portMediaInfoSerialNumber
portMediaInfoSerialNumber.description: The vendor serial number of the media device.

portMediaInfoDateCode.name: portMediaInfoDateCode
portMediaInfoDateCode.description: The date code of the media device.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoTable.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoTable
portOpticalMonitoringInfoTable.description: This table lists the instrumented parameters of all optical interfaces.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoEntry.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoEntry
portOpticalMonitoringInfoEntry.description: Only the ifIndices of optical interfaces whose parameters need to be monitored will be used to index this table.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoTemperature.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoTemperature
portOpticalMonitoringInfoTemperature.description: This object holds the value of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the interface. This object indicates the health of the transmitter. The format is xxx.yyyy C(elcius). If the device supports ALARM WARNING TRAP, then followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoVcc.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoVcc
portOpticalMonitoringInfoVcc.description: This object holds the value of the Vcc. It is measured in V. If the device supports ALARM WARNING TRAP, then followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoTxBiasCurrent.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoTxBiasCurrent
portOpticalMonitoringInfoTxBiasCurrent.description: Tx Bias Current. It is measured in mA. If the device supports ALARM WARNING TRAP, then followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoTxPower.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoTxPower
portOpticalMonitoringInfoTxPower.description: This object holds the value of the transmitter optical signal power for the interface, measured in dBm. If the device supports ALARM WARNING TRAP, then followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning.

portOpticalMonitoringInfoRxPower.name: portOpticalMonitoringInfoRxPower
portOpticalMonitoringInfoRxPower.description: This object holds the value of the receiver optical signal power for the interface, measured in dBm. If the device support ALARM WARNING TRAP, then followed by whether the measured value is normal, high/low alarm or high/low warning.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTable.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTable
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTable.description: This table lists the threshold of transceivers.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoEntry.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoEntry
portTransceiverThresholdInfoEntry.description: Identify the index of the transceiver

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureL.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureLowAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureL.description: This object holds the low alarm threshold of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureL.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureLowWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureL.description: This object holds the low warning threshold of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureH.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureHighWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureH.description: This object holds the high warning threshold of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureH.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureHighAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTemperatureH.description: This object holds the high alarm threshold of the transmitter laser diode temperature for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccLowAlarm.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccLowAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccLowAlarm.description: This object holds the low alarm threshold of the Vcc.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccLowWarn.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccLowWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccLowWarn.description: This object holds the low warning threshold of the Vcc.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccHighWarn.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccHighWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccHighWarn.description: This object holds the high warning threshold of the Vcc.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccHighAlarm.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccHighAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoVccHighAlarm.description: This object holds the high alarm threshold of the Vcc.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurrentLowAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.description: low alarm threshold of Tx Bias Current.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurrentLowWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.description: low warning threshold of Tx Bias Current.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurrentHighWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.description: high warning threshold of Tx Bias Current.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurrentHighAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxBiasCurren.description: high alarm threshold of Tx Bias Current.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerLowAl.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerLowAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerLowAl.description: This object holds the low alarm threshold of the transmitter optical signal power for theinterface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerLowWa.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerLowWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerLowWa.description: This object holds the low warning threshold of the transmitter optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerHighW.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerHighWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerHighW.description: This object holds the high warning threshold of the transmitter optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerHighA.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerHighAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoTxPowerHighA.description: This object holds the high alarm threshold of the transmitter optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerLowAl.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerLowAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerLowAl.description: This object holds the low alarm threshold of the receiver optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerLowWa.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerLowWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerLowWa.description: This object holds the low warning threshold of the receiver optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerHighW.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerHighWarn
portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerHighW.description: This object holds the high warning threshold of the receiver optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerHighA.name: portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerHighAlarm
portTransceiverThresholdInfoRxPowerHighA.description: This object holds the high alarm threshold of the receiver optical signal power for the interface.

portTransceiverThresholdAutoMode.name: portTransceiverThresholdAutoMode
portTransceiverThresholdAutoMode.description: Indicate the transceiver threshold is retrieved from EEPROM or configured by user.

portPDTable.name: portPDTable
portPDTable.description: This table lists the info of all PD (powered device) interfaces.

portPDIfIndex.name: portPDIfIndex
portPDIfIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

portPDStatus.name: portPDStatus
portPDStatus.description: Indicates the status of the powered device port. None for non PD device, up for powered device port consuming power from PSE (power sourcing equipment) port.

trunkMaxId.name: trunkMaxId
trunkMaxId.description: The maximum number for a trunk identifier.

trunkTable.name: trunkTable
trunkTable.description: Table describing the configuration and status of each trunk.

trunkEntry.name: trunkEntry
trunkEntry.description: An entry describing the configuration and status of a particular trunk.

trunkIndex.name: trunkIndex
trunkIndex.description: Identifies the trunk within the switch that is described by the table entry.

trunkPorts.name: trunkPorts
trunkPorts.description: The complete set of ports currently associated with this trunk.

trunkCreation.name: trunkCreation
trunkCreation.description: A value of static(1) means a statically configured trunk. A value of lacp(2) means an LACP-configured trunk.

trunkStatus.name: trunkStatus
trunkStatus.description: Writing this to valid(1) creates an entry. Writing this to invalid(2) destroys an entry. A trunk created by LACP cannot be manually destroyed or (re)configured.

trunkBalanceMode.name: trunkBalanceMode
trunkBalanceMode.description: This defines the load balancing mode of trunks in the system. It may be based on source and/or destination MAC address or IP address. macSrc(1) means source MAC address. macDst(2) means destination MAC address. macSrcDst(3) means source and destination MAC address. ipSrc(4) means source IP address. ipDst(5) means destination IP address. ipSrcDst(6) means source and destination IP address.

lacpPortEntry.name: lacpPortEntry
lacpPortEntry.description: Entry for LACP port configuration. While an entry may exist for a particular port, the port may not support LACP and an attempt to enable LACP may result in failure.

lacpPortIndex.name: lacpPortIndex
lacpPortIndex.description: The port interface of the lacpPortTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

staSystemStatus.name: staSystemStatus
staSystemStatus.description: Global spanning tree status. (1) Spanning tree protocol is enabled. (2) Spanning tree protocol is disabled.

staPortTable.name: staPortTable
staPortTable.description: The table manages port settings for Spanning Tree Protocol 802.1d, 802.1w or 802.1s depending on the value specified by staProtocolType.

staPortProtocolMigration.name: staPortProtocolMigration
staPortProtocolMigration.description: When operating in RSTP (version 2) mode, writing true(1) to this object forces this port to transmit RSTP BPDUs. Any other operation on this object has no effect and it always returns false(2) when read.

staPortOperEdgePort.name: staPortOperEdgePort
staPortOperEdgePort.description: The operational value of the edge port parameter. The object is initialized to the value of staPortAdminEdgePort and is set false when a BPDU is received.

staPortAdminPointToPoint.name: staPortAdminPointToPoint
staPortAdminPointToPoint.description: The administrative point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. A value of forceTrue(0) indicates that this port should always be treated as if it is connected to a point-to-point link. A value of forceFalse(1) indicates that this port should be treated as having a shared media connection. A value of auto(2) indicates that this port is considered to have a point-to-point link if it is an Aggregator and all of its members are aggregatable, or if the MAC entity is configured for full duplex operation, either through auto-negotiation or by management means.

staPortOperPointToPoint.name: staPortOperPointToPoint
staPortOperPointToPoint.description: The operational point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. This indicates whether a port is considered to have a point-to-point connection or not. The value is determined by management or by auto-detection, as described in the staPortAdminPointToPoint object.

staPortSystemStatus.name: staPortSystemStatus
staPortSystemStatus.description: Per-port spanning tree status. (1) Spanning tree protocol is enabled. (2) Spanning tree protocol is disabled.

staPortLongAdminPathCost.name: staPortLongAdminPathCost
staPortLongAdminPathCost.description: The admin value of the RSTP path cost or MST external pathcost. The contribution of this port to the path cost (in 32 bits value) of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. This object is used to configure the spanning tree port path cost in the 32-bit value range when the staPathCostMethod is long(2). If the staPathCostMethod is short(1), this mib object is not instantiated. Setting this to 0 means that the path cost is automatically determined. In this case, read staPortLongOperPathCost to get the oper value.

staPortLongOperPathCost.name: staPortLongOperPathCost
staPortLongOperPathCost.description: The oper value of the RSTP path cost or MST external pathcost. The contribution of this port to the path cost (in 32 bits value) of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. This object is used to configure the spanning tree port path cost in the 32-bit value range when the staPathCostMethod is long(2). If the staPathCostMethod is short(1), this mib object is not instantiated.

staPortBpduFlooding.name: staPortBpduFlooding
staPortBpduFlooding.description: This parameter is used to configure the capability of BPDUs flooding.

staPortBpduGuard.name: staPortBpduGuard
staPortBpduGuard.description: A value of enabled(1) indicates that BPDU port guard feature is enabled for each port. A value of disabled(2) indicates that the feature is disabled.

staPortAdminEdgePortWithAuto.name: staPortAdminEdgePortWithAuto
staPortAdminEdgePortWithAuto.description: The administrative value of the edge port parameter. A value of enable(1) indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port, a value of disable(2) indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port and a value of auot (3) indicates this port in RSPT or MSTP mode should be assumed as an edge-port after migration or max age expire without receiving any BPDU and sending BPDU with proposal flag on.

staPortBpduFilter.name: staPortBpduFilter
staPortBpduFilter.description: The administrative value of the BPDU filter parameter. A value of enabled(1) indicates that this port will avoid transmitting BPDUs on edge-port and the value of disabled(2) indicates that this port will not avoid transmitting BPDUs on edge-port.

staPortRootGuardStatus.name: staPortRootGuardStatus
staPortRootGuardStatus.description: Specifies the desired status of the root guard. This variable configures the root guard feature to enforce the root bridge placement in the network.

staPortBpduGuardAutoRecovery.name: staPortBpduGuardAutoRecovery
staPortBpduGuardAutoRecovery.description: A value of enabled(1) indicates that BPDU port guard auto recovery mechanism is enabled for this port. A value of disabled(2) indicates that the mechanism is disabled.

staPortBpduGuardAutoRecoveryInterval.name: staPortBpduGuardAutoRecoveryInterval
staPortBpduGuardAutoRecoveryInterval.description: The interval in seconds used by BPDU guard auto recovery mechanism.

staPortTcPropStop.name: staPortTcPropStop
staPortTcPropStop.description: Stop topology change progate on this ifindex. Don't enable on potentially ring port.

staProtocolType.name: staProtocolType
staProtocolType.description: The version of Spanning Tree Protocol the bridge is currently running. The value 'stp(1)' indicates the Spanning Tree Protocol is as specified in IEEE 802.1D,'rstp(2)' indicates that the Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol is as specified in IEEE 802.1w, and the value 'mstp(3)' indicates that the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol is as specified in IEEE 802.1s. New values may be defined in the future as new or updated versions of the protocol become available.

staTxHoldCount.name: staTxHoldCount
staTxHoldCount.description: The value used by the Port Transmit state machine to limit the maximum transmission rate.

staPathCostMethod.name: staPathCostMethod
staPathCostMethod.description: Indicates the type of spanning tree path cost mode configured on the switch. This mode applies to all instances of the spanning tree protocol running on the switch. When the value of this MIB object is changed, the path cost of all ports will be reassigned to the default path cost values based on the new spanning tree path cost mode and the ports' speed. When the value of this MIB object is set to long(2), the staPortLongPathCost MIB object must be used to retrieve/configure the spanning tree port path cost as a 32-bit value. The set operation on dot1dStpPortPathCost in BRIDGE-MIB will be rejected. While retrieving the value of dot1dStpPortPathCost, the maximum value of 65535 will be returned if the value of staPortLongPathCost for the same instance exceeds 65535. When the value of this MIB object is set to short(1), the dot1dStpPortPathCost in BRIDGE-MIB must be used.

mstName.name: mstName
mstName.description: The name of the Multiple Spanning Tree region.

mstRevision.name: mstRevision
mstRevision.description: The Revision number of the Multiple Spanning Tree region.

mstMaxHops.name: mstMaxHops
mstMaxHops.description: The max hop number counts of the Multiple Spanning Tree region.

xstInstanceCfgTable.name: xstInstanceCfgTable
xstInstanceCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure the property of a specific instance in Multiple Spanning Tree or Rapid Spanning Tree. If Rapid Spanning Tree protocol is in use, the mstInstanceEditIndex is always 0.

xstInstanceCfgEntry.name: xstInstanceCfgEntry
xstInstanceCfgEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the property of the RST or MST instance.

xstInstanceCfgIndex.name: xstInstanceCfgIndex
xstInstanceCfgIndex.description: An arbitrary integer within the range from 1 to the value of the maximum instance that uniquely identifies a spanning tree instance.

xstInstanceCfgPriority.name: xstInstanceCfgPriority
xstInstanceCfgPriority.description: The priority of a specific spanning tree instance. The value assigned should be in the range 0-61440 in steps of 4096.

xstInstanceCfgTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: xstInstanceCfgTimeSinceTopologyChange
xstInstanceCfgTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last topology change detected by the bridge entity in RST or MST.

xstInstanceCfgTopChanges.name: xstInstanceCfgTopChanges
xstInstanceCfgTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge in RST or MST since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

xstInstanceCfgDesignatedRoot.name: xstInstanceCfgDesignatedRoot
xstInstanceCfgDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol. (802.1s) or Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (802.1w) executed by this node. This value is used as the root identifier parameter in all configuration bridge PDUs originated by this node.

xstInstanceCfgRootCost.name: xstInstanceCfgRootCost
xstInstanceCfgRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge of the RST or MST.

xstInstanceCfgRootPort.name: xstInstanceCfgRootPort
xstInstanceCfgRootPort.description: The number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge of the RST or MST.

xstInstanceCfgMaxAge.name: xstInstanceCfgMaxAge
xstInstanceCfgMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol (802.1s) or Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol (802.1w) information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

xstInstanceCfgHelloTime.name: xstInstanceCfgHelloTime
xstInstanceCfgHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the specific spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using in RST or MST.

xstInstanceCfgHoldTime.name: xstInstanceCfgHoldTime
xstInstanceCfgHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

xstInstanceCfgForwardDelay.name: xstInstanceCfgForwardDelay
xstInstanceCfgForwardDelay.description: For RST or MST protocol, this time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the listening and learning states, which precede the forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the forwarding database. This value is the current value being used by the bridge. xstInstanceCfgBridgeForwardDelay defines the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.

xstInstanceCfgBridgeMaxAge.name: xstInstanceCfgBridgeMaxAge
xstInstanceCfgBridgeMaxAge.description: For RST or MST protocol, the time (in hundredths of second) that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of xstInstanceCfgBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second.

xstInstanceCfgBridgeHelloTime.name: xstInstanceCfgBridgeHelloTime
xstInstanceCfgBridgeHelloTime.description: For RST or MST protocol,the time (in hundredths of a second) that all bridges use for HelloTime when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second.

xstInstanceCfgBridgeForwardDelay.name: xstInstanceCfgBridgeForwardDelay
xstInstanceCfgBridgeForwardDelay.description: For RST or MST protocol, the time (in hundredths of a second) that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of xstInstanceCfgBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second.

xstInstanceCfgTxHoldCount.name: xstInstanceCfgTxHoldCount
xstInstanceCfgTxHoldCount.description: For RST or MST protocol, the value used by the port transmit state machine to limit the maximum transmission rate.

xstInstanceCfgPathCostMethod.name: xstInstanceCfgPathCostMethod
xstInstanceCfgPathCostMethod.description: For RST or MST protocol, this indicates the type of spanning tree path cost mode used by the switch. The mode applies to all instances of the Spanning Tree protocol running on the switch. When the value of this MIB object is changed, the path cost of all ports will be reassigned to the default path cost values based on the new spanning tree path cost mode and the ports' speed. When the value of this MIB object is set to long(2), the xstInstancePortPathCost MIB object must be used in order to retrieve/configure the spanning tree port path cost as a 32-bit value. The set operation on dot1dStpPortPathCost in BRIDGE-MIB will be rejected. While retrieving the value of dot1dStpPortPathCost, the maximum value of 65535 will be returned if the value of xstInstancePortPathCost for the same instance exceeds 65535. When the value of this MIB object is set to short(1), the dot1dStpPortPathCost in BRIDGE-MIB must be used.

xstInstancePortTable.name: xstInstancePortTable
xstInstancePortTable.description: The extension table for dot1dStpPortEntry to provide additional Spanning Tree information and configuration.

xstInstancePortPriority.name: xstInstancePortPriority
xstInstancePortPriority.description: Defines the priority used for this port in the Spanning Tree Algorithm. If the path cost for all ports on a switch is the same, the port with the highest priority (i.e., lowest value) will be configured as an active link in the Spanning Tree. This makes a port with higher priority less likely to be blocked if the Spanning Tree Algorithm is detecting network loops. Where more than one port is assigned the highest priority, the port with lowest numeric identifier will be enabled.

xstInstancePortState.name: xstInstancePortState
xstInstancePortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame: discarding(1): Port receives configuration messages, but does not forward packets. learning(2): Port has transmitted configuration messages for an interval set by the Forward Delay parameter without receiving contradictory information. Port address table is cleared, and the port begins learning addresses. forwarding(3): Port forwards packets, and continues learning addresses. For ports which are disabled (see xstInstancePortEnable), this object will have a value of discarding(1).

xstInstancePortEnable.name: xstInstancePortEnable
xstInstancePortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

xstInstancePortDesignatedRoot.name: xstInstancePortDesignatedRoot
xstInstancePortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique bridge identifier of the bridge recorded as the root in the configuration BPDUs transmitted by the designated bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

xstInstancePortDesignatedCost.name: xstInstancePortDesignatedCost
xstInstancePortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the designated port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the root path cost field in received bridge PDUs.

xstInstancePortDesignatedBridge.name: xstInstancePortDesignatedBridge
xstInstancePortDesignatedBridge.description: The bridge identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the designated bridge for this port's segment.

xstInstancePortDesignatedPort.name: xstInstancePortDesignatedPort
xstInstancePortDesignatedPort.description: The port identifier of the port on the designated bridge for this port's segment.

xstInstancePortForwardTransitions.name: xstInstancePortForwardTransitions
xstInstancePortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the learning state to the forwarding state.

xstInstancePortPortRole.name: xstInstancePortPortRole
xstInstancePortPortRole.description: The role of the port in the RST or MST protocol: (1) The port has no role within the spanning tree (2) The port is part of the active topology connecting the bridge to the root bridge (i.e., root port) (3) The port is connecting a LAN through the bridge to the root bridge (i.e., designated port) (4) The port may provide connectivity if other bridges, bridge ports, or LANs fail or are removed. (5) The port provides backup if other bridges, bridge ports, or LANs fail or are removed. (6) For MST protocol only, indicates whether this instance is in a master role.

xstInstancePortAdminPathCost.name: xstInstancePortAdminPathCost
xstInstancePortAdminPathCost.description: The admin value of the MST internal pathcost, in the range of 1 to 200000000. This parameter is used to determine the best path between devices. Therefore, lower values should be assigned to ports attached to faster media, and higher values assigned to ports with slower media. (Path cost takes precedence over port priority).

xstInstancePortOperPathCost.name: xstInstancePortOperPathCost
xstInstancePortOperPathCost.description: The oper value of the RST pathcost or MST internal pathcost, in the range of 1 to 200000000. This parameter is used to determine the best path between devices. Therefore, lower values should be assigned to ports attached to faster media, and higher values assigned to ports with slower media. (Path cost takes precedence over port priority).

mstInstanceEditTable.name: mstInstanceEditTable
mstInstanceEditTable.description: The Multiple Spanning Tree region instance vlan configuration table. Please read the actual instance vlan mapped in the mstInstanceOperTable.

mstInstanceEditEntry.name: mstInstanceEditEntry
mstInstanceEditEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the status of the MSTP instance.

mstInstanceEditIndex.name: mstInstanceEditIndex
mstInstanceEditIndex.description: An arbitrary integer within the range from 1 to the value of the maximum instance that uniquely identifies a spanning tree instance.

mstInstanceEditVlansMap.name: mstInstanceEditVlansMap
mstInstanceEditVlansMap.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 0 through 7; the second octet to VLANs 8 through 15; etc., The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. To create a row, write any of mstInstanceEditVlansMap, mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k, mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k or mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k, to a non-empty list. To destroy a row, write all of these four variables to an empty list.

mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k.name: mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k
mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with vlanIndex values of 1024 through 2047. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 1024 through 1031; the second octet to VLANs 1032 through 1039; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. To create a row, write any of mstInstanceEditVlansMap, mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k, mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k or mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k, to a non-empty list. To destroy a row, write all of these four variables to an empty list.

mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k.name: mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k
mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with vlanIndex values of 2048 through 3071. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 2048 through 2055; the second octet to VLANs 2056 through 2063; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. To create a row, write any of mstInstanceEditVlansMap, mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k, mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k or mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k, to a non-empty list. To destroy a row, write all of these four variables to an empty list.

mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k.name: mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k
mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with vlanIndex values of 3072 through 4095. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 3072 through 3079; the second octet to VLANs 3080 through 3087; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'. To create a row, write any of mstInstanceEditVlansMap, mstInstanceEditVlansMap2k, mstInstanceEditVlansMap3k or mstInstanceEditVlansMap4k, to a non-empty list. To destroy a row, write all of these four variables to an empty list.

mstInstanceEditRemainingHops.name: mstInstanceEditRemainingHops
mstInstanceEditRemainingHops.description: The remaining hop count for this MST instance.

mstInstanceOperTable.name: mstInstanceOperTable
mstInstanceOperTable.description: The Multiple Spanning Tree region instance vlan mapped table.

mstInstanceOperEntry.name: mstInstanceOperEntry
mstInstanceOperEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the status of the MSTP instance.

mstInstanceOperIndex.name: mstInstanceOperIndex
mstInstanceOperIndex.description: An arbitrary integer within the range from 1 to the value of the maximum instance that uniquely identifies a spanning tree instance.

mstInstanceOperVlansMap.name: mstInstanceOperVlansMap
mstInstanceOperVlansMap.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 0 through 7; the second octet to VLANs 8 through 15; etc., The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'.

mstInstanceOperVlansMap2k.name: mstInstanceOperVlansMap2k
mstInstanceOperVlansMap2k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with vlanIndex values of 1024 through 2047. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 1024 through 1031; the second octet to VLANs 1032 through 1039; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'.

mstInstanceOperVlansMap3k.name: mstInstanceOperVlansMap3k
mstInstanceOperVlansMap3k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with vlanIndex values of 2048 through 3071. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 2048 through 2055; the second octet to VLANs 2056 through 2063; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'.

mstInstanceOperVlansMap4k.name: mstInstanceOperVlansMap4k
mstInstanceOperVlansMap4k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANS with vlanIndex values of 3072 through 4095. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with vlanIndex values of 3072 through 3079; the second octet to VLANs 3080 through 3087; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value vlanIndex in that octet. For each VLAN, if it is mapped to this MSTP instance, then the bit corresponding to that VLAN is set to '1'.

staLoopbackDetectionPortTable.name: staLoopbackDetectionPortTable
staLoopbackDetectionPortTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the spanning tree loopback detection of each port or trunk

staLoopbackDetectionPortIfIndex.name: staLoopbackDetectionPortIfIndex
staLoopbackDetectionPortIfIndex.description: The port and the trunk interfaces of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

staLoopbackDetectionPortStatus.name: staLoopbackDetectionPortStatus
staLoopbackDetectionPortStatus.description: Status of the port on whether spanning tree loopback detection is enabled.

staLoopbackDetectionPortTrapStatus.name: staLoopbackDetectionPortTrapStatus
staLoopbackDetectionPortTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the loopback BPDUs have been detected.

staLoopbackDetectionPortReleaseMode.name: staLoopbackDetectionPortReleaseMode
staLoopbackDetectionPortReleaseMode.description: Setting it to auto(1) indicates that this port can be released from discarding state automatically after loopback has occurred. Setting it to manual(2) indicates that this port can be released from discarding state manually after loopback has occurred.

staLoopbackDetectionPortRelease.name: staLoopbackDetectionPortRelease
staLoopbackDetectionPortRelease.description: Set this to release(2) to release the port from discarding state. noRelease(1) will always be obtained when reading this variable.

staSystemBPDUFlooding.name: staSystemBPDUFlooding
staSystemBPDUFlooding.description: Global BPDU flooding behavior configuration. When BPDU is received on spanning tree disabled port. (1) BPDU is flooded to all other spanning tree disabled ports in vlan that received BPDU. (2) BPDU is flooded to all other spanning tree disabled ports.

restartOpCodeFile.name: restartOpCodeFile
restartOpCodeFile.description: Name of op-code file for start-up.

restartConfigFile.name: restartConfigFile
restartConfigFile.description: Name of configuration file for start-up.

restartControl.name: restartControl
restartControl.description: Setting this object to warmBoot(2) causes the device to reinitialize itself such that neither the agent configuration nor the protocol entity implementation is altered. Setting this object to coldBoot(3) causes the device to reinitialize itself such that the agent's configuration or the protocol entity implementation may be altered. When the device is running normally, this variable has a value of running(1).

mirrorTable.name: mirrorTable
mirrorTable.description: Table for port mirroring, enabling a port to be mirrored to/from another port. Not all ports can be mirrored and limitations may apply as to which ports can be used as either source or destination ports.

mirrorDestinationPort.name: mirrorDestinationPort
mirrorDestinationPort.description: The destination port interface for mirrored packets. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mirrorSourcePort.name: mirrorSourcePort
mirrorSourcePort.description: The source port interface for mirrored packets. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mirrorType.name: mirrorType
mirrorType.description: If this value is rx(1), receive packets will be mirrored. If this value is tx(2), transmit packets will be mirrored. If this value is both(3), both receive and transmit packets will be mirrored.

mirrorStatus.name: mirrorStatus
mirrorStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

vlanMirrorTable.name: vlanMirrorTable
vlanMirrorTable.description: Table for VLAN mirroring, enabling a VLAN to be mirrored to a port.

vlanMirrorDestinationPort.name: vlanMirrorDestinationPort
vlanMirrorDestinationPort.description: The destination port interface for mirrored packets. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

vlanMirrorSourceVlan.name: vlanMirrorSourceVlan
vlanMirrorSourceVlan.description: The source VLAN for mirrored packets. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB.

vlanMirrorStatus.name: vlanMirrorStatus
vlanMirrorStatus.description: Set this to valid(1) to create an entry. Set this to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

rspanTable.name: rspanTable
rspanTable.description: A table that contains the settings of RSPAN.

rspanSessionId.name: rspanSessionId
rspanSessionId.description: The session ID that may specify an entry in the table which contains destination port(s) information.

rspanSrcTxPorts.name: rspanSrcTxPorts
rspanSrcTxPorts.description: Specifies the source port list in tx mode.

rspanSrcRxPorts.name: rspanSrcRxPorts
rspanSrcRxPorts.description: Specifies the source port list in rx mode.

rspanDstPort.name: rspanDstPort
rspanDstPort.description: The port number of a destination port. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

rspanDstPortTag.name: rspanDstPortTag
rspanDstPortTag.description: Specifies the traffic which is sent out from source port with RSPAN VLAN ID or not.

rspanSwitchRole.name: rspanSwitchRole
rspanSwitchRole.description: Specifies the role of current switch.

rspanRemoteVlanId.name: rspanRemoteVlanId
rspanRemoteVlanId.description: Specifies the ID of a RSPAN VLAN.

rspanOperStatus.name: rspanOperStatus
rspanOperStatus.description: The operational status of the entry. A status of up(1) means the setting of a session is complete and it has started performing its function. A status of down(2) means no function is performed because of incompleted session setting.

rspanStatus.name: rspanStatus
rspanStatus.description: Set this to valid(1) to create an entry. Set this to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

macMirrorTable.name: macMirrorTable
macMirrorTable.description: Table for MAC mirroring, enabling a MAC address to be mirrored to a port.

macMirrorDestinationPort.name: macMirrorDestinationPort
macMirrorDestinationPort.description: The destination port interface for mirrored packets. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

macMirrorSourceMacAddr.name: macMirrorSourceMacAddr
macMirrorSourceMacAddr.description: Packets with matching source MAC address will be monitored.

macMirrorStatus.name: macMirrorStatus
macMirrorStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

igmpSnoopStatus.name: igmpSnoopStatus
igmpSnoopStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping on the device. When enabled, the device will examine IGMP packets and set up filters for IGMP ports.

igmpSnoopQuerier.name: igmpSnoopQuerier
igmpSnoopQuerier.description: Enables (disables) whether the switch acts as an IGMP querier.

igmpSnoopRouterPortExpireTime.name: igmpSnoopRouterPortExpireTime
igmpSnoopRouterPortExpireTime.description: Sets the time (in seconds) the switch waits after the previous querier has stopped querying before the router port (which received query packets from previous querier) expires.

igmpSnoopRouterCurrentVlanIndex.name: igmpSnoopRouterCurrentVlanIndex
igmpSnoopRouterCurrentVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to igmpSnoopRouterStaticTable.

igmpSnoopRouterCurrentPorts.name: igmpSnoopRouterCurrentPorts
igmpSnoopRouterCurrentPorts.description: The set of ports which are current router ports, including static router ports. Please refer to igmpSnoopRouterStaticTable.

igmpSnoopRouterCurrentStatus.name: igmpSnoopRouterCurrentStatus
igmpSnoopRouterCurrentStatus.description: The set of ports which are static router ports.

igmpSnoopRouterStaticVlanIndex.name: igmpSnoopRouterStaticVlanIndex
igmpSnoopRouterStaticVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to igmpSnoopRouterStaticTable.

igmpSnoopRouterStaticPorts.name: igmpSnoopRouterStaticPorts
igmpSnoopRouterStaticPorts.description: The set of ports which are static router ports.

igmpSnoopRouterStaticStatus.name: igmpSnoopRouterStaticStatus
igmpSnoopRouterStaticStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

igmpSnoopMulticastStaticVlanIndex.name: igmpSnoopMulticastStaticVlanIndex
igmpSnoopMulticastStaticVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to igmpSnoopMulticastStaticTable.

igmpSnoopMulticastStaticPorts.name: igmpSnoopMulticastStaticPorts
igmpSnoopMulticastStaticPorts.description: The set of ports which are members.

igmpSnoopMulticastStaticStatus.name: igmpSnoopMulticastStaticStatus
igmpSnoopMulticastStaticStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanTable.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanTable
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanTable.description: Table for enabling or disabling IGMP snooping per VLAN.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanEntry.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanEntry
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanEntry.description: Entry for enabling or disabling IGMP snooping.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanIndex.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanIndex
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanIndex.description: Same is dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. This table has only one entry - the entry for the VLAN of the management interface.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanStatus.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanStatus
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping on this VLAN. When enabled, the device will examine IGMP packets and set up filters for IGMP ports.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeave.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeave
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeave.description: The parameter to enable or disable the Immediate-Leave feature on this VLAN.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanGeneralQuerySuppress.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanGeneralQuerySuppression
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanGeneralQuerySuppress.description: The parameter to enable or disable the general query suppresion on this VLAN.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanLastMemQueryCount.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanLastMemQueryCount
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanLastMemQueryCount.description: Represents the number of queries sent by the switch before it assumes there are no local members.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanLastMemQueryIntvl.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanLastMemQueryIntvl
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanLastMemQueryIntvl.description: The last member query interval is the max response time inserted into group-specific queries sent in response to leave group messages,and is also the the max response time inserted into group-and-source-specific query messages.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanProxyAddress.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanProxyAddress
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanProxyAddress.description: Represents the address of queries sent by the switch.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanQueryIntvl.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanQueryIntvl
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanQueryIntvl.description: Represents the query interval of queries sent by the switch.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanQueryRespIntvl.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanQueryRespIntvl
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanQueryRespIntvl.description: Represents the query response interval of queries sent by the switch.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanProxyReporting.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanProxyReporting
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanProxyReporting.description: Set this variable to enabled(1) to enable the feature. Set this variable to disabled(2) to disable the feature. Set this variable to default(3), the status of the feature is decided by the global configuration.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanVersion.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanVersion
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanVersion.description: the version of igmp packets is supported by this vlan.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanVersionExclusive.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanVersionExclusive
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanVersionExclusive.description: Enable/disable control of the IGMP Snooping exclusive supported version.

igmpSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeaveByHost.name: igmpSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeaveByHostIp
igmpSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeaveByHost.description: The parameter to enable or disable the Immediate-Leave feature by host ip on this VLAN.

igmpSnoopMulticastGroupVlanIndex.name: igmpSnoopMulticastGroupVlanIndex
igmpSnoopMulticastGroupVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to igmpSnoopMulticastStaticTable.

igmpSnoopMulticastGroupPorts.name: igmpSnoopMulticastGroupPorts
igmpSnoopMulticastGroupPorts.description: The set of ports which are members of a multicast group, including static members. Please refer to igmpSnoopMulticastStaticTable.

igmpSnoopMulticastGroupStatus.name: igmpSnoopMulticastGroupStatus
igmpSnoopMulticastGroupStatus.description: The set of ports which are static IGMP member ports.

igmpSnoopMulticastGroupPortCount.name: igmpSnoopMulticastGroupPortCount
igmpSnoopMulticastGroupPortCount.description: The number of forwarding port in this group

igmpSnoopFilterStatus.name: igmpSnoopFilterStatus
igmpSnoopFilterStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP filtering on the device.

igmpSnoopProfileTable.name: igmpSnoopProfileTable
igmpSnoopProfileTable.description: The table for configuring the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopProfileEntry.name: igmpSnoopProfileEntry
igmpSnoopProfileEntry.description: The entry for configuring the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopProfileId.name: igmpSnoopProfileId
igmpSnoopProfileId.description: The ID of the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopProfileAction.name: igmpSnoopProfileAction
igmpSnoopProfileAction.description: The access mode of the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopProfileStatus.name: igmpSnoopProfileStatus
igmpSnoopProfileStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

igmpSnoopProfileCtlId.name: igmpSnoopProfileCtlId
igmpSnoopProfileCtlId.description: The ID of the IGMP snooping profile. The default value is zero, meaning that no ID is specified. In order to create a profile, a non-zero value must be specified.

igmpSnoopProfileCtlInetAddressType.name: igmpSnoopProfileCtlInetAddressType
igmpSnoopProfileCtlInetAddressType.description: The address type is associated with this agent. Only ipv4(1) type is supported.

igmpSnoopProfileCtlStartInetAddress.name: igmpSnoopProfileCtlStartInetAddress
igmpSnoopProfileCtlStartInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the start of the controlled IP multicast addresses.

igmpSnoopProfileCtlEndInetAddress.name: igmpSnoopProfileCtlEndInetAddress
igmpSnoopProfileCtlEndInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the end of the controlled IP multicast addresses.

igmpSnoopProfileCtlAction.name: igmpSnoopProfileCtlAction
igmpSnoopProfileCtlAction.description: Setting it to create(2) creates the range of the controlled IP multicast addresses. Setting it to destroy(3) destroys the range of the controlled IP multicast addresses. When the action is completed, this object becomes noAction(1).

igmpSnoopProfileRangeTable.name: igmpSnoopProfileRangeTable
igmpSnoopProfileRangeTable.description: The table for configuring the range of the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopProfileRangeEntry.name: igmpSnoopProfileRangeEntry
igmpSnoopProfileRangeEntry.description: The entry for configuring the range of the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopProfileRangeInetAddressType.name: igmpSnoopProfileRangeInetAddressType
igmpSnoopProfileRangeInetAddressType.description: The address type is associated with this agent. Only ipv4(1) type is supported.

igmpSnoopProfileRangeStartInetAddress.name: igmpSnoopProfileRangeStartInetAddress
