igmpSnoopProfileRangeStartInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the start of the controlled IP multicast addresses.

igmpSnoopProfileRangeEndInetAddress.name: igmpSnoopProfileRangeEndInetAddress
igmpSnoopProfileRangeEndInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the end of the controlled IP multicast addresses.

igmpSnoopProfileRangeAction.name: igmpSnoopProfileRangeAction
igmpSnoopProfileRangeAction.description: The access mode of the IGMP snooping profile.

igmpSnoopFilterPortTable.name: igmpSnoopFilterPortTable
igmpSnoopFilterPortTable.description: Table for port configuration in IGMP filtering.

igmpSnoopFilterPortEntry.name: igmpSnoopFilterPortEntry
igmpSnoopFilterPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in IGMP filtering.

igmpSnoopFilterPortIndex.name: igmpSnoopFilterPortIndex
igmpSnoopFilterPortIndex.description: The port and trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

igmpSnoopFilterPortProfileId.name: igmpSnoopFilterPortProfileId
igmpSnoopFilterPortProfileId.description: The igmpSnoopProfileEntry identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of the igmpSnoopProfileId object. If there is no corresponding entry in the igmpSnoopProfileTable, then no association exists. In particular, if this value is zero, no associated profile will be generated, as zero is not a valid profile index.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortTable.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortTable
igmpSnoopThrottlePortTable.description: Table for port configuration in IGMP throttling.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortEntry.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortEntry
igmpSnoopThrottlePortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in IGMP throttling.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortIndex.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortIndex
igmpSnoopThrottlePortIndex.description: The port and trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortRunningStatus.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortRunningStatus
igmpSnoopThrottlePortRunningStatus.description: Describes the running status of the IGMP throttling to the switch. A value of true(1) indicates the IGMP throttling mechanism is active. A value of false(2) indicates the IGMP throttling mechanism is inactive.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortAction.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortAction
igmpSnoopThrottlePortAction.description: The action mode of the IGMP throttling. A value of replace(1) means to replace a joined multicast group randomly when an interface receives an IGMP report and the number of current joined multicast groups is equal to the maximum number of IGMP groups that the interface can join. A value of deny(2) means to deny the IGMP report request when an interface receives an IGMP report and the number of current joined multicast groups is equal to the maximum number of IGMP groups that the interface can join.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortMaxGroups.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortMaxGroups
igmpSnoopThrottlePortMaxGroups.description: The maximum number of IGMP groups that the interface can join.

igmpSnoopThrottlePortCurrentGroups.name: igmpSnoopThrottlePortCurrentGroups
igmpSnoopThrottlePortCurrentGroups.description: The current number of IGMP groups that the interface has joined.

igmpSnoopPortTable.name: igmpSnoopPortTable
igmpSnoopPortTable.description: Table of IGMP Snooping service per port.

igmpSnoopPortEntry.name: igmpSnoopPortEntry
igmpSnoopPortEntry.description: Entry of IGMP Snooping service per port.

igmpSnoopPortIndex.name: igmpSnoopPortIndex
igmpSnoopPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the igmpSnoopPortTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

igmpSnoopQueryDrop.name: igmpSnoopQueryDrop
igmpSnoopQueryDrop.description: Parameter to enable or disable dropping IGMP Query packet.

igmpSnoopMulticastDataDrop.name: igmpSnoopMulticastDataDrop
igmpSnoopMulticastDataDrop.description: Parameter to enable or disable dropping IP multicast data

igmpSnoopAuthentication.name: igmpSnoopAuthentication
igmpSnoopAuthentication.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP Authentication

igmpSnoopProxyReporting.name: igmpSnoopProxyReporting
igmpSnoopProxyReporting.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping proxy reporting on the device.

igmpSnoopRouterAlertOptionCheck.name: igmpSnoopRouterAlertOptionCheck
igmpSnoopRouterAlertOptionCheck.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping router alert option check on the device.

igmpSnoopTcnFlood.name: igmpSnoopTcnFlood
igmpSnoopTcnFlood.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping tcn flood on the device.

igmpSnoopTcnQuerySolicit.name: igmpSnoopTcnQuerySolicit
igmpSnoopTcnQuerySolicit.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping tcn query solicit on the device.

igmpSnoopUnregisteredDataFlood.name: igmpSnoopUnregisteredDataFlood
igmpSnoopUnregisteredDataFlood.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping Unregistered data flood solicit on the device.

igmpSnoopUnsolicitedReportInterval.name: igmpSnoopUnsolicitedReportInterval
igmpSnoopUnsolicitedReportInterval.description: Setting this value to specify how long (in seconds) the uplink ports should transmit unsolicited reports.

igmpSnoopVersionExclusive.name: igmpSnoopVersionExclusive
igmpSnoopVersionExclusive.description: Parameter to enable or disable IGMP snooping version exclusive on the device.

igmpSnoopMrouterForwardMode.name: igmpSnoopMrouterForwardMode
igmpSnoopMrouterForwardMode.description: Paremete to set IGMP snooping Mrouter port forward mode. When set dynamic, IGMP snooping Mrouter port won't forward multicast streams received from other mrouter port. When set forward, IGMP snooping Mrouter port will forward multicast streams received from other mrouter port.

igmpSnoopForwardingPriority.name: igmpSnoopForwardingPriority
igmpSnoopForwardingPriority.description: Configure IGMP snooping multicast stream forwarding priority. If value is 65535, it means the priority is disabled

igmpSnoopQueryDropTable.name: igmpSnoopQueryDropTable
igmpSnoopQueryDropTable.description: Table of IGMP Snooping query drop per vlan and per vlan configuration.

igmpSnoopQueryDropEntry.name: igmpSnoopQueryDropEntry
igmpSnoopQueryDropEntry.description: Entry of IGMP Snooping service per port and per VLAN.

igmpSnoopQueryDropPortIndex.name: igmpSnoopQueryDropPortIndex
igmpSnoopQueryDropPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the igmpSnoopPortTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

igmpSnoopQueryDropVlanBitmap.name: igmpSnoopQueryDropVlanBitmap
igmpSnoopQueryDropVlanBitmap.description: The VLAN bitmap which query drop applied on this port. If all zero, it means disable, For all VLAN, please use igmpSnoopPortTable to configure.

igmpSnoopClearDynamicGroups.name: igmpSnoopClearDynamicGroups
igmpSnoopClearDynamicGroups.description: The current number of IGMP groups that the interface has joined.

igmpSnoopVlanTable.name: igmpSnoopVlanTable
igmpSnoopVlanTable.description: Table of IGMP Snooping service per port.

igmpSnoopVlanEntry.name: igmpSnoopVlanEntry
igmpSnoopVlanEntry.description: Entry of IGMP Snooping service per VLAN.

netConfigEntry.name: netConfigEntry
netConfigEntry.description: A set of configuration parameters for a particular network interface on this device. If the device has no network interface, this table is empty. The index is composed of the ifIndex assigned to the corresponding interface.

netConfigIfIndex.name: netConfigIfIndex
netConfigIfIndex.description: The VLAN interface being used by this table entry. Only the VLAN interfaces which have an IP configured will appear in the table.

netConfigIPAddress.name: netConfigIPAddress
netConfigIPAddress.description: The IP address of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask is 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use BOOTP to try to figure out what these values should be. If BOOTP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

netConfigSubnetMask.name: netConfigSubnetMask
netConfigSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask of this Net interface. The default value for this object is 0.0.0.0. If either the netConfigIPAddress or netConfigSubnetMask are 0.0.0.0, then when the device boots, it may use BOOTP to try to figure out what these values should be. If BOOTP fails, before the device can talk on the network, this value must be configured (e.g., through a terminal attached to the device).

netConfigPrimaryInterface.name: netConfigPrimaryInterface
netConfigPrimaryInterface.description: Whether this is a primary interface.

netConfigUnnumbered.name: netConfigUnnumbered
netConfigUnnumbered.description: Whether this is an unnumbered interface.

netConfigStatus.name: netConfigStatus
netConfigStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row entry. This object isused to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device (see NOTE below); - 'notReady', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is missing information necessary in order to be available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndGo', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndWait', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row (but not make it available for use by the managed device); and, - 'destroy', which is supplied by a management station wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row. Whereas five of the six values (all except 'notReady') may be specified in a management protocol set operation, only three values will be returned in response to a management protocol retrieval operation: 'notReady', 'notInService' or 'active'. That is, when queried, an existing conceptual row has only three states: it is either available for use by the managed device (the status column has value 'active'); it is not available for use by the managed device, though the agent has sufficient information to make it so (the status column has value 'notInService'); or, it is not available for use by the managed device, and an attempt to make it so would fail because the agent has insufficient information (the state column has value 'notReady'). For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

netDefaultGateway.name: netDefaultGateway
netDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway. If this value is undefined or unknown, it shall have the value 0.0.0.0.

ipDhcpRestart.name: ipDhcpRestart
ipDhcpRestart.description: When set to restart(1) the DHCP server will restart. When read, this value always returns noRestart(2).

dhcpcInterfaceTable.name: dhcpcInterfaceTable
dhcpcInterfaceTable.description: Table for DHCP client information listed by interface. Depending on the nature of the product, this table may have only one entry(e.g. for the management VLAN), or may have many entries(e.g. for all ports, or for all static VLANs).

dhcpcInterfaceEntry.name: dhcpcInterfaceEntry
dhcpcInterfaceEntry.description: Entry for DHCP client information listed by interface.

dhcpcIfIndex.name: dhcpcIfIndex
dhcpcIfIndex.description: This is defined by ifIndex in the IF-MIB.(static vlan if index)

dhcpcIfVendorClassIdMode.name: dhcpcIfVendorClassIdMode
dhcpcIfVendorClassIdMode.description: Whether the vendor class ID is in text mode or in Hex mode.

dhcpcIfVendorClassId.name: dhcpcIfVendorClassId
dhcpcIfVendorClassId.description: The value that the DHCP client sets in the vendor class_id option of DHCPDISCOVER and DHCPREQUEST messages. This value may be used by DHCP servers to identify vendor classof the client.

pingIpAddress.name: pingIpAddress
pingIpAddress.description: Specifies the IP address of the device that is planned to ping.

pingPacketSize.name: pingPacketSize
pingPacketSize.description: Specifies the size of each data potion of ping packets in bytes.

pingCompleted.name: pingCompleted
pingCompleted.description: A value of true(1) will be read when this ping operation has been either responded to or changed to the time-out status. A value of false(2) will be read when there is a ping operation running and all associated objects in the pingMgt operation cannot be modified during this period.

pingAction.name: pingAction
pingAction.description: The action of the pingMgt operation. Sets these objects to pingStart(2) to begin the ping operation. Once the action is set to pingStart(2), the associated pingMgt objects cannot be modified until this ping operation is completed (pingCompleted is true). When the ping has ended or there is no ping operation performing, this object will get a value of noAction(1).

pingProbeCount.name: pingProbeCount
pingProbeCount.description: Specifies the number of times to perform a ping operation at a remote host.

pingSentPackets.name: pingSentPackets
pingSentPackets.description: The value of this object reflects the number of probes sent. The value of this object must be reported as 0 when no probes have been sent.

pingReceivedPackets.name: pingReceivedPackets
pingReceivedPackets.description: Number of responses received. The value of this object must be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.

pingPacketLossRate.name: pingPacketLossRate
pingPacketLossRate.description: Packet loss rate of this ping operation. This variable is calculated by pingReceivedPackets and pingSentPackets. The rate is expressed as a percentage.

pingHistoryTable.name: pingHistoryTable
pingHistoryTable.description: Contains the executive result information for the ping operation.

pingHistoryEntry.name: pingHistoryEntry
pingHistoryEntry.description: A conceptual row in the pingHistory table.

pingHistoryIndex.name: pingHistoryIndex
pingHistoryIndex.description: A new entry in this table is created when the result of a ping probe is determined. The old entries will be cleared when a new ping action is started.

pingHistoryResponse.name: pingHistoryResponse
pingHistoryResponse.description: This variable represents the round trip time and is measured in milliseconds. The variable is the difference between received time and sent time for a ping probe. If the difference value is more than the time-out value or no response is received, then the variable will be 5000 milliseconds.

dhcpOption82Status.name: dhcpOption82Status
dhcpOption82Status.description: Set enabled(1) to enable DHCP Relay Option 82, set disabled(2) to disable it.

dhcpOption82Policy.name: dhcpOption82Policy
dhcpOption82Policy.description: Provide three policies to handle packet

dhcpOption82RemoteIDMode.name: dhcpOption82RemoteIDMode
dhcpOption82RemoteIDMode.description: Provide five mode for insertion remote-id sub-option of option 82. If configured-string(5) has been set, dhcpOption82RemoteIDString will take effect.

dhcpOption82RemoteIDString.name: dhcpOption82RemoteIDString
dhcpOption82RemoteIDString.description: Set string to remote-id sub-option of option 82. It only take effect when dhcpOption82RemoteIDMode is set to configured-string(5)

dhcpOption82EncodeFormat.name: dhcpOption82EncodeFormat
dhcpOption82EncodeFormat.description: Set encode format for CID and RID in option82. Set extra-subtype-included(1) will have extra subtype and length field in CID and RID. Set no-extra-subtype-included(2) will only have TLV format for CID and RID.

dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrTable.name: dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrTable
dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrTable.description: This table is to specify relay server IP address, the maximum number of server IP addresses user can specify is 5.

dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrIndex.name: dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrIndex
dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrIndex.description: The index of the relay server IP address.

dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrServerIp.name: dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrServerIp
dhcpOption82RelayServerAddrServerIp.description: The IP address of the relay server.

dhcpDynamicProvisionStatus.name: dhcpDynamicProvisionStatus
dhcpDynamicProvisionStatus.description: A per-system enable/disable configuration to decide whether to use the specified configuration file in DHCP packet. It shall use the specified configuration file in DHCP packet if this configuration is disabled and the start-up configuration file is Factory_Default_Config.cfg.

arpCacheDeleteAll.name: arpCacheDeleteAll
arpCacheDeleteAll.description: To delete all dynamic entries in the ARP cache, write this variable to delete(1). Writing this variable to noDelete(2) has no effect on the device. When read, this variable always returns noDelete(2). This object is only for Layer 2 switch.

vlanIndex.name: vlanIndex
vlanIndex.description: Based on dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. This table has only one entry - the entry for the VLAN of the management interface.

vlanAddressMethod.name: vlanAddressMethod
vlanAddressMethod.description: Method to get the IP address.

vlanPortTable.name: vlanPortTable
vlanPortTable.description: Table for port configuration in VLAN.

vlanPortEntry.name: vlanPortEntry
vlanPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in VLAN.

vlanPortIndex.name: vlanPortIndex
vlanPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qPvid in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB.

vlanPortMode.name: vlanPortMode
vlanPortMode.description: This variable sets the 802.1Q VLAN mode. Setting it to hybrid(1) sets a hybrid link. Setting it to dot1qTrunk(2) sets a trunk link. Setting it to access(3) sets an access link.

vlanPortPrivateVlanType.name: vlanPortPrivateVlanType
vlanPortPrivateVlanType.description: The port type defined for private VLAN.

vlanDot1qTunnelStatus.name: vlanDot1qTunnelStatus
vlanDot1qTunnelStatus.description: This parameter is used to globally enable/disable 802.1Q Tunneling on the device.

vlanDot1qTunnelPortTable.name: vlanDot1qTunnelPortTable
vlanDot1qTunnelPortTable.description: Table for port configuration in 802.1Q Tunneling.

vlanDot1qTunnelPortEntry.name: vlanDot1qTunnelPortEntry
vlanDot1qTunnelPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in 802.1Q Tunneling.

vlanDot1qTunnelPortIndex.name: vlanDot1qTunnelPortIndex
vlanDot1qTunnelPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

vlanDot1qTunnelPortMode.name: vlanDot1qTunnelPortMode
vlanDot1qTunnelPortMode.description: This variable sets the 802.1Q Tunneling mode. Setting it to none(1) indicates no mode in this port. Setting it to access(2) sets as dot1q-tunnel mode port which link to customer. Setting it to uplink(3) sets as dot1q-tunnel mode port which link to service-provider. If vlanDot1qTunnelStatus is disabled, it means vlanDot1qTunnelPortMode is inactive.

vlanDot1qTunnelPortEtherType.name: vlanDot1qTunnelPortEtherType
vlanDot1qTunnelPortEtherType.description: TPID for 802.1Q encapsulation. It's used to select a nonstandard (nondefault) 2-byte ethertype to identify 802.1Q tagged frames.

vlanDot1qTunnelPortPriorityMapStatus.name: vlanDot1qTunnelPortPriorityMapStatus
vlanDot1qTunnelPortPriorityMapStatus.description: Status of priority mapping. Set to enabled(1) to use 802.1p priority of inner tag as packet's priority instead of using outer tag.

voiceVlanOuiTable.name: voiceVlanOuiTable
voiceVlanOuiTable.description: A table containing the mac address which can be identified by Voice VLAN.

voiceVlanOuiEntry.name: voiceVlanOuiEntry
voiceVlanOuiEntry.description: A table containing the mac address which can be identified by Voice VLAN.

voiceVlanOuiAddress.name: voiceVlanOuiAddress
voiceVlanOuiAddress.description: MAC address can be identified by voice vlan.

voiceVlanOuiStatus.name: voiceVlanOuiStatus
voiceVlanOuiStatus.description: Current operation status of the row.

voiceVlanEnabledId.name: voiceVlanEnabledId
voiceVlanEnabledId.description: Voice VLAN enabled status and VLAN ID: enabled (1..4093), disabled (-1).

voiceVlanAgingTime.name: voiceVlanAgingTime
voiceVlanAgingTime.description: Voice VLAN aging time, the unit of which is minute.

voiceVlanPortTable.name: voiceVlanPortTable
voiceVlanPortTable.description: A list of voice VLAN port entries.

voiceVlanPortEntry.name: voiceVlanPortEntry
voiceVlanPortEntry.description: An entry containing Voice VLAN port information, which is applicable to a Voice VLAN enabled interface.

voiceVlanPortIfIndex.name: voiceVlanPortIfIndex
voiceVlanPortIfIndex.description: The index of interface on which Voice VLAN function is enabled.

voiceVlanPortSecurity.name: voiceVlanPortSecurity
voiceVlanPortSecurity.description: If the security is enabled, the port only allows voice traffic for the Voice VLAN.

voiceVlanPortPriority.name: voiceVlanPortPriority
voiceVlanPortPriority.description: The priority of the voice vlan traffic in the port.

voiceVlanPortRuleOui.name: voiceVlanPortRuleOui
voiceVlanPortRuleOui.description: The address of voice device is learned from OUI table.

voiceVlanPortRuleLldp.name: voiceVlanPortRuleLldp
voiceVlanPortRuleLldp.description: The address of voice device is learned from LLDP discovery.

voiceVlanPortRemainAge.name: voiceVlanPortRemainAge
voiceVlanPortRemainAge.description: Remaining aging time, the unit of which is minute.

dot1vProtocolExPortTable.name: dot1vProtocolExPortTable
dot1vProtocolExPortTable.description: A table that contains protocol Vlan priority information.

dot1vProtocolExPortEntry.name: dot1vProtocolExPortEntry
dot1vProtocolExPortEntry.description: A list of protocol VLAN user priority sets for each port.

dot1vProtocolExPortGroupPriority.name: dot1vProtocolExPortGroupPriority
dot1vProtocolExPortGroupPriority.description: Specifies the priority in the added tag for qualified frames.

macVlanTable.name: macVlanTable
macVlanTable.description: A table that contains the settings for MAC-based VLAN.

macVlanEntry.name: macVlanEntry
macVlanEntry.description: A conceptual row in the macVlanTable.

macVlanMacAddress.name: macVlanMacAddress
macVlanMacAddress.description: The MAC address that may specify an entry in the table which contains MAC-based VLAN information.

macVlanId.name: macVlanId
macVlanId.description: Specifies the VLAN ID which the MAC address associates with.

macVlanPriority.name: macVlanPriority
macVlanPriority.description: Specifies the priority whcich the MAC address associates with.

macVlanStatus.name: macVlanStatus
macVlanStatus.description: Set this to valid(1) to create an entry. Set this to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

macVlanMacMask.name: macVlanMacMask
macVlanMacMask.description: The MAC address mask that may specify an entry in the table which contains MAC-based VLAN information.

macVlanClearAction.name: macVlanClearAction
macVlanClearAction.description: Action for clearing macVlanTable. When this object is set to clear(2), all entries in macVlanTable will be cleared. When this object is read, the value of this object is always noClear(1).

subnetVlanTable.name: subnetVlanTable
subnetVlanTable.description: A table that contains the settings for IP subnet-based VLAN.

subnetVlanEntry.name: subnetVlanEntry
subnetVlanEntry.description: A conceptual row in the subnetVlanTable.

subnetVlanIpAddress.name: subnetVlanIpAddress
subnetVlanIpAddress.description: The IPv4 address of a subnet. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the subnetVlanMask object is not equal to x.

subnetVlanMask.name: subnetVlanMask
subnetVlanMask.description: The netmask of a subnet. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the subnetVlanIpAddress object is not equal to subnetVlanIpAddress.

subnetVlanId.name: subnetVlanId
subnetVlanId.description: Specifies the VLAN ID which the subnet associates with.

subnetVlanPriority.name: subnetVlanPriority
subnetVlanPriority.description: Specifies the priority whcich the subnet associates with.

subnetVlanStatus.name: subnetVlanStatus
subnetVlanStatus.description: Set this to valid(1) to create an entry. Set this to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

subnetVlanClearAction.name: subnetVlanClearAction
subnetVlanClearAction.description: Action for clearing subnetVlanTable. When this object is set to clear(2), all entries in subnetVlanTable will be cleared. When this object is read, the value of this object is always noClear(1).

vlanStaticExtTable.name: vlanStaticExtTable
vlanStaticExtTable.description: The extension table of dot1qVlanStaticTable. This table enhances the original table with extra vlanStaticExtRspanStatus to create and destroy RSPAN VLAN(s).

vlanStaticExtEntry.name: vlanStaticExtEntry
vlanStaticExtEntry.description: A conceptual row in the vlanStaticExtTable.

vlanStaticExtRspanStatus.name: vlanStaticExtRspanStatus
vlanStaticExtRspanStatus.description: Displays type of a VLAN is vlan(2) or rspanVlan(3). Set this to destroy(1) to destroy a RSPAN VLAN. Set this to rspanVlan(3) to create a RSPAN VLAN. Setting this to vlan(2) is not allowed.

vlanL2ProtocolTunnelPortTable.name: vlanL2ProtocolTunnelPortTable
vlanL2ProtocolTunnelPortTable.description: Table for port configuration in Layer 2 Protocol Tunneling.

vlanL2ProtocolTunnelPortEntry.name: vlanL2ProtocolTunnelPortEntry
vlanL2ProtocolTunnelPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in Layer 2 Protocol Tunneling.

vlanL2ptPortIndex.name: vlanL2ptPortIndex
vlanL2ptPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

vlanL2ptPortSta.name: vlanL2ptPortSta
vlanL2ptPortSta.description: Set enabled(1) to enable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for spanning-tree protocol. Set disabled(2) to disable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for spanning-tree protocol.

vlanL2ptPortLldp.name: vlanL2ptPortLldp
vlanL2ptPortLldp.description: Set enabled(1) to enable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for LLDP. Set disabled(2) to disable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for LLDP.

vlanL2ptPortCdp.name: vlanL2ptPortCdp
vlanL2ptPortCdp.description: Set enabled(1) to enable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for Cisco Discovery Protocol. Set disabled(2) to disable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for Cisco Discovery Protocol.

vlanL2ptPortVtp.name: vlanL2ptPortVtp
vlanL2ptPortVtp.description: Set enabled(1) to enable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for Cisco VTP. Set disabled(2) to disable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for Cisco VTP.

vlanL2ptPortPvst.name: vlanL2ptPortPvst
vlanL2ptPortPvst.description: Set enabled(1) to enable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for Cisco PVST+. Set disabled(2) to disable Layer 2 protocol tunneling for Cisco PVST+.

vlanL2ProtocolTunnelAddress.name: vlanL2ProtocolTunnelAddress
vlanL2ProtocolTunnelAddress.description: Destination MAC address for PDU tunneling.

vlanStaticTable.name: vlanStaticTable
vlanStaticTable.description: Table for static VLAN configuration including VLAN aggregation support.

vlanStaticEntry.name: vlanStaticEntry
vlanStaticEntry.description: Static information for a VLAN configured on the device by (local or network) management.

vlanStaticIndex.name: vlanStaticIndex
vlanStaticIndex.description: The VLAN ID of the VLAN.

vlanStaticInterfaceType.name: vlanStaticInterfaceType
vlanStaticInterfaceType.description: The interface type of the VLAN (there is a subtype of IANAifType). l2vlan(135) refers to L2 interface and can't accept any L3 related configuration. l3ipvlan(136) refers to L3 interface and can accept L3 related configuration.

vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortTable.name: vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortTable
vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortTable.description: Table for port configuration to specify how to insert outer tag by matching customer VLAN ID.

vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortEntry.name: vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortEntry
vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration to specify how to insert outer tag by matching customer VLAN ID.

vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortIndex.name: vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortIndex
vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortIndex.description: The port interface of the vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortStatus.name: vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortStatus
vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortStatus.description: Sets to valid(1) to create an entry. Sets to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortAction.name: vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortAction
vlanDot1qTunnelSrvCvidPortAction.description: Sets to assignSvid(2) to assign service VLAN ID.

vlanMacAddrLearningTable.name: vlanMacAddrLearningTable
vlanMacAddrLearningTable.description: Table for VLAN MAC learning configuration.

vlanMacAddrLearningEntry.name: vlanMacAddrLearningEntry
vlanMacAddrLearningEntry.description: Entry for VLAN MAC learning configuration.

vlanMacAddrLearningIndex.name: vlanMacAddrLearningIndex
vlanMacAddrLearningIndex.description: The vlan id of the VLAN

vlanMacAddrLearningStatus.name: vlanMacAddrLearningStatus
vlanMacAddrLearningStatus.description: Set this variable to enabled(1) to start to learn MAC addresses. Set this variable to disabled(2) to stop to learn MAC addresses.

prioIpPrecDscpStatus.name: prioIpPrecDscpStatus
prioIpPrecDscpStatus.description: Selects whether no frame priority mapping, IP ToS precedence mapping or DSCP mapping is performed.

prioIpDscpTable.name: prioIpDscpTable
prioIpDscpTable.description: Table for IP DSCP priority mapping.

prioIpDscpEntry.name: prioIpDscpEntry
prioIpDscpEntry.description: Entry for IP DSCP priority mapping.

prioIpDscpPort.name: prioIpDscpPort
prioIpDscpPort.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

prioIpDscpValue.name: prioIpDscpValue
prioIpDscpValue.description: Value of IP DSCP as specified in the packet header.

prioIpDscpCos.name: prioIpDscpCos
prioIpDscpCos.description: Class of Service as defined by dot1dTrafficClassPriority in the P-BRIDGE-MIB. The prioIpDscpValue value in the same table row will be mapped to this Class of Service (CoS). This CoS is then further mapped to the hardware queue according to dot1dTrafficClassTable.

prioIpDscpRestoreDefault.name: prioIpDscpRestoreDefault
prioIpDscpRestoreDefault.description: Enables the IP DSCP settings of a port to be reset to their defaults. To reset the IP DSCP settings of a port, assign the value of the relevant ifIndex defined by the ifIndex in the IF-MIB. For example, assigning the value 1 will result in the IP DSCP settings of port 1 being restored to their default. 0 will always be obtained when reading this variable

prioCopyIpDscp.name: prioCopyIpDscp
prioCopyIpDscp.description: Action to copy IP DSCP settings from a source port to many destination ports. The first four octets represent an integer for the source port in high-to-low (big-endian) order. Starting from the 5th octet is the destination port list in a form described by PortList in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. Writing this object will perform copy. Reading this object will always get a zero-length octet string.

prioWrrTrafficClass.name: prioWrrTrafficClass
prioWrrTrafficClass.description: Traffic class for this entry, as defined in dot1dTrafficClass in the P-BRIDGE-MIB. The actual maximum depends on the hardware, and is equal to dot1dPortNumTrafficClasses-1.

prioQueueMode.name: prioQueueMode
prioQueueMode.description: The global status for the prioQueue. wrr(1),strict(2)

trapIpFilterRejectMode.name: trapIpFilterRejectMode
trapIpFilterRejectMode.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicated the ipfilter reject mode. web(1), snmp(2), telnet(3).

trapIpFilterRejectIp.name: trapIpFilterRejectIp
trapIpFilterRejectIp.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicating the IP address that rejected by the ipfilter.

trapVarLoginUserName.name: trapVarLoginUserName
trapVarLoginUserName.description: The name of the user who logs into the switch.

trapVarSessionType.name: trapVarSessionType
trapVarSessionType.description: The method by which the user logs in to control the switch.

trapVarLoginInetAddressType.name: trapVarLoginInetAddressType
trapVarLoginInetAddressType.description: The address type of the address associated with this agent. Only IPv4 and IPv6 types are supported.

trapVarLoginInetAddress.name: trapVarLoginInetAddress
trapVarLoginInetAddress.description: The IP address from which the user logs into the switch.

trapIpFilterRejectInetAddressType.name: trapIpFilterRejectInetAddressType
trapIpFilterRejectInetAddressType.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicating the IP address that was rejected by the IP filter.

trapIpFilterRejectInetAddress.name: trapIpFilterRejectInetAddress
trapIpFilterRejectInetAddress.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicating the IP address that was rejected by the IP filter.

trapAutoUpgradeResult.name: trapAutoUpgradeResult
trapAutoUpgradeResult.description: The parameter indicates which result triggers the trap.

trapAutoUpgradeNewVer.name: trapAutoUpgradeNewVer
trapAutoUpgradeNewVer.description: The parameter indicates new version which was upgraded to. When trapAutoUpgradeResult was failed(2), it would be null string.

trapPortSecurityIntrusionMac.name: trapPortSecurityIntrusionMac
trapPortSecurityIntrusionMac.description: This variable indicates the intrusion MAC address.

trapDhcpClientPortIfIndex.name: trapDhcpClientPortIfIndex
trapDhcpClientPortIfIndex.description: ifIndex for the port connected to DHCP rogue server.

trapDhcpServerIpAddress.name: trapDhcpServerIpAddress
trapDhcpServerIpAddress.description: The IP address of the rogue server.

trapSfpThresholdAlarmWarnIfIndex.name: trapSfpThresholdAlarmWarnIfIndex
trapSfpThresholdAlarmWarnIfIndex.description: ifIndex for the port issued alarm/warning trap.

trapDhcpServerMacAddress.name: trapDhcpServerMacAddress
trapDhcpServerMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the rogue server.

trapIfIndex.name: trapIfIndex
trapIfIndex.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicating the index of an interface.

trapVlanId.name: trapVlanId
trapVlanId.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicating the identifier of a VLAN.

trapUdldPortShutdownReason.name: trapUdldPortShutdownReason
trapUdldPortShutdownReason.description: This variable is for trap var binding, indicated the reason for the UDLD port shutdown. unidirectionalLink(1): unidirectional link detected, mismatchWithNeighbor(2): mismatch with neighbor state reported. transmitToReceiveLoop(3): transmit-to-receive loop detected. aggressiveModeFailure(4): aggressive mode failure detected.

trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoIpAddrType.name: trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoIpAddrType
trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoIpAddrType.description: The IP address type of the user who fails in SNMP authentication.

trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoIpAddr.name: trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoIpAddr
trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoIpAddr.description: The IP address of the user who fails in SNMP authentication.

trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoMacAddr.name: trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoMacAddr
trapVarSnmpAuthenInfoMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the user who fails in SNMP authentication.

rateLimitPortTable.name: rateLimitPortTable
rateLimitPortTable.description: Table for rate limit of each port.

rateLimitPortEntry.name: rateLimitPortEntry
rateLimitPortEntry.description: Entry for rate limit of each port.

rlPortIndex.name: rlPortIndex
rlPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (including trunk member) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

rlPortInputStatus.name: rlPortInputStatus
rlPortInputStatus.description: Whether input rate limit is enabled for this port.

rlPortOutputStatus.name: rlPortOutputStatus
rlPortOutputStatus.description: Whether output rate limit is enabled for this port.

rlPortInputLimitInKilo.name: rlPortInputLimitInKilo
rlPortInputLimitInKilo.description: Value of the input rate limit. Its unit is kilobits per second. For a 100 Mbps port, the range is 64 to 100000. For a 1000 Mbps port, the range is 64 to 1000000.

rlPortOutputLimitInKilo.name: rlPortOutputLimitInKilo
rlPortOutputLimitInKilo.description: Value of the output rate limit. Its unit is kilobits per second. For a 100 Mbps port, the range is 64 to 100000. For a 1000 Mbps port, the range is 64 to 1000000.

prioIfClassificationModeTable.name: prioIfClassificationModeTable
prioIfClassificationModeTable.description: Table for setting the interface Qos mapping classification mode.

prioIfClassificationModeEntry.name: prioIfClassificationModeEntry
prioIfClassificationModeEntry.description: Entry for setting the interface Qos mapping classification mode.

prioIfClassificationModeIf.name: prioIfClassificationModeIf
prioIfClassificationModeIf.description: The port or trunk interface of the device. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

prioIfClassificationModeStatus.name: prioIfClassificationModeStatus
prioIfClassificationModeStatus.description: The Qos mapping classification mode of the interface. cos mode means that the internal priority is mapped from priority field of packet's VLAN tag if a VLAN tag exists; IP precedence mode means that the internal priority is mapped from the IP precedence value of IP packets; DSCP mode means the internal priority is mapped from the dscp value of IP packets.

diffServPolicyMapIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapIndex
diffServPolicyMapIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in this table.

diffServPolicyMapElementIndexList.name: diffServPolicyMapElementIndexList
diffServPolicyMapElementIndexList.description: The octet string containes the diffServPolicyMapElementEntry indexes. Two octets express one index and it is represented in network order. This index list indicates the diffServPolicyMapEntrys which belong to this entry.

diffServPolicyMapStatus.name: diffServPolicyMapStatus
diffServPolicyMapStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row, or modify or delete an existing row, in this table. The status column has six defined values: The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device (see NOTE below); - 'notReady', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is missing information necessary in order to be available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndGo', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndWait', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row (but not make it available for use by the managed device); and, - 'destroy', which is supplied by a management station wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row. Whereas five of the six values (all except 'notReady') may be specified in a management protocol set operation, only three values will be returned in response to a management protocol retrieval operation: 'notReady', 'notInService' or 'active'. That is, when queried, an existing conceptual row has only three states: it is either available for use by the managed device (the status column has the value 'active');it is not available for use by the managed device, though the agent has sufficient information to make it so (the status column has the value 'notInService'); or, it is not available for use by the managed device, and an attempt to make it so would fail because the agent has insufficient information (the state column has the value 'notReady'). For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlIndex
diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlIndex.description: Index for attachment control. Specifies the policy map as the target to relate with the policy map element. The policy map identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServPolicyMapEntry as identified by the same value of diffServPolicyMapIndex.

diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlElementIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlElementIndex
diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlElementIndex.description: Element Index for attachment control.Specifies the policy map element to relate with the policy map. The policy map element identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServPolicyMapElementEntry as identified by the same value of diffServPolicyMapElementIndex.

diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlAction.name: diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlAction
diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlAction.description: Action for attachment control. When setting this object to attach(2) to begin the attaching operation, a particular policy map element is attached to a particular policy map. When setting this object to detach(3) to begin the not attached operation, a particular policy map element is not attached to a particular policy map. When the action is finshed or no action is taken, the value of this object is noAction(1). A particular policy map is specified in the diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlIndex. A particularpolicy map element is specified in the diffServPolicyMapAttachCtlElementIndex.

diffServPolicyMapElementIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapElementIndex
diffServPolicyMapElementIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in this table.

diffServPolicyMapElementClassMapIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapElementClassMapIndex
diffServPolicyMapElementClassMapIndex.description: Specifies the class map binding to this entry. The class map identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServClassMapEntry as identified by the same value of diffServClassMapIndex.

diffServPolicyMapElementMeterIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapElementMeterIndex
diffServPolicyMapElementMeterIndex.description: Specifies the meter binding to this entry. The meter identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServMeterEntry as identified by the same value of diffServMeterIndex. If this value is zero, no associated meter will be associated, as zero is not a valid meter index.

diffServPolicyMapElementActionIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapElementActionIndex
diffServPolicyMapElementActionIndex.description: Specifies the action binding to this entry. The action identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServActionEntry as identified by the same value of diffServActionIndex.

diffServPolicyMapElementStatus.name: diffServPolicyMapElementStatus

For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

diffServClassMapIndex.name: diffServClassMapIndex
diffServClassMapIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in this table.

diffServClassMapMatchType.name: diffServClassMapMatchType
diffServClassMapMatchType.description: The map match type of this entry.

diffServClassMapElementIndexTypeList.name: diffServClassMapElementIndexTypeList
diffServClassMapElementIndexTypeList.description: The octet string containes the type of class map element indexes. Two octets which are represented in network order express one type of the class map element index in network order and it maps the index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList in order. When the type is macAce(1), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServMacAceEntry. When the type is ipAce(2), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServIpAceEntry. When the type is acl(3), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServAclEntry. When the type is ipv6Ace(4), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServIpv6AceEntry.

diffServClassMapElementIndexList.name: diffServClassMapElementIndexList
diffServClassMapElementIndexList.description: The octet string containes the class map element indexes. Two octets express one index and it is represented in network order. This index list indicates the particular class map elements which belong to this table. The class map element uses type to indicate diffServAclEntry, the diffServIpAceEntry or diffServMacAceEntry. The type is two octet specified in differServClasssMapElementIndexTypeList in order. When the type is macAce(1), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServMacAceEntry. When the type is ipAce(2), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServIpAceEntry. When the type is acl(3), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServAclEntry. When type is ipv6Ace(4), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServIpv6AceEntry.

For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

diffServClassMapAttachCtlIndex.name: diffServClassMapAttachCtlIndex
diffServClassMapAttachCtlIndex.description: Index for attachment control. Specifies the class map as the target to relate with class map elements. The class map identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServClassMapEntry as identified by the same value of diffServClassMapIndex.

diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndexTyp.name: diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndexType
diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndexTyp.description: Element Index for attachment control. Specifies the type of class map element to relate with the class map. When type is macAce(1), the index of diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex is the index of diffServMacAceEntry. When the type is ipAce(2), the index of diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex is the index of diffServIpAceEntry. When the type is acl(3), the index of diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex is the index of diffServAclEntry. When type is ipv6Ace(4), the index of diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex is the index of diffServIpv6AceEntry.

diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex.name: diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex
diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex.description: Element Index for attachment control. Specifies the class map element related with the class map. The class map element uses type to indicate diffServAclEntry, the diffServIpAceEntry or diffServMacAceEntry. The type is specified in diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndexType. When the type is macAce(1), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServMacAceEntry. When the type is ipAce(2), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServIpAceEntry. When the type is acl(3), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServAclEntry. When type is ipv6Ace(4), the maping index of differServClasssMapElementIndexList is the diffServIpv6AceEntry.

diffServClassMapAttachCtlAction.name: diffServClassMapAttachCtlAction
diffServClassMapAttachCtlAction.description: Action for attachment control. When setting this object to attach(2) to begin the attaching operation, a particular class map element is attached to a particular class map. When setting this object to detach(3) to begin the not attached operation, then a particular class map element is not attached to a particular class map. When the action is finshed whether successfully or not, or no action is taken, the value of this object always is noAction(1). The value of a particular class map is specified in the AclAttachCtlTargetIndex. The class map element is specified by diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndexType and diffServClassMapAttachCtlElementIndex.

diffServAclIndex.name: diffServAclIndex
diffServAclIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the ACL table.

diffServAclType.name: diffServAclType
diffServAclType.description: The type of this entry. When the value of ACL type is modified, then the ACEs in the diffServAclAceIndexList of this entry will be auto-removed, and this entry will be auto- unbound from the diffServPortTable and the diffServClassMapTable.

diffServAclAceIndexList.name: diffServAclAceIndexList
diffServAclAceIndexList.description: The octet string containes the ACE indexes. Two octets express one index and it is represented in network order. This index list indicates the particular ACEs which belong to this table. The ACE uses type to indicate the diffServMacAceEntry, the diffServIpAceEntry, the diffServIpv6AceEntry or the diffServArpAceEntry. The type is specified in diffServAclType. When the type is mac(1), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServMacAceEntry. When the type is ipstandard(2) or ipextended(3), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServIpAceEntry. When the type is ipv6standard(4) or ipv6extended(5), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServIpv6AceEntry. When the type is arp(6), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServArpAceEntry.

diffServAclStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

diffServAclAttachCtlIndex.name: diffServAclAttachCtlIndex
diffServAclAttachCtlIndex.description: Index for attachment control. Specifies the ACL as the target to relate with the IP ACE, the MAC ACE or IPv6 ACE. The ACL identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same diffServAclEntry as identified by the same value of diffServAclIndex.

diffServAclAttachCtlAceType.name: diffServAclAttachCtlAceType
diffServAclAttachCtlAceType.description: Type for attachment control. Specifies the type of diffServAclAttachCtlAceIndex to relate with the diffServAclAttachCtlIndex. When the type is macAce(1), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServMacAceEntry. When the type is ipAce(2), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServIpAceEntry. When the type is ipv6Ace(3), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServIpv6AceEntry. When the type is arpAce(4), the index of diffServAclAceIndexList is the diffServArpAceEntry.

diffServAclAttachCtlAceIndex.name: diffServAclAttachCtlAceIndex
diffServAclAttachCtlAceIndex.description: Index for attachment control. Specifies the ACE to relate with the diffServAclAttachCtlIndex. When diffServAclAttachCtlAceType is macAce(1), the value of diffServAclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServMacAceEntry. When diffServAclAttachCtlAceType is ipAce(2), the value of diffServAclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServIpAceEntry. When diffServAclAttachCtlAceType is ipv6Ace(3), the value of diffServAclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServIpv6AceEntry. When diffServAclAttachCtlAceType is arpAce(4), the value of diffServAclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServArpAceEntry.

diffServAclAttachCtlAction.name: diffServAclAttachCtlAction
diffServAclAttachCtlAction.description: Action for attachment control. When setting this object to attach(2) to begin the attaching operation, a particular ACE is attached to a particular ACL. When setting this object to detach(3) to begin the not attached operation, then a particular ACE is not attached to a particular ACL. When the action is finshed whether successfully or not, or no action is taken, the value of this object always is noAction(1), The value of a particular ACL is specified in the diffServAclAttachCtlAceType and diffServAclAttachCtlAceIndex.

diffServIpAceIndex.name: diffServIpAceIndex
diffServIpAceIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the IP ACE table.

diffServIpAceType.name: diffServIpAceType
diffServIpAceType.description: The specified IP ACE type. When the type of this entry is modified, then this entry will be auto-unbound from the diffServAclEntry and the not supporting field of this entry will be set 0.

diffServIpAceAccess.name: diffServIpAceAccess
diffServIpAceAccess.description: Indicates the action to be taken if a packet matches this ACE.

diffServIpAceSourceIpAddr.name: diffServIpAceSourceIpAddr
diffServIpAceSourceIpAddr.description: The specified source IP address. The packet's source address is AND-ed with the value of IpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServIpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask.name: diffServIpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask
diffServIpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask.description: The specified source IP address mask. The packet's source address is AND-ed with the value of IpAceSourceIpAddr and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServIpAceDestIpAddr.name: diffServIpAceDestIpAddr
diffServIpAceDestIpAddr.description: The specified destination IP address. The packet's destination address is AND-ed with the value of diffServIpAceDestIpAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceDestIpAddrBitmask.name: diffServIpAceDestIpAddrBitmask
diffServIpAceDestIpAddrBitmask.description: The specified destination IP address mask. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceProtocol.name: diffServIpAceProtocol
diffServIpAceProtocol.description: The protocol number field in the IP header used to indicate the higher layer protocol as specified in RFC 1700. A value of 0 matches every IP packet. The object=256 means 'any'. For example: 0 is IP, 1 is ICMP, 2 is IGMP, 4 is IP in IP encapsulation, 6 is TCP, 9 is IGRP, 17 is UDP, 47 is GRE, 50 is ESP, 51 is AH, 88 is IGRP, 89 is OSPF, 94 is KA9Q/NOS compatible IP over IP, 103 is PIMv2, 108 is PCP. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAcePrec.name: diffServIpAcePrec
diffServIpAcePrec.description: Specifies the IP precedence value to match against. The value of this object is ignored whenever the value of diffServIpAcePrec object is 8. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceTos.name: diffServIpAceTos
diffServIpAceTos.description: Specifies the IP ToS facility value to match against. The value of this object is ignored whenever the value of diffServIpAcePrec object is 9. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceDscp.name: diffServIpAceDscp
diffServIpAceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value to match against. The value of this object is ignored whenever the value of diffServIpAcePrec object is 64. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceSourcePortOp.name: diffServIpAceSourcePortOp
diffServIpAceSourcePortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's source TCP/UDP port number is to be compared. noOperator(1), which is the default value, means no comparison is to be made with the source TCP/UDP port number. equal(2), which is used the diffServIpAceSourcePortBitmask and the diffServIpAceMinSourcePort to match against. range(3),which is used the diffServIpAceMinSourcePort and the diffServIpAceMaxSourcePort to match against. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceMinSourcePort.name: diffServIpAceMinSourcePort
diffServIpAceMinSourcePort.description: If the diffServIpAceSourcePortOp is range(3), this indicates the lower bound of the TCP/UDP port number value range. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceSourcePortBitmask.name: diffServIpAceSourcePortBitmask
diffServIpAceSourcePortBitmask.description: If the diffServIpAceSourcePortOp is equal(2), this indicates the bitmask of the diffServIpAceMinSourcePort. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceDestPortOp.name: diffServIpAceDestPortOp
diffServIpAceDestPortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's destination TCP/UDP port number is to be compared. noOperator(1), which is the default value, means that no comparison is to be made with the destination TCP/UDP port number. equal(2), which is used the diffServIpAceSourcePortBitmask and the diffServIpAceMinDestPort to match against. range(3),which is used the diffServIpAceMinDestPort and the diffServIpAceMaxDestPort to match against. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceMinDestPort.name: diffServIpAceMinDestPort
diffServIpAceMinDestPort.description: If the diffServIpAceDestPortOp is range(3), this indicates the lower bound of the TCP/UDP port number value range. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceDestPortBitmask.name: diffServIpAceDestPortBitmask
diffServIpAceDestPortBitmask.description: If the diffServIpAceDestPortOp is equal(2), this indicates the bitmask of the diffServIpAceMinDestPort. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceControlCode.name: diffServIpAceControlCode
diffServIpAceControlCode.description: Indicates how the control flags of TCP packets are to be compared. diffServIpAceControlCode is AND-ed with diffServIpAceControlCodeBitmask. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpAceControlCodeBitmask.name: diffServIpAceControlCodeBitmask
diffServIpAceControlCodeBitmask.description: Indicates how the control flags of TCP packets are to be compared. It can be used to check multiple flags of the FIN, SYN, RST, PSH, ACK, URG by the sum of FIN=1, SYN=2, RST=4, PSH=8, ACK=16, URG=32. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpAceType object is equal to standard(1).

For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

diffServMacAceIndex.name: diffServMacAceIndex
diffServMacAceIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the MAC ACE table.

diffServMacAceAccess.name: diffServMacAceAccess
diffServMacAceAccess.description: Indicates the action to be taken if a packet matches this ACE.

diffServMacAcePktformat.name: diffServMacAcePktformat
diffServMacAcePktformat.description: Used to check the packet format of the packets. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServMacAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServMacAceSourceMacAddr.name: diffServMacAceSourceMacAddr
diffServMacAceSourceMacAddr.description: Indicates the 48-bit source MAC address. The specified source MAC of the packet. The packet's source MAC address is AND-ed with the value of diffServMacAceSourceMacAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServMacAceSourceMacAddrBitmask.name: diffServMacAceSourceMacAddrBitmask
diffServMacAceSourceMacAddrBitmask.description: The specified source MAC address mask.

diffServMacAceDestMacAddr.name: diffServMacAceDestMacAddr
diffServMacAceDestMacAddr.description: Indicates the 48-bit destination MAC address. The specified destination MAC of the packet. The packet's destination MAC address is AND-ed with the value of diffServMacAceDestMacAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServMacAceDestMacAddrBitmask.name: diffServMacAceDestMacAddrBitmask
diffServMacAceDestMacAddrBitmask.description: The specified destination MAC address mask.

diffServMacAceVidOp.name: diffServMacAceVidOp
diffServMacAceVidOp.description: Indicates how a packet's VID is to be compared. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServMacAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServMacAceMinVid.name: diffServMacAceMinVid
diffServMacAceMinVid.description: Indicates the lower bound of the VID value range if the diffServMacAceVidOp is range(3).

diffServMacAceVidBitmask.name: diffServMacAceVidBitmask
diffServMacAceVidBitmask.description: The bit mask of the VID. The default value is 0.

diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp.name: diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp
diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp.description: Indicates how a packet's ether type is to be compared.

diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask.name: diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask
diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask.description: The bit mask of Ether type. The default value is 0.

diffServMacAceMinEtherType.name: diffServMacAceMinEtherType
diffServMacAceMinEtherType.description: Indicates the lower bound of the ether type value range if the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is range(3).

diffServMacAceStatus.name: diffServMacAceStatus
diffServMacAceStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. The status column has six defined values: The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device (see NOTE below); - 'notReady', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is missing information necessary in order to be available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndGo', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndWait', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row (but not make it available for use by the managed device); and, - 'destroy', which is supplied by a management station wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row. diffServMacAceCosOp.name: diffServMacAceCosOp
diffServMacAceCosOp.description: Indicates how a packet's CoS is compared. If the object type of diffServMacAceCosOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceMinCos indicates the CoS value for comparing, and diffServMacAceCosBitmask is used as the bitmask of the CoS value. If the object type of diffServMacAceCosOp is range(3), diffServMacAceMinCos should be used as the lower bound of the CoS value.

diffServMacAceCosBitmask.name: diffServMacAceCosBitmask
diffServMacAceCosBitmask.description: Indicates the bitmask of the CoS value if the object type of diffServMacAceCosOp is equal(2). The default value is 0.

diffServMacAceMinCos.name: diffServMacAceMinCos
diffServMacAceMinCos.description: If the object type of diffServMacAceCosOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceMinCos indicates the CoS value for comparing. If the object type of diffServMacAceCosOp is range(3), diffServMacAceMinCos indicates the lower bound of the CoS value.

diffServMacAceSourceIpAddr.name: diffServMacAceSourceIpAddr
diffServMacAceSourceIpAddr.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '0800'h, this specified source IP address. The packet's source address is AND-ed with the value of diffServMacAceSourceIpAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServMacAceSourceIpAddrBitmask.name: diffServMacAceSourceIpAddrBitmask
diffServMacAceSourceIpAddrBitmask.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '0800'h, this specified source IP address mask. The packet's source address is AND-ed with the value of diffServMacAceSourceIpAddr and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServMacAceDestIpAddr.name: diffServMacAceDestIpAddr
diffServMacAceDestIpAddr.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '0800'h, this specified destination IP address. The packet's destination address is AND-ed with the value of diffServMacAceDestIpAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServMacAceDestIpAddrBitmask.name: diffServMacAceDestIpAddrBitmask
diffServMacAceDestIpAddrBitmask.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '0800'h, this specified destination IP address mask. The packet's source address is AND-ed with the value of diffServMacAceDestIpAddr and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServMacAceSourceIpv6Addr.name: diffServMacAceSourceIpv6Addr
diffServMacAceSourceIpv6Addr.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '86DD'h, this specifies the source IPv6 address.

diffServMacAceSourceIpv6AddrPrefixLen.name: diffServMacAceSourceIpv6AddrPrefixLen
diffServMacAceSourceIpv6AddrPrefixLen.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '86DD'h, this specifies the length (in bits) associated with the source IPv6 address prefix of this entry.

diffServMacAceDestIpv6Addr.name: diffServMacAceDestIpv6Addr
diffServMacAceDestIpv6Addr.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '86DD'h, this specifies the destination IPv6 address. This object may not be modified if the associated aclIpv6AceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServMacAceDestIpv6AddrPrefixLen.name: diffServMacAceDestIpv6AddrPrefixLen
diffServMacAceDestIpv6AddrPrefixLen.description: If the diffServMacAceEtherTypeOp is equal(2), diffServMacAceEtherTypeBitmask is 'FFFF'h, and diffServMacAceMinEtherType is '86DD'h, this specifies the length (in bits) associated with the destination IPv6 address prefix of this entry.

diffServMacAceIpProtocol.name: diffServMacAceIpProtocol
diffServMacAceIpProtocol.description: The protocol number field in the IP header (or the next header field in the IPv6 header) used to indicate the higher layer protocol as specified in RFC 1700. A value of 0 matches every IP packet. The object=256 means 'any'. For example: 0 is IP, 1 is ICMP, 2 is IGMP, 4 is IP in IP encapsulation, 6 is TCP, 9 is IGRP, 17 is UDP, 47 is GRE, 50 is ESP, 51 is AH, 88 is IGRP, 89 is OSPF, 94 is KA9Q/NOS compatible IP over IP, 103 is PIMv2, 108 is PCP. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServMacAceMinEtherType object is not equal to '0800'h or '86DD'h.

diffServMacAceL4SourcePortOp.name: diffServMacAceL4SourcePortOp
diffServMacAceL4SourcePortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's L4 source port is compared.

diffServMacAceL4SourcePort.name: diffServMacAceL4SourcePort
diffServMacAceL4SourcePort.description: If the object type of diffServMacAceL4SourcePortOp is equal(2), this indicates the l4 source port value for comparing.

diffServMacAceL4SourcePortBitmask.name: diffServMacAceL4SourcePortBitmask
diffServMacAceL4SourcePortBitmask.description: If the object type of diffServMacAceL4SourcePortOp is equal(2), this indicates the bitmask for diffServMacAceL4SourcePort

diffServMacAceL4DestPortOp.name: diffServMacAceL4DestPortOp
diffServMacAceL4DestPortOp.description: Indicates how a packet's L4 destination port is compared.

diffServMacAceL4DestPort.name: diffServMacAceL4DestPort
diffServMacAceL4DestPort.description: If the object type of diffServMacAceL4DestPortOp is equal(2), this indicates the l4 destination port value for comparing.

diffServMacAceL4DestPortBitmask.name: diffServMacAceL4DestPortBitmask
diffServMacAceL4DestPortBitmask.description: If the object type of diffServMacAceL4SourcePortOp is equal(2), this indicates the bitmask for diffServMacAceL4DestPort

diffServActionIndex.name: diffServActionIndex
diffServActionIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the action table.

diffServActionList.name: diffServActionList
diffServActionList.description: The bitmap value used to identify which action capabilities are enabled on the entry. The actionPktNewPri and actionPktNewDscp can not be enabled at the same time on the entry. The actionRedPktNewDscp and actionRedDrop can not be enabled at the same time on the entry.

diffServActionPktNewPri.name: diffServActionPktNewPri
diffServActionPktNewPri.description: Specifies the new priority value for the packet when the action is satisfied. If the actionPktNewPri bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServActionPktNewPhb.name: diffServActionPktNewPhb
diffServActionPktNewPhb.description: Specifies the inner priority value for the packet when the action is satisfied. If the actionPktNewPhb bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServActionGreenPktTransmit.name: diffServActionGreenPktTransmit
diffServActionGreenPktTransmit.description: The actionGreenPktTransmit bit of the diffServActionList is for configuring this object. If the value of this object is enabled, the green marking packet will be Transmitted.

diffServActionGreenPktNewDscp.name: diffServActionGreenPktNewDscp
diffServActionGreenPktNewDscp.description: Specifies the new DSCP value for the packet when the action is satisfied. The value of this object is ignored whenever the value of diffServActionGreenPktNewDscp object is 64. If the actionGreenPktNewDscp bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServActionYellowPktNewDscp.name: diffServActionYellowPktNewDscp
diffServActionYellowPktNewDscp.description: Specifies the new DSCP value for the packet when the action is satisfied. The value of this object is ignored whenever the value of diffServActionYellowPktNewDscp object is 64. If the actionYellowPktNewDscp bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServActionYellowPktDrop.name: diffServActionYellowPktDrop
diffServActionYellowPktDrop.description: The actionYellowPktDrop bit of the diffServActionList is for configuring this object. If the value of this object is enabled, the red marking packet will be dropped.

diffServActionRedPktNewDscp.name: diffServActionRedPktNewDscp
diffServActionRedPktNewDscp.description: Specifies the new DSCP value for the red marking packet when the action is satisfied. The value of this object is ignored whenever the value of diffServActionRedPktNewDscp object is 64. If the actionRedPktNewDscp bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServActionRedPktDrop.name: diffServActionRedPktDrop
diffServActionRedPktDrop.description: The actionRedPktDrop bit of the diffServActionList is for configuring this object. If the value of this object is enabled, the red marking packet will be dropped.

diffServActionPktNewIpPrec.description: Specifies the new precedence value for the packet when the action is satisfied. If the actionPktNewIpPrec bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServActionPktNewDscp.name: diffServActionPktNewDscp
diffServActionPktNewDscp.description: Specifies the new DSCP value for the packet when the action is satisfied. If the actionPktNewDscp bit of the diffServActionList is not enabled, this object can not be set.

diffServMeterIndex.name: diffServMeterIndex
diffServMeterIndex.description: An entry that describes a single set of token bucket parameters.

diffServMeterModel.name: diffServMeterModel
diffServMeterModel.description: The Metering algorithm associated with the Token Bucket parameters. The zeroDotZero indicates this is unknown.

diffServMeterRate.name: diffServMeterRate
diffServMeterRate.description: The token-bucket rate, in kilobits per second (kbps).

diffServMeterBurstSize.name: diffServMeterBurstSize
diffServMeterBurstSize.description: The maximum number of bytes in a single transmission burst.

diffServMeterPeakRate.name: diffServMeterPeakRate
diffServMeterPeakRate.description: The token-bucket rate, in kilobits per second (kbps).

diffServMeterPeakBurstSize.name: diffServMeterPeakBurstSize
diffServMeterPeakBurstSize.description: The maximum number of bytes in a double transmission burst.

diffServIpv6AceIndex.name: diffServIpv6AceIndex
diffServIpv6AceIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the IPv6 table.

diffServIpv6AceType.name: diffServIpv6AceType
diffServIpv6AceType.description: The specified IP v6 ACE type. When the type of this entry is modified, then this entry will be auto-unbound from the diffServAclEntry and the not supporting field of this entry will be set 0.

diffServIpv6AceAccess.name: diffServIpv6AceAccess
diffServIpv6AceAccess.description: Indicates the action to be taken if a packet matches this ACE.

diffServIpv6AceSourceIpAddrPrefixLen.name: diffServIpv6AceSourceIpAddrPrefixLen
diffServIpv6AceSourceIpAddrPrefixLen.description: The length (in bits) associated with the source IPv6 address prefix of this entry.

diffServIpv6AceDestIpAddr.name: diffServIpv6AceDestIpAddr
diffServIpv6AceDestIpAddr.description: Specifies the destination IPv6 address. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpv6AceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpv6AceDestIpAddrPrefixLen.name: diffServIpv6AceDestIpAddrPrefixLen
diffServIpv6AceDestIpAddrPrefixLen.description: The length (in bits) associated with the destination IPv6 address prefix of this entry. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpv6AceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServIpv6AceDscp.name: diffServIpv6AceDscp
diffServIpv6AceDscp.description: Specifies the DSCP value to match against. This object may not be modified if the associated diffServIpv6AceType object is equal to standard(1).

diffServArpAceTable.name: diffServArpAceTable
diffServArpAceTable.description: The conceptual table of all of diffServArpAceEntry.

diffServArpAceIndex.name: diffServArpAceIndex
diffServArpAceIndex.description: The unique index of an ACE within an ACL.

diffServArpAceAction.name: diffServArpAceAction
diffServArpAceAction.description: Indicates the action to be taken if a packet matches this ACE. This object cannot not be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServArpAcePktType.name: diffServArpAcePktType
diffServArpAcePktType.description: Indicates the packet type to be taken if a packet matches this ACE. This object can not be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServArpAceSourceIpAddr.name: diffServArpAceSourceIpAddr
diffServArpAceSourceIpAddr.description: The specified source ARP address. The packet's source address is AND'ed with the value of diffServArpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServArpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask.name: diffServArpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask
diffServArpAceSourceIpAddrBitmask.description: The specified source ARP address mask. The packet's destination address is AND'ed with the value of diffServArpAceSourceIpAddr and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServArpAceDestIpAddr.name: diffServArpAceDestIpAddr
diffServArpAceDestIpAddr.description: The specified destination IP address. The packet's destination address is AND'ed with the value of diffServArpAceDestIpAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object.

diffServArpAceDestIpAddrBitmask.name: diffServArpAceDestIpAddrBitmask
diffServArpAceDestIpAddrBitmask.description: The specified destination IP address mask.

diffServArpAceSourceMacAddr.name: diffServArpAceSourceMacAddr
diffServArpAceSourceMacAddr.description: Indicates the 48-bit destination MAC address. The specified source MAC of the packet. The packet's source MAC address is AND'ed with the value of aceArpSourceMacAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServArpAceSourceMacAddrBitmask.name: diffServArpAceSourceMacAddrBitmask
diffServArpAceSourceMacAddrBitmask.description: The specified source MAC address mask. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServArpAceDestMacAddr.name: diffServArpAceDestMacAddr
diffServArpAceDestMacAddr.description: Indicates the 48-bit destination MAC address. The specified destination MAC of the packet. The packet's destination MAC address is AND'ed with the value of aceArpDestMacAddrBitmask and then compared against the value of this object. diffServArpAceDestMacAddrBitmask.name: diffServArpAceDestMacAddrBitmask
diffServArpAceDestMacAddrBitmask.description: The specified destination MAC address mask. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).

diffServArpAceLogStatus.name: diffServArpAceLogStatus
diffServArpAceLogStatus.description: Indicates whether to log messages against the packets. This object cannot be configured when the status of the entry, diffServArpAceStatus, is active(1).
