diffServArpTable.name: diffServArpTable
diffServArpTable.description: The conceptual table of all of diffServArpEntry.

diffServArpAclName.name: diffServArpAclName
diffServArpAclName.description: The name of an ACL. Within a feature, a unique name is used to identify the list to which the entry belongs in the device.

diffServAclHwCounterTable.name: diffServAclHwCounterTable
diffServAclHwCounterTable.description: Table for differentiated services hardware counter on each port.

diffServAclHwCounterEntry.name: diffServAclHwCounterEntry
diffServAclHwCounterEntry.description: Entry for differentiated services hardware counter on each port.

diffServAclHwCounterIfIndex.name: diffServAclHwCounterIfIndex
diffServAclHwCounterIfIndex.description: This object is the interface index of diffServPortEntry. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

diffServAclHwCounterDirection.name: diffServAclHwCounterDirection
diffServAclHwCounterDirection.description: Indicates a particular direction of traffic.

diffServAclHwCounterAclIndex.name: diffServAclHwCounterAclIndex
diffServAclHwCounterAclIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the ACL table.

diffServAclHwCounterAceIndex.name: diffServAclHwCounterAceIndex
diffServAclHwCounterAceIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry of an ACL. This entry might be a compressed ACE (which index is bigger than SYS_ADPT_MAX_NBRS_OF_ACE_OF_SYSTEM) with multiple user configured ACEs, and the index of compressed ACE will not show in ACE table.

diffServAclHwCounterAceHitCount.name: diffServAclHwCounterAceHitCount
diffServAclHwCounterAceHitCount.description: Specifies the hardware counter of an ACE entry.

diffServPolicyMapPortTable.name: diffServPolicyMapPortTable
diffServPolicyMapPortTable.description: Table for policy map of each port.

diffServPolicyMapPortIfIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapPortIfIndex
diffServPolicyMapPortIfIndex.description: This object is the interface index of DiffServPolicyMapPortEntry. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

diffServPolicyMapPortDirection.name: diffServPolicyMapPortDirection
diffServPolicyMapPortDirection.description: Indicates this policy map effect to which direction of traffic.

diffServPolicyMapPortPolicyMapIndex.name: diffServPolicyMapPortPolicyMapIndex
diffServPolicyMapPortPolicyMapIndex.description: Specifies the policy map index binded to the interface. The policy map identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same DiffServPolicyMapEntry as identified by the same value of diffServPolicyMapIndex.

diffServAccessGroupTable.name: diffServAccessGroupTable
diffServAccessGroupTable.description: Table for specifies access group for ACL on each port.

diffServAccessGroupIfIndex.name: diffServAccessGroupIfIndex
diffServAccessGroupIfIndex.description: This object is the interface index of diffServAccessGroupEntry. diffServAccessGroupDirection.name: diffServAccessGroupDirection
diffServAccessGroupDirection.description: Indicates this access group effect to which direction of traffic.

diffServAccessGroupType.name: diffServAccessGroupType
diffServAccessGroupType.description: Specifies the access group type, only support bind one ACL on a port.

diffServAccessGroupAclIndex.name: diffServAccessGroupAclIndex
diffServAccessGroupAclIndex.description: Specifies the ACL index apply to this access group. The index uniquely identifies an entry in diffServAclTable.

diffServAccessGroupTimeRangeName.name: diffServAccessGroupTimeRangeName
diffServAccessGroupTimeRangeName.description: The name of the time range entry bound to the access group. This object should be equal to one of the timeRangeName objects in timeRangeTable.

diffServAccessGroupCounterStatus.name: diffServAccessGroupCounterStatus
diffServAccessGroupCounterStatus.description: The acl counter enable status of this access group.

diffServAccessGroupStatus.name: diffServAccessGroupStatus
diffServAccessGroupStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.The status column has six defined values: The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device (see NOTE below); - 'notReady', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is missing information necessary in order to be available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndGo', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndWait', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row (but not make it available for use by the managed device); and, - 'destroy', which is supplied by a management station wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row. Whereas five of the six values (all except 'notReady') may be specified in a management protocol set operation, only three values will be returned in response to a management protocol retrieval operation: 'notReady', 'notInService' or 'active'. That is, when queried, an existing conceptual row has only three states: it is either available for use by the managed device (the status column has value 'active'); it is not available for use by the managed device, though the agent has sufficient information to make it so (the status column has value 'notInService'); or, it is not available for use by the managed device, and an attempt to make it so would fail because the agent has insufficient information (the state column has value 'notReady'). For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB.

diffServTcamTable.name: diffServTcamTable
diffServTcamTable.description: The conceptual table of all of DiffServTcamEntry.

diffServTcamUnit.name: diffServTcamUnit
diffServTcamUnit.description: This object identifies the switch within the system for which this entry contains information.

diffServTcamDevice.name: diffServTcamDevice
diffServTcamDevice.description: The device id of the specified unit.

diffServTcamPool.name: diffServTcamPool
diffServTcamPool.description: The TCAM pool index of the specified unit and device.

diffServTcamPoolCapability.name: diffServTcamPoolCapability
diffServTcamPoolCapability.description: The bitmap value used to identify which functions supported on this pool.

diffServTcamTotal.name: diffServTcamTotal
diffServTcamTotal.description: The total number of TCAM pool entry.

diffServTcamFree.name: diffServTcamFree
diffServTcamFree.description: The free number of TCAM pool entry.

diffServTcamUsed.name: diffServTcamUsed
diffServTcamUsed.description: The used number of TCAM pool entry.

prioGlobalCosToDscpTable.name: prioGlobalCosToDscpTable
prioGlobalCosToDscpTable.description: Table for CoS/CFI to internal QoS label mapping.

prioGlobalCosToDscpEntry.name: prioGlobalCosToDscpEntry
prioGlobalCosToDscpEntry.description: Entry for CoS/CFI to internal QoS label mapping.

prioGlobalCosToDscpCosValue.name: prioGlobalCosToDscpCosValue
prioGlobalCosToDscpCosValue.description: The CoS value (0 to 7) mapped to an internal QoS label value which is composed of PHB (3 bits) and drop precedence (2 bits).

prioGlobalCosToDscpCFIValue.name: prioGlobalCosToDscpCFIValue
prioGlobalCosToDscpCFIValue.description: The CFI value (0 or 1) mapped to an internal QoS label value which is composed of PHB (3 bits) and drop precedence (2 bits).

prioGlobalCosToDscpPhbValue.name: prioGlobalCosToDscpPhbValue
prioGlobalCosToDscpPhbValue.description: The PHB value of internal QoS label.

prioGlobalCosToDscpColorValue.name: prioGlobalCosToDscpColorValue
prioGlobalCosToDscpColorValue.description: The drop precedence value of internal QoS label. Green(0), Yellow(3), Red(1).

prioGlobalDscpToDscpTable.name: prioGlobalDscpToDscpTable
prioGlobalDscpToDscpTable.description: Table for DSCP to internal QoS label mapping. This table setting will take effect only when the interface Qos mapping classification mode is set to DSCP mode.

prioGlobalDscpToDscpEntry.name: prioGlobalDscpToDscpEntry
prioGlobalDscpToDscpEntry.description: Entry for ingress DSCP to internal QoS label mapping.

prioGlobalDscpToDscpIngressDscpValue.name: prioGlobalDscpToDscpIngressDscpValue
prioGlobalDscpToDscpIngressDscpValue.description: The ingress DSCP value which will be mapped to internal QoS label value.

prioGlobalDscpToDscpPhbValue.name: prioGlobalDscpToDscpPhbValue
prioGlobalDscpToDscpPhbValue.description: The PHB value of internal QoS label.

prioGlobalDscpToDscpColorValue.name: prioGlobalDscpToDscpColorValue
prioGlobalDscpToDscpColorValue.description: The drop precedence value of internal QoS label. Green(0), Yellow(3), Red(1).

prioGlobalDscpToQueueTable.name: prioGlobalDscpToQueueTable
prioGlobalDscpToQueueTable.description: Table for PHB to queue mapping.

prioGlobalDscpToQueueEntry.name: prioGlobalDscpToQueueEntry
prioGlobalDscpToQueueEntry.description: Entry for PHB to queue mapping.

prioGlobalDscpToQueuePHBValue.name: prioGlobalDscpToQueuePHBValue
prioGlobalDscpToQueuePHBValue.description: The PHB value of internal QoS label.

prioGlobalDscpToQueueQueueValue.name: prioGlobalDscpToQueueQueueValue
prioGlobalDscpToQueueQueueValue.description: The queue value which is mapped from the PHB value of QoS label.

privateVlanStatus.name: privateVlanStatus
privateVlanStatus.description: This controls whether private VLAN is enabled.

privateVlanUplinkPorts.name: privateVlanUplinkPorts
privateVlanUplinkPorts.description: This is the list of uplink ports for private VLAN. They should not overlap with privateVlanDownlinkPorts. 0 will be displayed if the privateVlanStatus is disabled. You must enable the privateVlanStatus before setting this variable.

privateVlanDownlinkPorts.name: privateVlanDownlinkPorts
privateVlanDownlinkPorts.description: This is the list of downlink ports for private VLAN. They should not overlap with privateVlanUplinkPorts. Multiple port setting is permitted. 0 will be displayed if the privateVlanStatus is disabled. You must enable the privateVlanStatus before setting this variable.

privateVlanVlanTable.name: privateVlanVlanTable
privateVlanVlanTable.description: A table containing private VLAN information on the VLANs which currently exist.

privateVlanVlanEntry.name: privateVlanVlanEntry
privateVlanVlanEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the private VLAN information on the VLANs for a particular management domain.

privateVlanVlanIndex.name: privateVlanVlanIndex
privateVlanVlanIndex.description: The VLAN ID of this private VLAN.

privateVlanVlanType.name: privateVlanVlanType
privateVlanVlanType.description: The VLAN type as defined for Private VLAN feature. Set the value to invalid(1) to destroy an entry. Set other values to create an entry. If an index already exists, set others to modifiy it. Note that a VLAN's private VLAN type cannot be changed once it has any port members.

privateVlanAssoicatedPrimaryVlan.name: privateVlanAssoicatedPrimaryVlan
privateVlanAssoicatedPrimaryVlan.description: The VLAN ID of the associated primary VLAN used for the private VLAN feature if privateVlanVlanType has the value of isolated(3), community(4). If privateVlanVlanType has the value of primary(2), then this object has the value of 0. Note that one isolated VLAN can only be associated with one unique primary VLAN. One primary VLAN can only be associated with one isolated VLAN. One primary VLAN can be associated with multiple community VLANs; one community VLAN can only be associated with one unique primary VLAN.

privateVlanPrivatePortTable.name: privateVlanPrivatePortTable
privateVlanPrivatePortTable.description: A table containing information on the configuration of secondary VLANs on the device ports.

privateVlanPrivatePortEntry.name: privateVlanPrivatePortEntry
privateVlanPrivatePortEntry.description: A conceptual row containing information of the configuration of secondary VLANs for each port. An entry is created by the managed system for each interface which can be configured as a private port for Private VLAN feature.

privateVlanPrivatePortIfIndex.name: privateVlanPrivatePortIfIndex
privateVlanPrivatePortIfIndex.description: This is defined as the ifIndex.

privateVlanPrivatePortSecondaryVlan.name: privateVlanPrivatePortSecondaryVlan
privateVlanPrivatePortSecondaryVlan.description: The VLAN ID of the secondary VLAN configured on this private port. A private port is a port that allows ingress traffic of the secondary VLAN as well as egress traffic of its associated primary VLAN, but blocks the egress traffic of the isolated VLAN while allowing the egress traffic of the community or twoWayCommunity VLAN depending on the type of the secondary VLAN. Note that a port can join a secondary VLAN only after this secondary VLAN has been associated with a primary VLAN, i.e., the cpvlanVlanAssociatedPrimaryVlan has a non-zero value. The default value of 0 for this object means this port has not yet joined a secondary VLAN.

privateVlanPromPortTable.name: privateVlanPromPortTable
privateVlanPromPortTable.description: A table containing secondary VLAN to primary VLAN remapping information on ports of the device.

privateVlanPromPortEntry.name: privateVlanPromPortEntry
privateVlanPromPortEntry.description: A conceptual row containing secondary VLAN to primary VLAN remapping information for each port. An entry is created by the managed system for each interface which can be configured as a promiscuous port for the private VLAN feature.

privateVlanPromPortPrimaryVlanId.name: privateVlanPromPortPrimaryVlanId
privateVlanPromPortPrimaryVlanId.description: The primary VLAN ID of the promiscous port.

privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap.name: privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap
privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN in the management domain on this port. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 0 through 7; the second octet to VLANs 8 through 15; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value VlanIndexOrZero in that octet. Note that if the length of this string is less than 128 octets, any 'missing' octets are assumed to contain the value zero. An NMS may omit any zero-valued octets from the end of this string in order to reduce SetPDU size, and the agent may also omit zero-valued trailing octets, to reduce the size of GetResponse PDUs.

privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap2k.name: privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap2k
privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap2k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 1024 through 2047 in the management domain on this port. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 1024 through 1031; the second octet to VLANs 1032 through 1039; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value VlanIndexOrZero in that octet. Note that if the length of this string is less than 128 octets, any 'missing' octets are assumed to contain the value zero. An NMS may omit any zero-valued octets from the end of this string in order to reduce SetPDU size, and the agent may also omit zero-valued trailing octets, to reduce the size of GetResponse PDUs. This object is only instantiated on devices which support the range of VlanIndexOrZero up to 4095.

privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap3k.name: privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap3k
privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap3k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 2048 through 3071 in the management domain on this port. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 2048 through 2055; the second octet to VLANs 2056 through 2063; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value VlanIndexOrZero in that octet. Note that if the length of this string is less than 128 octets, any 'missing' octets are assumed to contain the value zero. An NMS may omit any zero-valued octets from the end of this string in order to reduce SetPDU size, and the agent may also omit zero-valued trailing octets, to reduce the size of GetResponse PDUs. This object is only instantiated on devices which support the range of VlanIndexOrZero up to 4095.

privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap4k.name: privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap4k
privateVlanPromPortSecondaryRemap4k.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 3072 through 4095 in the management domain on this port. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndexOrZero values of 3072 through 3079; the second octet to VLANs 3080 through 3087; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value VlanIndexOrZero in that octet. Note that if the length of this string is less than 128 octets, any 'missing' octets are assumed to contain the value zero. An NMS may omit any zero-valued octets from the end of this string in order to reduce SetPDU size, and the agent may also omit zero-valued trailing octets, to reduce the size of GetResponse PDUs. This object is only instantiated on devices which support the range of VlanIndexOrZero up to 4095.

privateVlanSessionTable.name: privateVlanSessionTable
privateVlanSessionTable.description: Contains the settings for private VLAN Session.

privateVlanSessionEntry.name: privateVlanSessionEntry
privateVlanSessionEntry.description: A conceptual row in the privateVlanSession table.

privateVlanSessionId.name: privateVlanSessionId
privateVlanSessionId.description: The session ID that may specifiy certain entry in the table which contains private VLAN session information.

privateVlanSessionUplinkPorts.name: privateVlanSessionUplinkPorts
privateVlanSessionUplinkPorts.description: This is the list of uplink ports for a session of private VLAN. They should not overlap with the privateVlanSessionPortDownlink of the same session, and they also should not overlap with the privateVlanSessionPortUplink and the privateVlanSessionPortDownlink of other session.

privateVlanSessionDownlinkPorts.name: privateVlanSessionDownlinkPorts
privateVlanSessionDownlinkPorts.description: This is the list of downlink ports for a session of private VLAN. They should not overlap with the privateVlanSessionPortUplink of the same session, and they also should not overlap with the privateVlanSessionPortUplink and the privateVlanSessionPortDownlink of other session.

privateVlanSessionStatus.name: privateVlanSessionStatus
privateVlanSessionStatus.description: Set this to valid(1) to create an entry. Sets this to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

privateVlanUplinkToUplink.name: privateVlanUplinkToUplink
privateVlanUplinkToUplink.description: Sets this to blocking(2) to deny the traffic of uplink ports between different sessions. Set this to forwarding(1) to allow the traffic of uplink ports between different sessions.

portSecPortIndex.name: portSecPortIndex
portSecPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

portSecPortStatus.name: portSecPortStatus
portSecPortStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable port security and set disabled(2) to disable port security.

portSecAction.name: portSecAction
portSecAction.description: The corresponding actions that will take place when a port is under intrusion, when this variable is set to none(1), no action will be performed, when this variable is set to trap(2), a swPortSecurityTrap trap will be sent, when this variable is set to shutdown(3), the port will shutdown, when this variable is set to trapAndShutdown(4), a swPortSecurityTrap will be sent and the port will shutdown.

portSecMaxMacCount.name: portSecMaxMacCount
portSecMaxMacCount.description: The maximun number of MAC addresses that will be learned and locked. When we change the value of this variable, if the portSecPortStatus is enabled, we will discard all secure MAC and begin to learn again, until the number of MAC has reached this value, and only the secure MAC addresses can enter this port. If the portSecPortStatus is disabled, we will begin to learn the MAC, and auto enabled the portSecPortStatus when the MAC has reached this value.

portSecAutoSaveStatus.name: portSecAutoSaveStatus
portSecAutoSaveStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable the feature and set disabled(2) to disable the feature.

portSecMacAsPermanentPortIndex.name: portSecMacAsPermanentPortIndex
portSecMacAsPermanentPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB. Specifies the interface to convert the learnt secured MAC address into manual configured. '0' represents that no interface is specified.

portSecMacAsPermanentAction.name: portSecMacAsPermanentAction
portSecMacAsPermanentAction.description: Set action(2) to convert the learnt secured MAC address into manual configured. When action finsh or no action, the value of this object is noAction(1).

radiusServerGlobalAuthPort.name: radiusServerGlobalAuthPort
radiusServerGlobalAuthPort.description: Aauthentication port number for RADIUS server. When specified radius server do not set aauthentication port number, this value is used.

radiusServerGlobalAcctPort.name: radiusServerGlobalAcctPort
radiusServerGlobalAcctPort.description: Accounting port number of RADIUS server. When specified radius server do not set accounting port number, this value is used.

radiusServerGlobalKey.name: radiusServerGlobalKey
radiusServerGlobalKey.description: Key for RADIUS. This variable can only be written. When this variable is read, it always returns a zero-length string. When specified radius server do not set key, this this value is used.

radiusServerGlobalRetransmit.name: radiusServerGlobalRetransmit
radiusServerGlobalRetransmit.description: Maximum number of retransmissions for RADIUS. When specified radius server do not set maximum number of retransmissions, this value is used.

radiusServerGlobalTimeout.name: radiusServerGlobalTimeout
radiusServerGlobalTimeout.description: Timeout for RADIUS. When specified radius server do not set timeout, this value is used.

radiusServerIndex.name: radiusServerIndex
radiusServerIndex.description: The RADIUS server index in the table.

radiusServerAddress.name: radiusServerAddress
radiusServerAddress.description: IP address of a RADIUS server.

radiusServerAuthPortNumber.name: radiusServerAuthPortNumber
radiusServerAuthPortNumber.description: Authentication port number of RADIUS server.

radiusServerAcctPortNumber.name: radiusServerAcctPortNumber
radiusServerAcctPortNumber.description: Accounting port number of RADIUS server.

radiusServerKey.name: radiusServerKey
radiusServerKey.description: Key for RADIUS. This variable can only be written. When this variable is read, it always returns a zero-length string.

radiusServerStatus.name: radiusServerStatus
radiusServerStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

tacacsPlusServerGlobalPortNumber.name: tacacsPlusServerGlobalPortNumber
tacacsPlusServerGlobalPortNumber.description: TCP port number of TACACS+ server. When specified TACACS+ server do not set TCP port number, this this value is used.

tacacsPlusServerGlobalKey.name: tacacsPlusServerGlobalKey
tacacsPlusServerGlobalKey.description: The encryption key used to encrpt the traffic between client and TACACS+ server. Do not use blank spaces in the string. This variable can only be set. When this variable is read, it always returns a zero-length string.When specified TACACS+ server do not set the encryption key , this this value is used.

tacacsPlusServerAddress.name: tacacsPlusServerAddress
tacacsPlusServerAddress.description: IP address of a TACACS+ server.

tacacsPlusServerPortNumber.name: tacacsPlusServerPortNumber
tacacsPlusServerPortNumber.description: TCP port number of a TACACS+ server.

tacacsPlusServerKey.name: tacacsPlusServerKey
tacacsPlusServerKey.description: The encryption key used to encrpt the traffic between client and TACACS+ server. Do not use blank spaces in the string. This variable can only be set. When this variable is read, it always returns a zero-length string.

tacacsPlusServerStatus.name: tacacsPlusServerStatus
tacacsPlusServerStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

sshServerStatus.name: sshServerStatus
sshServerStatus.description: The status of Secure Shell Server. Set this value to enabled(1) to enable SSH server, set this value to disabled(2) to disable the SSH server.

sshServerMajorVersion.name: sshServerMajorVersion
sshServerMajorVersion.description: The major version of the SSH Server.

sshServerMinorVersion.name: sshServerMinorVersion
sshServerMinorVersion.description: The minor version of the SSH Server.

sshTimeout.name: sshTimeout
sshTimeout.description: The time interval that the router waits for the SSH client to respond. The range is 1-120.

sshAuthRetries.name: sshAuthRetries
sshAuthRetries.description: The number of attempts after which the interface is reset. The range is 1-5.

sshConnInfoTable.name: sshConnInfoTable
sshConnInfoTable.description: The table for Secure Shell Connection.

sshConnID.name: sshConnID
sshConnID.description: The connection ID of the Secure Shell Connection.

sshConnStatus.name: sshConnStatus
sshConnStatus.description: The SSH connection State. negotiationStart(1) means the SSH is in its negotiation start state, authenticationStart(2) means the SSH is in authentication start state, sessionStart(3) means the SSH is in session start State.

sshConnUserName.name: sshConnUserName
sshConnUserName.description: The user name of the connection.

sshDisconnect.name: sshDisconnect
sshDisconnect.description: Set the variable to disconnect the connection, noDisconnect(1) will always be obtained when reading this variable.

sshConnEncryptionTypeStr.name: sshConnEncryptionTypeStr
sshConnEncryptionTypeStr.description: The encryption type of the SSH.

sshHostKeyGenAction.name: sshHostKeyGenAction
sshHostKeyGenAction.description: This variable is for host key generating. For the set behavior: Set it to genRsaKey(2) to generate the RSA host key, and to genDsaKey(3) to generate the DSA host key, if genBothKeys(4) is set, both RSA and DSA host key are generated. For the get behavior: You will get genRsaKey(2), genDsaKey(3) or genBothKeys(4) when the key gen action is in progress. otherwise, you will get noGen(1).

sshHostKeyGenStatus.name: sshHostKeyGenStatus
sshHostKeyGenStatus.description: The result of the last KeyGen status. if no key gen action has been performed. you will get unknown(1) status.

sshHostKeySaveAction.name: sshHostKeySaveAction
sshHostKeySaveAction.description: To save host key from memory to flash. For the set behavior: Set it to save(2) to perform the save operation. For the get behavior: You will get save(1) when the save action is in progress. Otherwise, you will get noSave(1).

sshHostKeySaveStatus.name: sshHostKeySaveStatus
sshHostKeySaveStatus.description: The result of the last savekey status. If no save action has been performed, you will get unknown(1) status.

sshHostKeyDelAction.name: sshHostKeyDelAction
sshHostKeyDelAction.description: To delete the host key. For the set behavior: Set it to delRsaKey(2) to delete the RSA host key, to delDsaKey(3) to delete the DSA host key, or to delBothKeys(4) to delete both RSA and DSA host key. For the get behavior: You will get delRsaKey(2), delDsaKey(3) or delBothKeys(4) when the delete operation is in progress. Otherwise, you will get noDel(1).

sshUserTable.name: sshUserTable
sshUserTable.description: The conceptual table of all of sshUserEntry.

sshUserKeyDelAction.name: sshUserKeyDelAction
sshUserKeyDelAction.description: To delete the user key. For the set behavior: Set it to delRsaKey(2) to delete the RSA user key, to delDsaKey(3) to delete the DSA user key, or to delBothKeys(4) to delete both RSA and DSA user key. For the get behavior: You will get delRsaKey(2), delDsaKey(3) or delBothKeys(4) when the delete operation is in progress. Otherwise, you will get noDel(1).

sshRsaHostKeySHA1FingerPrint.name: sshRsaHostKeySHA1FingerPrint
sshRsaHostKeySHA1FingerPrint.description: The SHA1 finger print of the RSA host key.

sshRsaHostKeyMD5FingerPrint.name: sshRsaHostKeyMD5FingerPrint
sshRsaHostKeyMD5FingerPrint.description: The MD5 finger print of RSA host key.

sshDsaHostKeySHA1FingerPrint.name: sshDsaHostKeySHA1FingerPrint
sshDsaHostKeySHA1FingerPrint.description: The SHA1 finger print of the DSA host key.

sshDsaHostKeyMD5FingerPrint.name: sshDsaHostKeyMD5FingerPrint
sshDsaHostKeyMD5FingerPrint.description: The MD5 finger print of the DSA host key.

aaaMethodTable.name: aaaMethodTable
aaaMethodTable.description: Contains the settings needed for accounting.

aaaMethodEntry.name: aaaMethodEntry
aaaMethodEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aaaMethodTable.

aaaMethodIndex.name: aaaMethodIndex
aaaMethodIndex.description: Specifies the index for the entry.

aaaMethodGroupName.name: aaaMethodGroupName
aaaMethodGroupName.description: Name for the server to use, pointing to aaaRadiusGroupName or aaaTacacsPlusGroupName.

aaaMethodMode.name: aaaMethodMode
aaaMethodMode.description: start-stop(1),sends a 'start' accounting notice at the beginning of a process and a 'stop' accounting notice at the end of a process. The 'start' accounting record is sent in the background. The requested user process begins regardless of whether or not the 'start' accounting notice was received by the accounting server.

aaaMethodStatus.name: aaaMethodStatus
aaaMethodStatus.description: Set to 1 to initiate the aaaMethodTable, 2 to destroy the table.

aaaMethodClientType.name: aaaMethodClientType
aaaMethodClientType.description: dot1x(1): Provides accounting service for 802.1x activity; exec(2): Provides accounting service for EXEC connection such as Telnet, SSH or console; commands(3): Provides accounting service for command privileges.

aaaMethodPrivilegeLevel.name: aaaMethodPrivilegeLevel
aaaMethodPrivilegeLevel.description: Specifies the privilege level for the entry. When aaaMethodClientType is in the mode of command(3), the privilege level is enabled to be accessed.

aaaRadiusGroupTable.name: aaaRadiusGroupTable
aaaRadiusGroupTable.description: Uses a subset of RADIUS servers for accounting as defined by the server group

aaaRadiusGroupIndex.name: aaaRadiusGroupIndex
aaaRadiusGroupIndex.description: Specifies the index for the entry.

aaaRadiusGroupServerBitMap.name: aaaRadiusGroupServerBitMap
aaaRadiusGroupServerBitMap.description: Identifies which RADIUS sever to use, each bit points to each radius server. 80 (1000 0000) point to radius server 1, C0 (11000000) points to radius 1 and radius 2.

aaaRadiusGroupName.name: aaaRadiusGroupName
aaaRadiusGroupName.description: Uses a subset of servers for accounting as defined by the server group. The same name as aaaTacasPlusGroupName is not allowed.

aaaRadiusGroupStatus.name: aaaRadiusGroupStatus
aaaRadiusGroupStatus.description: Set to 1 to initiate the aaaRadiusGroupTable, 2 to destroy the table.

aaaTacacsPlusGroupTable.name: aaaTacacsPlusGroupTable
aaaTacacsPlusGroupTable.description: Uses a subset of TACACS+ servers for accounting as defined by the server group

aaaTacacsPlusGroupIndex.name: aaaTacacsPlusGroupIndex
aaaTacacsPlusGroupIndex.description: Specifies the index for the entry.

aaaTacacsPlusGroupServerBitMap.name: aaaTacacsPlusGroupServerBitMap
aaaTacacsPlusGroupServerBitMap.description: Identifies which TACACS+ sever to use.

aaaTacacsPlusGroupName.name: aaaTacacsPlusGroupName
aaaTacacsPlusGroupName.description: Uses a subset of servers for accounting as defined by the server group. We can't have the same name as aaaRadiusGroupName

aaaTacacsPlusGroupStatus.name: aaaTacacsPlusGroupStatus
aaaTacacsPlusGroupStatus.description: Set to 1 to initiate the aaaRadiusGroupTable, 2 to destroy the table.

aaaUpdate.name: aaaUpdate
aaaUpdate.description: Specifies the periodic interim accounting records to be sent to the accounting server and periodic intervals to send accounting update records(in minutes).

aaaAccountTable.name: aaaAccountTable
aaaAccountTable.description: Specifies an interface or a set of interfaces that the accounting method list will be applied to.

aaaAccountMethodName.name: aaaAccountMethodName
aaaAccountMethodName.description: Specifies the name of the list of accounting methods to use. If no method name is specified, the system uses the default.

aaaAccountProtocol.name: aaaAccountProtocol
aaaAccountProtocol.description: Get the protocol type of a list method to know which server (RADIUS or TACACS+) is in use.

aaaAccountStatus.name: aaaAccountStatus
aaaAccountStatus.description: Set to 1 to initiate the aaaRadiusGroupTable, 2 to destroy the table.

aaaCommandPrivilegesTable.name: aaaCommandPrivilegesTable
aaaCommandPrivilegesTable.description: Contains the settings needed for command privileges.

aaaCommandPrivilegesEntry.name: aaaCommandPrivilegesEntry
aaaCommandPrivilegesEntry.description: A conceptual row in the aaaCommandPrivilegesTable.

aaaCommandPrivilegesLevel.name: aaaCommandPrivilegesLevel
aaaCommandPrivilegesLevel.description: Specifies the privilege level index for the entry.

aaaCommandPrivilegesInterfaceIndex.name: aaaCommandPrivilegesInterfaceIndex
aaaCommandPrivilegesInterfaceIndex.description: Specifies the interface index for the entry.

aaaCommandPrivilegesMethodName.name: aaaCommandPrivilegesMethodName
aaaCommandPrivilegesMethodName.description: Specifies the method name in the lists under the mode of command privileges.

aaaAccExecTable.name: aaaAccExecTable
aaaAccExecTable.description: Specifies an interface or a set of interfaces that the accounting method list will be applied to.

aaaAccExecIndex.name: aaaAccExecIndex
aaaAccExecIndex.description: The method of accessing CLI management.

aaaAccExecMethodName.name: aaaAccExecMethodName
aaaAccExecMethodName.description: Specifies the name of the list of accounting methods to use. If no method name is specified, the system uses the default.

userAuthEnablePassword.name: userAuthEnablePassword
userAuthEnablePassword.description: Set enable password or delete enable password. NULL is used to delete the enable password. The password is starting with alphanumeric.

userAuthMethod.name: userAuthMethod
userAuthMethod.description: Set user authencation method for system.

userAuthTable.name: userAuthTable
userAuthTable.description: This table is for creating the new user.

userAuthEntry.name: userAuthEntry
userAuthEntry.description: Entries in this table correspond to the users entries in system.

userAuthUserName.name: userAuthUserName
userAuthUserName.description: The name of the user. The user name is starting with alphanumeric.

userAuthPassword.name: userAuthPassword
userAuthPassword.description: Specifies the user password. zero length input will set the user enrty without password. If the user is not exist, it will create the user with the giving password and privilege 0. The password is starting with alphanumeric.

userAuthPrivilege.name: userAuthPrivilege
userAuthPrivilege.description: Specifies the user level. If the user is not exist, it will create the user with the giving privilege with none password. Privilege 15 is maximum privilege that only can be applied to system administrator.

userAuthPublicKey.name: userAuthPublicKey
userAuthPublicKey.description: User public key, the value can be 'RSA' or 'DSA' or 'Both' or 'None'.

userAuthStatus.name: userAuthStatus
userAuthStatus.description: This node is used to create the user entry by '1' and to delete one user entry by '0'.

aclAttachCtlIndex.name: aclAttachCtlIndex
aclAttachCtlIndex.description: Index for attachment control. Specifies the ACL as the target to relate with the IP ACE, the MAC ACE or IPv6 ACE. The ACL identified by a particular value of this index is associated with the same aclEntry as identified by the same value of aclIndex.

aclAttachCtlAceType.name: aclAttachCtlAceType
aclAttachCtlAceType.description: Type for attachment control. Specifies the type of aclAttachCtlAceIndex to relate with the aclAttachCtlIndex. When the type is macAce(1), the index of aclAceIndexList is the aclMacAceEntry. When the type is ipAce(2), the index of aclAceIndexList is the aclIpAceEntry. When the type is ipv6Ace(3), the index of aclAceIndexList is the aclIpv6AceEntry.

aclAttachCtlAceIndex.name: aclAttachCtlAceIndex
aclAttachCtlAceIndex.description: Index for attachment control. Specifies the ACE to relate with the aclAttachCtlIndex. When aclAttachCtlAceType is macAce(1), the value of aclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServMacAceEntry. When aclAttachCtlAceType is ipAce(2), the value of aclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServIpAceEntry. When aclAttachCtlAceType is ipv6Ace(3), the value of aclAttachCtlIndex is the diffServIpv6AceEntry.

aclAttachCtlAction.name: aclAttachCtlAction
aclAttachCtlAction.description: Action for attachment control. When setting this object to attach(2) to begin the attaching operation, a particular ACE is attached to a particular ACL. When setting this object to detach(3) to begin the not attached operation, then a particular ACE is not attached to a particular ACL. When the action is finshed whether successfully or not, or no action is taken, the value of this object always is noAction(1), The value of a particular ACL is specified in the aclAttachCtlAceType and aclAttachCtlAceIndex.

ipFilterSnmpInetTable.name: ipFilterSnmpInetTable
ipFilterSnmpInetTable.description: A list of IP address entries.

ipFilterSnmpInetEntry.name: ipFilterSnmpInetEntry
ipFilterSnmpInetEntry.description: This entry includes an IP address range which the system will allow to connect to this device through SNMP.

ipFilterSnmpInetAddressType.name: ipFilterSnmpInetAddressType
ipFilterSnmpInetAddressType.description: The type of IP address filter. Only supports IPv4 and IPv6 address types.

ipFilterSnmpInetStatus.name: ipFilterSnmpInetStatus
ipFilterSnmpInetStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

ipFilterHttpInetTable.name: ipFilterHttpInetTable
ipFilterHttpInetTable.description: A list of IP address entries.

ipFilterHttpInetEntry.name: ipFilterHttpInetEntry
ipFilterHttpInetEntry.description: This entry includes an IP address range which the system will allow to connect to this device through SNMP.

ipFilterHttpInetAddressType.name: ipFilterHttpInetAddressType
ipFilterHttpInetAddressType.description: The type of IP address filter . Only supports IPv4 and IPv6 address types.

ipFilterHttpInetStatus.name: ipFilterHttpInetStatus
ipFilterHttpInetStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

ipFilterTelnetInetTable.name: ipFilterTelnetInetTable
ipFilterTelnetInetTable.description: A list of IP address entries.

ipFilterTelnetInetEntry.name: ipFilterTelnetInetEntry
ipFilterTelnetInetEntry.description: This entry includes an IP address range which the system will allow them to connect to this device through SNMP.

ipFilterTelnetInetAddressType.name: ipFilterTelnetInetAddressType
ipFilterTelnetInetAddressType.description: The type of IP address filter . Only supports IPv4 and IPv6 address types.

ipFilterTelnetInetStatus.name: ipFilterTelnetInetStatus
ipFilterTelnetInetStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

ipFilterAllClientCtlInetAddressType.name: ipFilterAllClientCtlInetAddressType
ipFilterAllClientCtlInetAddressType.description: The type of IP address filter. Only supports IPv4 and IPv6 address types.

ipFilterAllClientCtlAction.name: ipFilterAllClientCtlAction
ipFilterAllClientCtlAction.description: Action for IP filter control. Set this object to create(2) to create entries in the ipFilterSnmpInetTable, ipFilterHttpInetTable and ipFilterTelnetInetTable. Set this object to destroy(3) to destroy specified entries in the ipFilterSnmpInetTable, ipFilterHttpInetTable and ipFilterTelnetInetTable. When the action is finshed, whether successfully or not, or no action is taken, the value of this object is always noAction(1).

dot1xAuthConfigExtOperMode.name: dot1xAuthConfigExtOperMode
dot1xAuthConfigExtOperMode.description: The operation mode of dot1x port which allows host connection to 802.1x-authorized ports.

dot1xAuthConfigExtMultiHostMaxCnt.name: dot1xAuthConfigExtMultiHostMaxCnt
dot1xAuthConfigExtMultiHostMaxCnt.description: The maximum number of hosts when the dot1xAuthConfigExtOperMode is multiHost(2). When the operation Mode is singleHost(1), we can ignore this variables.

dot1xAuthConfigExtPortIntrusionAction.name: dot1xAuthConfigExtPortIntrusionAction
dot1xAuthConfigExtPortIntrusionAction.description: Responses to intrusion when the authentication is failed; block-traffic(1) means that to block traffic when the authentication is failed and guest-vlan(2) means that to join to a guest VLAN when the authentication is failed.

dot1xEapolPassThrough.name: dot1xEapolPassThrough
dot1xEapolPassThrough.description: When this variable is enabled(1), EAPOL frames will be forwarded to all ports where the Spanning Tree status is forwarding. When this variable is disabled(2), EAPOL frames will be discarded. EAPOL Pass-Through operates when the global status of 802.1X is disabled.

networkAccessPortTable.name: networkAccessPortTable
networkAccessPortTable.description: A table contains the information of network access about every port.

networkAccessPortEntry.name: networkAccessPortEntry
networkAccessPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the networkAccessPort table.

networkAccessPortPortIndex.name: networkAccessPortPortIndex
networkAccessPortPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this port index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

networkAccessPortDynamicVlan.name: networkAccessPortDynamicVlan
networkAccessPortDynamicVlan.description: Sets enabled(1) to enable dynamic VLAN assigment and sets disabled(2) to disable dynamic VLAN assigment.

networkAccessPortMaxMacCount.name: networkAccessPortMaxMacCount
networkAccessPortMaxMacCount.description: Specifies the maximum number of authenticated MAC address.

networkAccessPortMode.name: networkAccessPortMode
networkAccessPortMode.description: Specifies the secure port mode. enabled(1) means that Mac address authentication is used and disabled(2) means that the authentication is disabled.

networkAccessPortMacFilter.name: networkAccessPortMacFilter
networkAccessPortMacFilter.description: Specifies the MAC filter ID, Set this variable to zero to disable MAC filter.

networkAccessPortGuestVlan.name: networkAccessPortGuestVlan
networkAccessPortGuestVlan.description: Specifies the guest VLAN ID. To disable the VLAN, set the value to 0.

networkAccessPortLinkDetectionStatus.name: networkAccessPortLinkDetectionStatus
networkAccessPortLinkDetectionStatus.description: Set this object to enabled(1) to enable link detection. Set this object to disabled(2) to disable link detection.

networkAccessPortLinkDetectionMode.name: networkAccessPortLinkDetectionMode
networkAccessPortLinkDetectionMode.description: Specifies the detection event for a port. Set this object to linkUp(1) to detect a link-up event. Set this object to linkDown(2) to detect a link-down event. Set this object to linkUpDown(3) to detect both link up and link down events.

networkAccessPortLinkDetectionAciton.name: networkAccessPortLinkDetectionAciton
networkAccessPortLinkDetectionAciton.description: Specifies the action to take when a networkAccessPortLinkDetection event is triggered. Set this object to trap(1) to send a trap when a networkAccessPortLinkDetection event is triggered. Set this object to shutDown(2) to shut down the port when a networkAccessPortLinkDetection event is triggered. Set this object to trapAndShutDown(3) to send a trap and shut down the port when a networkAccessPortLinkDetection event is triggered.

networkAccessPortDynamicQos.name: networkAccessPortDynamicQos
networkAccessPortDynamicQos.description: Set this object to enabled(1) to enable Dynamic QoS. Set this object to disabled(2) to disable Dynamic QoS.

networkAccessClearMacAddressAttribute.name: networkAccessClearMacAddressAttribute
networkAccessClearMacAddressAttribute.description: Attribute for clearing Mac address. Specifies the certain attribute in Mac address table. all(1) indicates both reauthorized and learnt secure MAC address; static(2) indicates reauthorized MAC address; dynamic(3) indicates learnt secure MAC address.

networkAccessClearMacAddressMacAddress.name: networkAccessClearMacAddressMacAddress
networkAccessClearMacAddressMacAddress.description: Specifies MAC address in the MAC address table for clearing MAC address. '000000' represents that no MAC address is specified.

networkAccessClearMacAddressPort.name: networkAccessClearMacAddressPort
networkAccessClearMacAddressPort.description: The specifies port in the MAC address table for clearing MAC address. '0' represents that no port is specified.

networkAccessClearMacAddressAction.name: networkAccessClearMacAddressAction
networkAccessClearMacAddressAction.description: Action for clearing MAC address . When setting this object to clear(2) to begin the clearing MAC address operation, a particular MAC address is cleared from the MAC address table. When the action is finshed whether or not it is successful or no action is taken, the value of this object is always noclear(1).

networkAccessMacAddressTable.name: networkAccessMacAddressTable
networkAccessMacAddressTable.description: Contains the information of network access MAC addresses.

networkAccessMacAddressEntry.name: networkAccessMacAddressEntry
networkAccessMacAddressEntry.description: A conceptual row in the networkAccessMacAddress table.

networkAccessMacAddressPort.name: networkAccessMacAddressPort
networkAccessMacAddressPort.description: Specifies the port of authenticated MAC address.

networkAccessMacAddressInetAddressType.name: networkAccessMacAddressInetAddressType
networkAccessMacAddressInetAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of IP address denoted in networkAccessMacAddressRadiusServerInetAddress type.

networkAccessMacAddressRadiusServerInetA.name: networkAccessMacAddressRadiusServerInetAddress
networkAccessMacAddressRadiusServerInetA.description: Displays the IP address of radius server that authenticates the specified Mac address.

networkAccessMacAddressTime.name: networkAccessMacAddressTime
networkAccessMacAddressTime.description: Displays the authentication time of the authenticated MAC address. The following form is a text string; 'yyyy MMm DDd HHh MMm SSs'. 'yyyy' is a four-digit year. 'MM' is a month. A single-digit month is preceded by a zero. 'DD' is the day of a month. A single-digit day is preceded by the value zero. 'HH', 'MM' and 'SS' are hour, minute, and second respectively. A single-digit hour, minute, and second are preceded by a zero value. An example is: '2001y 01m 01d 00h 04m 43s'.

networkAccessMacAddressAttribute.name: networkAccessMacAddressAttribute
networkAccessMacAddressAttribute.description: Displays the attribute of an authenticated MAC address. static(1) indicates resauthorized secure MAC address. dynamic(2) indicates learnt secure MAC address.

networkAccessAging.name: networkAccessAging
networkAccessAging.description: Set this object to enabled(1) to enable MAC address aging feature. Set this object to disabled(2) to disable MAC address aging feature.

networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskTable.name: networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskTable
networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskTable.description: Contains the settings for MAC filter.

networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskEntry.name: networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskEntry
networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskEntry.description: A conceptual row in the networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskTable.

networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskMacAddress.name: networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskMacAddress
networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address to be filtered.

networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskMacAddress.name: networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskMacAddressMask
networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC mask to be filtered.

networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskStatus.name: networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskStatus
networkAccessMacFilterWithMaskStatus.description: Set this object to valid(1) to create an entry. Set this object to invalid(2) to destroy an entry.

macAuthPortTable.name: macAuthPortTable
macAuthPortTable.description: Contains the settings for mac authentication of each port.

macAuthPortEntry.name: macAuthPortEntry
macAuthPortEntry.description: A conceptual row in the macAuthPort table.

macAuthPortIndex.name: macAuthPortIndex
macAuthPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (including trunk members) interface of the port table. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

macAuthPortMaxMacCount.name: macAuthPortMaxMacCount
macAuthPortMaxMacCount.description: Specifies the maximum number of authenticated MAC addresses for MAC authentication.

macAuthPortIntrusionAction.name: macAuthPortIntrusionAction
macAuthPortIntrusionAction.description: Responses to intrusion when the authentication is failed. block-traffic(1) : denies network access to an unauthorized client; pass-traffic(2) : allows unauthorized clients to the access network.

webAuthSystemAuthControl.name: webAuthSystemAuthControl
webAuthSystemAuthControl.description: Sets enabled(1) to enable WebAuth feature and sets disabled(2) to disable WebAuth feature.

webAuthSessionTimeout.name: webAuthSessionTimeout
webAuthSessionTimeout.description: For authenticated success users, they can use internet service during a certain period. Whenever this period expires, users need to be re-authenticated again. This period is called session time.

webAuthQuietPeriod.name: webAuthQuietPeriod
webAuthQuietPeriod.description: Specifies the re-authentication interval when the authentication fail attempts reach the webAuthLoginAttempts value. Unauthenticated user won't be authenticated during this period.

webAuthLoginAttempts.name: webAuthLoginAttempts
webAuthLoginAttempts.description: Specifies the counter that configures the authentication fail times for a client. If authentication fail times reaches the specified value, the client are not allowed to login for some period.

webAuthReauthenticatePort.name: webAuthReauthenticatePort
webAuthReauthenticatePort.description: Specifies the port to re-authenticate for all of its authenticated hosts.

webAuthReauthenticateAction.name: webAuthReauthenticateAction
webAuthReauthenticateAction.description: Action for WebAuth re-authenication. When setting this object to reauth(2) to begin the re-authenticated operation, a particular user is re-authenticated. When the action is finshed whether it is successfully, or no action is taken, the value of this object is always noReauth(1).

webAuthPortConfigTable.name: webAuthPortConfigTable
webAuthPortConfigTable.description: Contains the settings for web authentication of each port.

webAuthPortConfigEntry.name: webAuthPortConfigEntry
webAuthPortConfigEntry.description: A conceptual row in the webAuthPortConfigTable.

webAuthPortConfigPortIndex.name: webAuthPortConfigPortIndex
webAuthPortConfigPortIndex.description: The port number of the port that may specify certain entry in the table which contains web authentication information.

webAuthPortConfigStatus.name: webAuthPortConfigStatus
webAuthPortConfigStatus.description: Sets enabled(1) to enable web authentication feature for each port and sets disabled(2) to disable web authentication for each port.

webAuthPortConfigAuthenticatedHostCount.name: webAuthPortConfigAuthenticatedHostCount
webAuthPortConfigAuthenticatedHostCount.description: Displays the authenticated host counts for each port

webAuthPortInfoTable.name: webAuthPortInfoTable
webAuthPortInfoTable.description: Contains the information for web authentication of each port.

webAuthPortInfoEntry.name: webAuthPortInfoEntry
webAuthPortInfoEntry.description: A conceptual row in the webAuthPortTable.

webAuthPortInfoPortIndex.name: webAuthPortInfoPortIndex
webAuthPortInfoPortIndex.description: The port number for which this entry contains web authentication information.

webAuthPortInfoPortAuthSuccessIndex.name: webAuthPortInfoPortAuthSuccessIndex
webAuthPortInfoPortAuthSuccessIndex.description: The authentication success number of port for which this entry contains web authentication information.

webAuthPortInfoInetAddressType.name: webAuthPortInfoInetAddressType
webAuthPortInfoInetAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of IP address denoted in webAuthPortInfoIpAddress type.

webAuthPortInfoInetAddress.name: webAuthPortInfoInetAddress
webAuthPortInfoInetAddress.description: The IP address which may specify the entry containing web authentication information.

webAuthPortInfoRemainingSessiontime.name: webAuthPortInfoRemainingSessiontime
webAuthPortInfoRemainingSessiontime.description: The remaining session time for authenticated hosts. During this period, they may use internet resource. When the session time expires, they will need to re-authenticate again.

webAuthPortInfoStatus.name: webAuthPortInfoStatus
webAuthPortInfoStatus.description: Displays the web authentication status for each port. authenticated (1) means the user is authenticated.

dosEchoChargenStatus.name: dosEchoChargenStatus
dosEchoChargenStatus.description: The status of Echo/Chargen protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosEchoChargenRateLimitInKilo.name: dosEchoChargenRateLimitInKilo
dosEchoChargenRateLimitInKilo.description: Value of the rate limit for Echo/Chargen packets. The unit is kilobits per second.

dosSmurfStatus.name: dosSmurfStatus
dosSmurfStatus.description: The status of Smurf protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosTcpFloodingStatus.name: dosTcpFloodingStatus
dosTcpFloodingStatus.description: The status of TCP flooding protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosTcpFloodingRateLimitInKilo.name: dosTcpFloodingRateLimitInKilo
dosTcpFloodingRateLimitInKilo.description: Value of the rate limit for TCP flooding packets. The unit is kilobits per second.

dosTcpNullScanStatus.name: dosTcpNullScanStatus
dosTcpNullScanStatus.description: The status of TCP Null-scan protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosTcpSynFinScanStatus.name: dosTcpSynFinScanStatus
dosTcpSynFinScanStatus.description: The status of TCP SYN FIN scan protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosTcpXmasScanStatus.name: dosTcpXmasScanStatus
dosTcpXmasScanStatus.description: The status of TCP Xmas-scan protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosUdpFloodingStatus.name: dosUdpFloodingStatus
dosUdpFloodingStatus.description: The status of UDP flooding protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosUdpFloodingRateLimitInKilo.name: dosUdpFloodingRateLimitInKilo
dosUdpFloodingRateLimitInKilo.description: Value of the rate limit for UDP flooding packets. The unit is kilobits per second.

dosWinNukeStatus.name: dosWinNukeStatus
dosWinNukeStatus.description: The status of WinNUKE protection. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

dosWinNukeRateLimitInKilo.name: dosWinNukeRateLimitInKilo
dosWinNukeRateLimitInKilo.description: Value of the rate limit for WinNUKE packets. The unit is kilobits per second.

dosTcpUdpPortZeroStatus.name: dosTcpUdpPortZeroStatus
dosTcpUdpPortZeroStatus.description: The status of checking for TCP/UDP packets with port 0. Set this to enabled(1) to enable the feature, and set this to disabled(2) to disable the feature.

appFilterPortIndex.name: appFilterPortIndex
appFilterPortIndex.description: The port interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

appFilterProtocolType.name: appFilterProtocolType
appFilterProtocolType.description: The protocol type define some specific packets which are supported on this function

appFilterPktStatus.name: appFilterPktStatus
appFilterPktStatus.description: Set discard(1) to discard packet and set default(0) to transmit packet in default behavior.

sysLogStatus.name: sysLogStatus
sysLogStatus.description: Whether the system log is enabled.

sysLogHistoryFlashLevel.name: sysLogHistoryFlashLevel
sysLogHistoryFlashLevel.description: Severity level for logging to flash.

sysLogHistoryRamLevel.name: sysLogHistoryRamLevel
sysLogHistoryRamLevel.description: Severity level for logging to RAM.

remoteLogStatus.name: remoteLogStatus
remoteLogStatus.description: Whether the remote log system is enabled.

remoteLogFacilityType.name: remoteLogFacilityType
remoteLogFacilityType.description: The facility type for remote log.

remoteLogServerInetTable.name: remoteLogServerInetTable
remoteLogServerInetTable.description: A table for storing the remote log server list.

remoteLogServerInetAddressType.name: remoteLogServerInetAddressType
remoteLogServerInetAddressType.description: Indicates the type of address denoted in remoteLogServerInetAddress type. Only ipv4(1), ipv6(2) and ipv6z(4) types are supported.

remoteLogServerInetAddress.name: remoteLogServerInetAddress
remoteLogServerInetAddress.description: The IP address of the remote log Server.

remoteLogServerStatus.name: remoteLogServerStatus
remoteLogServerStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

remoteLogServerUdpPort.name: remoteLogServerUdpPort
remoteLogServerUdpPort.description: The UDP port number of the remote log Server

smtpStatus.name: smtpStatus
smtpStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable the SMTP, set disabled(2) to disable the SMTP.

smtpSeverityLevel.name: smtpSeverityLevel
smtpSeverityLevel.description: Specify the SMTP minimum severity level to send the event message.

smtpSourceEMail.name: smtpSourceEMail
smtpSourceEMail.description: SMTP source email address, the sender's mail address that appears in the 'From' field of the mail.

smtpServerIpTable.name: smtpServerIpTable
smtpServerIpTable.description: The SMTP server IP table. The maximum servers to be added is 3.

smtpServerIpEntry.name: smtpServerIpEntry
smtpServerIpEntry.description: A conceptual row of the smtpServerIpTable.

smtpServerIpStatus.name: smtpServerIpStatus
smtpServerIpStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

smtpDestEMailTable.name: smtpDestEMailTable
smtpDestEMailTable.description: The table of the destination e-mail address. The maximum numbers of destination email address to be added is 5.

smtpDestEMailEntry.name: smtpDestEMailEntry
smtpDestEMailEntry.description: A conceptual row of the smtpDestEMailTable.

smtpDestEMailStatus.name: smtpDestEMailStatus
smtpDestEMailStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

consoleParity.name: consoleParity
consoleParity.description: Defines the generation of a parity bit.

consoleBaudRate.name: consoleBaudRate
consoleBaudRate.description: Baud rate: Valid values are 115200, 57600, 38400, 19200, and 9600.

consoleStopBits.name: consoleStopBits
consoleStopBits.description: The console stop bits, valid values are stopbits1(1) or stopbits2(2)

consoleExecTimeout.name: consoleExecTimeout
consoleExecTimeout.description: In a serial console, use the consoleExecTimeout variable to set the interval that the EXEC command interpreter waits until user input is detected; set the value to 0 to disable it.

consolePasswordThreshold.name: consolePasswordThreshold
consolePasswordThreshold.description: The number of failed console logon attempts that may be made before the system will not accept a further attempt in the time specified by consoleSilentTime. A value of 0 disables the functionality.

consoleSilentTime.name: consoleSilentTime
consoleSilentTime.description: The length of time that the management console is inaccessible after the number of failed logon attempts has reached consolePasswordThreshold. A value of 0 disables the functionality.

telnetStatus.name: telnetStatus
telnetStatus.description: To enable or disable the telnet function. Any new telnet request will be rejected and all current telnet sessions will be terminated if this status is set to disabled(2).

vtyExecTimeout.name: vtyExecTimeout
vtyExecTimeout.description: Specifies the interval that the system waits for user input before terminating the current session.

vtyPasswordThreshold.name: vtyPasswordThreshold
vtyPasswordThreshold.description: The number of failed logon attempts that may be made before the system will not accept a further attempt to log on. Setting to 0 means disabled.

vtyMaxSession.name: vtyMaxSession
vtyMaxSession.description: The maximum number of allowed sessions.

vtySilentTime.name: vtySilentTime
vtySilentTime.description: The time the system waits before etablishing a new session after the number of failed logins reaches the specified limit. Setting to 0 means disabled.

sntpStatus.name: sntpStatus
sntpStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable the SNTP, set disabled(2) to disable the SNTP.

sntpServerTable.name: sntpServerTable
sntpServerTable.description: Table for SNTP servers. IP addresses must occupy contiguous indexes, starting from 1. If a removed entry is not the last entry, the table will be shifted to contiguous indexes automatically.

sntpServerInetAddressType.name: sntpServerInetAddressType
sntpServerInetAddressType.description: Indicates the type of address denoted in sntpServerInetAddress type. Only ipv4(1), ipv6(2) and ipv6z(4) types are supported.

sntpServerInetAddress.name: sntpServerInetAddress
sntpServerInetAddress.description: The IP address of a time server.

sntpServerStatus.name: sntpServerStatus
sntpServerStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

sysCurrentTime.name: sysCurrentTime
sysCurrentTime.description: This is a text string in the following form, based on Unix: 'Mmm _d hh:mm:ss yyyy'. 'Mmm' are the first three letters of the English name of the month. '_d' is the day of month. A single-digit day is preceded by a space. 'hh:mm:ss' is a 24-hour representations of hours, minutes, and seconds. A single-digit hour is preceded by a zero. 'yyyy' is a four-digit year. An example is: 'Jan 1 02:03:04 2002'.

sysTimeZone.name: sysTimeZone
sysTimeZone.description: This is a text string in the following form: '[s]hh:mm'. '[s]' is a plus-or-minus sign. For UTC, this is omitted. For a positive offset, this is '+'. For a negative offset, this is '-'. 'hh:mm' in the hour and minute offset from UTC. A single-digit hour is preceded by a zero. When sysTimeZonePredefined object is set to any value other than none(1), this object will be empty string.

sysTimeZoneName.name: sysTimeZoneName
sysTimeZoneName.description: The name of the time zone. When sysTimeZonePredefined object is set to any value other than none(1), this object will be empty string.

ntpStatus.name: ntpStatus
ntpStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable the NTP, set disabled(2) to disable the NTP.

ntpAuthenticateStatus.name: ntpAuthenticateStatus
ntpAuthenticateStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable the NTP Authenticate, set disabled(2) to disable the NTP.

ntpServerIpAddress.name: ntpServerIpAddress
ntpServerIpAddress.description: The IP address of a server. Valid IP addresses must occupy contiguous indexes. All IP addresses after the last valid index is 0.

ntpServerKeyId.name: ntpServerKeyId
ntpServerKeyId.description: Key for a NTP server. This variable can only be written.

ntpServerStatus.name: ntpServerStatus
ntpServerStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

ntpAuthKeyId.name: ntpAuthKeyId
ntpAuthKeyId.description: The index of a Authentication key. This table has fixed size.

ntpAuthKeyWord.name: ntpAuthKeyWord
ntpAuthKeyWord.description: The Authentication key word is used to created a key by the MD5 And the max length is 32.

ntpAuthKeyStatus.name: ntpAuthKeyStatus
ntpAuthKeyStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

fileCopySrcOperType.name: fileCopySrcOperType
fileCopySrcOperType.description: fileCopySrcOperType specifies where to copy from, and fileCopyDestOperType specifies where to copy to. Possible combinations of 'fileCopySrcOperType to fileCopyDestOperType' and required parameters are listed in the following table. --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- Source | Destination | Required parameters --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- file(1) | file(1) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName +------------------+--------------------------------- | runningCfg(2) | fileCopySrcFileName +------------------+--------------------------------- | startUpCfg(3) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName +------------------+--------------------------------- | tftp(4) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyFileType | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress +------------------+--------------------------------- | unit(5) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyFileType | | fileCopyUnitId +------------------+--------------------------------- | ftp(7) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyFileType | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress | | fileCopyServerUserName | | fileCopyServerPassword --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- runningCfg(2) | file(1) | fileCopyDestFileName +------------------+--------------------------------- | startUpCfg(3) | fileCopyDestFileName +------------------+--------------------------------- | tftp(4) | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress +------------------+--------------------------------- | ftp(7) | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress | | fileCopyServerUserName | | fileCopyServerPassword --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- startUpCfg(3) | file(1) | fileCopyDestFileName +------------------+--------------------------------- | runningCfg(2) | None. +------------------+--------------------------------- | tftp(4) | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress +------------------+--------------------------------- | ftp(7) | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress | | fileCopyServerUserName | | fileCopyServerPassword --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- tftp(4) | file(1) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyFileType | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress +------------------+--------------------------------- | runningCfg(2) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress +------------------+--------------------------------- | startUpCfg(3) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress +------------------+--------------------------------- | addRunningCfg(15)| fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- unit(5) | file(1) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyFileType | | fileCopyUnitId --------------+------------------+--------------------------------- ftp(7) | file(1) | fileCopySrcFileName | | fileCopyDestFileName | | fileCopyFileType | | fileCopyServerInetAddressType | | fileCopyServerInetAddress | | fileCopyServerUserName | | fileCopyServerPassword +------------------+--------------------------------- | runningCfg(2) | fileCopySrcFileName | |
