fileCopyServerPassword --------------+------------------+---------------------------------

fileCopySrcFileName.name: fileCopySrcFileName
fileCopySrcFileName.description: The source file name for fileCopyMgt when a copy operation is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to a zero length string when no file name has been specified. Note: If the fileCopySrcOperType is runningCfg(2) or startUpCfg(3), this variable can be ignored.

fileCopyDestFileName.name: fileCopyDestFileName
fileCopyDestFileName.description: The destination file name for fileCopyMgt when a copy operation is next requested via this MIB. This value is set to a zero length string when no file name has been specified. Note: If the fileCopyDestOperType is runningCfg(2) or startupCfg(3), this variable can be ignored.

fileCopyFileType.name: fileCopyFileType
fileCopyFileType.description: Type of file to copy in fileCopyMgt. opcode(1) indicates operation code, config(2) indicates configuration file, bootRom(3) indicates diagnostic image file and loader(5) indicates loader image file. If the fileCopySrcOperType or fileCopyDestOperType is either runningCfg(2) or startupCfg(3), this variable can be ignored. bootRom(3) and loader(5) can be set only when the fileCopySrcOperType is tftp(4) and fileCopyDestOperType is file(1).

fileCopyUnitId.name: fileCopyUnitId
fileCopyUnitId.description: Specifies the switch unit for stackable devices. When performing the 'copy unit file' or 'copy file unit' action, if neither fileCopySrcOperType nor fileCopyDestOperType is unit(5), this variable can be ignored.

fileCopyAction.name: fileCopyAction
fileCopyAction.description: Setting this object to copy(2) to begin the copy operation. When the device is not copying, this object will have a value of notCopying(1).

fileCopyStatus.name: fileCopyStatus
fileCopyStatus.description: The status of the last copy procedure, if any. This object will have a value of fileCopyUnknown(18) if no copy operation has been performed. The listed values are identical to fileAutoDownloadResultStatus.

fileCopyServerInetAddressType.name: fileCopyServerInetAddressType
fileCopyServerInetAddressType.description: Internet address type of the remote server. Only ipv4(1) type is supported.

fileCopyServerInetAddress.name: fileCopyServerInetAddress
fileCopyServerInetAddress.description: Internet address of the remote server.

fileCopyServerUserName.name: fileCopyServerUserName
fileCopyServerUserName.description: Login user name for the remote server. When this variable is empty, the system will use 'anonymous' as user name to log in to the remote server.

fileCopyServerPassword.name: fileCopyServerPassword
fileCopyServerPassword.description: Login password for the remote server. This variable can only be written. When this variable is read, it always returns a zero-length string.

fileInfoTable.name: fileInfoTable
fileInfoTable.description: This table contain the information of the file system; we can also perform the delete, set startup file operation.

fileInfoUnitID.name: fileInfoUnitID
fileInfoUnitID.description: The switch unit in a stacking system, in a non-stacking system, this value is always 1.

fileInfoFileName.name: fileInfoFileName
fileInfoFileName.description: The file Name of the file System in the device.

fileInfoFileType.name: fileInfoFileType
fileInfoFileType.description: The file type of the file System in the device.

fileInfoIsStartUp.name: fileInfoIsStartUp
fileInfoIsStartUp.description: This flag indicate whether this file is a startup file. Set this object to true(1) to indicate that this is a startup file. Setting this object to false(2) is a invalid operation.

fileInfoFileSize.name: fileInfoFileSize
fileInfoFileSize.description: The sizes( in bytes) of the file.

fileInfoCreationTime.name: fileInfoCreationTime
fileInfoCreationTime.description: The creation time of the file, This is a text string in the following form, based on Unix: 'Mmm _d hh:mm:ss yyyy'. 'Mmm' are the first three letters of the English name of the month. '_d' is the day of month. A single-digit day is preceded by a space. 'hh:mm:ss' is a 24-hour representations of hours, minutes, and seconds. A single-digit hour is preceded by a zero. 'yyyy' is the four-digit year. An example is: 'Jan 1 02:03:04 2002'.

fileInfoDelete.name: fileInfoDelete
fileInfoDelete.description: Write this object to delete(2) to delete a file, when read, this always return noDelete(1).

fileAutoDownloadResultTable.name: fileAutoDownloadResultTable
fileAutoDownloadResultTable.description: This table contains file auto download result information.

fileAutoDownloadResultUnitID.name: fileAutoDownloadResultUnitID
fileAutoDownloadResultUnitID.description: The switch unit in a stacking system, in a non-stacking system, this value is always 1.

fileAutoDownloadResultAction.name: fileAutoDownloadResultAction
fileAutoDownloadResultAction.description: The status of the auto download action. value copying(2) will be obtained if the auto download action is currently processing, or value notCopying(1) will be obtained if no auto download action is currently processing. You can check the download result through the fileAutoDownloadResultStatus object after the download action has finished. Please note that this object is read-only, since the auto download action is triggered automatically by the system when an image file or a config file is set as startup setting through the fileInfoIsStartUp, restartOpCodeFile or restartConfigFile objects, but not set by the user manually through this fileAutoDownloadResultAction object.

fileAutoDownloadResultStatus.name: fileAutoDownloadResultStatus
fileAutoDownloadResultStatus.description: The last auto download result status. value fileCopyUnknown(18) will be obtained if no download action has been performed before. The listed values are identical to fileCopyStatus.

dnsDomainLookup.name: dnsDomainLookup
dnsDomainLookup.description: To enable the IP Domain Naming System (DNS)-based host name-to-address translation.

dnsDomainName.name: dnsDomainName
dnsDomainName.description: To define a default domain name to complete unqualified host names (names without a dotted-decimal domain name).

dnsCacheTable.name: dnsCacheTable
dnsCacheTable.description: To display the RRs in DNS cache.

dnsCacheEntry.name: dnsCacheEntry
dnsCacheEntry.description: A conceptual row for the dnsCacheTable.

dnsCacheFlag.name: dnsCacheFlag
dnsCacheFlag.description: Always get 4, means this record is unreliable.

dnsCacheInetAddressType.name: dnsCacheInetAddressType
dnsCacheInetAddressType.description: Indicates the type of address denoted in dnsHostAddrInetAddress type. Only ipv4(1) and ipv6(2) types are supported.

dnsCacheInetAddress.name: dnsCacheInetAddress
dnsCacheInetAddress.description: IP address of DNS cache item.

dnsHostTable.name: dnsHostTable
dnsHostTable.description: The conceptual table of dnsHostEntry. The dnsHostTable and dnsHostAddrTable are used to define static host name-to-address mapping.

dnsHostEntry.name: dnsHostEntry
dnsHostEntry.description: A conceptual row for the dnsHostTable.

dnsHostStatus.name: dnsHostStatus
dnsHostStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

dnsHostAddrTable.name: dnsHostAddrTable
dnsHostAddrTable.description: The conceptual table of dnsHostAddrEntry. The dnsHostTable and dnsHostAddrTable are used to define static host name-to-address mapping.

dnsHostAddrEntry.name: dnsHostAddrEntry
dnsHostAddrEntry.description: A conceptual row for the dnsHostAddrTable.

dnsHostAddrInetAddressType.name: dnsHostAddrInetAddressType
dnsHostAddrInetAddressType.description: Indicates the type of address denoted in dnsHostAddrInetAddress type. Only ipv4(1), ipv6(2) and ipv6z(4) type are supported.

dnsHostAddrInetAddress.name: dnsHostAddrInetAddress
dnsHostAddrInetAddress.description: Specifies the address of the host. Adding one address to two different hosts is not allowed.

dnsHostAddrStatus.name: dnsHostAddrStatus
dnsHostAddrStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

dnsDomainListTable.name: dnsDomainListTable
dnsDomainListTable.description: This table defines a list of default domain names to complete unqualified host names.

dnsDomainListEntry.name: dnsDomainListEntry
dnsDomainListEntry.description: A conceptual row for the dnsDomainListTable.

dnsDomainListStatus.name: dnsDomainListStatus
dnsDomainListStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

dnsNameServerInetTable.name: dnsNameServerInetTable
dnsNameServerInetTable.description: Specifies the address of one or more name servers to use for name and address resolution.

dnsNameServerInetAddressType.name: dnsNameServerInetAddressType
dnsNameServerInetAddressType.description: Type of address. Only ipv4(1), ipv6(2) and ipv6z(4) types are supported.

dnsNameServerInetStatus.name: dnsNameServerInetStatus
dnsNameServerInetStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

fileAutoUpgradeOpCodeStatus.name: fileAutoUpgradeOpCodeStatus
fileAutoUpgradeOpCodeStatus.description: Set this variable to enabled(1) to enable the device to automatically upgrade the current software image when a new version is detected. Set this variable to disabled(2) to disable this feature.

fileAutoUpgradeOpCodePath.name: fileAutoUpgradeOpCodePath
fileAutoUpgradeOpCodePath.description: The URL (Universal Resource Location) of the image file location for automatic upgrades. The URL schema can be set to TFTP. The Hostname is the IP address of the server. The last character of the URL is always a '/' and the filename must not be included in the URL.

fileAutoUpgradeOpCodeFileName.name: fileAutoUpgradeOpCodeFileName
fileAutoUpgradeOpCodeFileName.description: The file name of the image file.

mcastStormTable.name: mcastStormTable
mcastStormTable.description: Table to manage the control of multicast storms for ports.

mcastStormIfIndex.name: mcastStormIfIndex
mcastStormIfIndex.description: The port and the trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mcastStormStatus.name: mcastStormStatus
mcastStormStatus.description: Whether multicast storm protection is enabled.

mcastStormOctetRate.name: mcastStormOctetRate
mcastStormOctetRate.description: Multicast storm threshold as kilobit per second. If this entry is for a trunk, this is the value for each member port. The range is 64 to 1000000.

bcastStormTable.name: bcastStormTable
bcastStormTable.description: Table to manage the control of broadcast storms for ports.

bcastStormIfIndex.name: bcastStormIfIndex
bcastStormIfIndex.description: The port and the trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

bcastStormStatus.name: bcastStormStatus
bcastStormStatus.description: Whether broadcast storm protection is enabled.

bcastStormOctetRate.name: bcastStormOctetRate
bcastStormOctetRate.description: Broadcast storm threshold as kilobit per second. If this entry is for a trunk, this is the value for each member port. The range is 64 to 1000000.

unknownUcastStormTable.name: unknownUcastStormTable
unknownUcastStormTable.description: Table to manage the unknown unicast storm control.

unknownUcastStormIfIndex.name: unknownUcastStormIfIndex
unknownUcastStormIfIndex.description: The port or trunk interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

unknownUcastStormStatus.name: unknownUcastStormStatus
unknownUcastStormStatus.description: The parameter indicates that the unknown unicast storm protection is enabled/disabled.

unknownUcastStormOctetRate.name: unknownUcastStormOctetRate
unknownUcastStormOctetRate.description: The parameter indicates the packet rate(kilobit per second) of the storm protection. The range is 64 to 1000000.

atcBcastStormTcApplyTime.name: atcBcastStormTcApplyTime
atcBcastStormTcApplyTime.description: The parameter indicates the timing when the ATC (Auto Traffic Control) is activated after the broadcast traffic being detected as the storm.

atcBcastStormTcReleaseTime.name: atcBcastStormTcReleaseTime
atcBcastStormTcReleaseTime.description: The parameter indicates the timing when the ATC is released after the broadcast traffic being detected as no storm.

atcBcastStormTable.name: atcBcastStormTable
atcBcastStormTable.description: The table contains the Auto Traffic Control configuration and the status for broadcast traffic.

atcBcastStormEntry.name: atcBcastStormEntry
atcBcastStormEntry.description: The conceptual row of the table.

atcBcastStormIfIndex.name: atcBcastStormIfIndex
atcBcastStormIfIndex.description: The specified port on which the ATC is applied.

atcBcastStormEnable.name: atcBcastStormEnable
atcBcastStormEnable.description: The parameter indicates whether the ATC of the broadcast traffic is applied.

atcBcastStormAutoRelease.name: atcBcastStormAutoRelease
atcBcastStormAutoRelease.description: The parameter indicates whether the Auto-Release feature of ATC is applied.

atcBcastStormSampleType.name: atcBcastStormSampleType
atcBcastStormSampleType.description: The parameter indicates the unit of traffic rate and threshold.

atcBcastStormCurrentTrafficRate.name: atcBcastStormCurrentTrafficRate
atcBcastStormCurrentTrafficRate.description: The parameter indicates the current broadcast traffic rate.

atcBcastStormAlarmFireThreshold.name: atcBcastStormAlarmFireThreshold
atcBcastStormAlarmFireThreshold.description: The parameter indicates that if the current broadcast traffic rate exceeds the specified threshold, it will be treated as the storm.

atcBcastStormAlarmClearThreshold.name: atcBcastStormAlarmClearThreshold
atcBcastStormAlarmClearThreshold.description: The parameter indicates that if the current broadcast traffic falls below the specified threshold it will be treated as the normal traffic.

atcBcastStormTcAction.name: atcBcastStormTcAction
atcBcastStormTcAction.description: The parameter indicates the protecting action which ATC will applied to the specified port.

atcBcastStormAlarmFireTrapStatus.name: atcBcastStormAlarmFireTrapStatus
atcBcastStormAlarmFireTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the broadcast storm has been detected.

atcBcastStormAlarmClearTrapStatus.name: atcBcastStormAlarmClearTrapStatus
atcBcastStormAlarmClearTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the broadcast storm has been detected as the normal traffic.

atcBcastStormTcApplyTrapStatus.name: atcBcastStormTcApplyTrapStatus
atcBcastStormTcApplyTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the ATC is activated.

atcBcastStormTcReleaseTrapStatus.name: atcBcastStormTcReleaseTrapStatus
atcBcastStormTcReleaseTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the ATC is released.

atcMcastStormTcApplyTime.name: atcMcastStormTcApplyTime
atcMcastStormTcApplyTime.description: The parameter indicates the timing when the ATC (Auto Traffic Control) is activated after the broadcast traffic being detected as the storm.

atcMcastStormTcReleaseTime.name: atcMcastStormTcReleaseTime
atcMcastStormTcReleaseTime.description: The parameter indicates the timing when the ATC is released after the broadcast traffic being detected as no storm.

atcMcastStormTable.name: atcMcastStormTable
atcMcastStormTable.description: The table contains the Auto Traffic Control configuration and the status for mulicast traffic.

atcMcastStormEntry.name: atcMcastStormEntry
atcMcastStormEntry.description: The conceptual row of the table.

atcMcastStormIfIndex.name: atcMcastStormIfIndex
atcMcastStormIfIndex.description: The specified port on which the ATC is applied.

atcMcastStormEnable.name: atcMcastStormEnable
atcMcastStormEnable.description: The parameter indicates whether the ATC of the mulicast traffic is applied.

atcMcastStormAutoRelease.name: atcMcastStormAutoRelease
atcMcastStormAutoRelease.description: The parameter indicates whether the Auto-Release feature of ATC is applied.

atcMcastStormSampleType.name: atcMcastStormSampleType
atcMcastStormSampleType.description: The parameter indicates the unit of traffic rate and threshold.

atcMcastStormCurrentTrafficRate.name: atcMcastStormCurrentTrafficRate
atcMcastStormCurrentTrafficRate.description: The parameter indicates the current mulicast traffic rate.

atcMcastStormAlarmFireThreshold.name: atcMcastStormAlarmFireThreshold
atcMcastStormAlarmFireThreshold.description: The parameter indicates that if the current mulicast traffic rate exceeds the specified threshold, it will be treated as the storm.

atcMcastStormAlarmClearThreshold.name: atcMcastStormAlarmClearThreshold
atcMcastStormAlarmClearThreshold.description: The parameter indicates that if the current mulicast traffic falls below the specified threshold it will be treated as the normal traffic.

atcMcastStormTcAction.name: atcMcastStormTcAction
atcMcastStormTcAction.description: The parameter indicates the protecting action which ATC will applied to the specified port.

atcMcastStormAlarmFireTrapStatus.name: atcMcastStormAlarmFireTrapStatus
atcMcastStormAlarmFireTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the mulicast storm has been detected.

atcMcastStormAlarmClearTrapStatus.name: atcMcastStormAlarmClearTrapStatus
atcMcastStormAlarmClearTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the mulicast storm has been detected as the normal traffic.

atcMcastStormTcApplyTrapStatus.name: atcMcastStormTcApplyTrapStatus
atcMcastStormTcApplyTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the ATC is activated.

atcMcastStormTcReleaseTrapStatus.name: atcMcastStormTcReleaseTrapStatus
atcMcastStormTcReleaseTrapStatus.description: The parameter indicates whether the trap has to be sent when the ATC is released.

cpuCurrentUti.name: cpuCurrentUti
cpuCurrentUti.description: The current CPU utilization in percent in the past 5 seconds.

cpuStatMaxUti.name: cpuStatMaxUti
cpuStatMaxUti.description: The maximum CPU utilization in percent in the past 60 seconds.

cpuStatAvgUti.name: cpuStatAvgUti
cpuStatAvgUti.description: The average CPU utilization in percent in the past 60 seconds.

cpuPeakTime.name: cpuPeakTime
cpuPeakTime.description: The time when the CPU utilization reaches cpuUtiRisingThreshold in the format of 'Mmm _d hh:mm:ss yyyy' as defined in sysCurrentTime of this MIB.

cpuPeakDuration.name: cpuPeakDuration
cpuPeakDuration.description: The duration from the CPU utilization reaches cpuUtiRisingThreshold to reaches cpuUtiFallingThreshold, in seconds.

cpuUtiRisingThreshold.name: cpuUtiRisingThreshold
cpuUtiRisingThreshold.description: The rising threshold of the cpu utilization.

cpuUtiFallingThreshold.name: cpuUtiFallingThreshold
cpuUtiFallingThreshold.description: The falling threshold of the cpu utilization.

memoryTotal.name: memoryTotal
memoryTotal.description: The total amount of the memory in kilobytes.

memoryAllocated.name: memoryAllocated
memoryAllocated.description: The amount of the memory allocated in kilobytes.

memoryFreed.name: memoryFreed
memoryFreed.description: The amount of the free memory in kilobytes.

memoryFreedInPercent.name: memoryFreedInPercent
memoryFreedInPercent.description: the memory freed in proportion to the total memory.

memoryUtiRisingThreshold.name: memoryUtiRisingThreshold
memoryUtiRisingThreshold.description: The rising threshold of the memory utilization.

memoryUtiFallingThreshold.name: memoryUtiFallingThreshold
memoryUtiFallingThreshold.description: The falling threshold of the memory utilization.

taskCpuTable.name: taskCpuTable
taskCpuTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information describing the CPU utilization of each task.

taskCpuEntry.name: taskCpuEntry
taskCpuEntry.description: An entry in the table, describing the CPU utilization of one task.

taskCpuCurrentUti.name: taskCpuCurrentUti
taskCpuCurrentUti.description: The current CPU utilization in hundredths of a percent in the past 5 seconds.

taskCpuStatMaxUti.name: taskCpuStatMaxUti
taskCpuStatMaxUti.description: The maximum CPU utilization in hundredths of a percent in the past 60 seconds.

taskCpuStatAvgUti.name: taskCpuStatAvgUti
taskCpuStatAvgUti.description: The average CPU utilization in hundredths of a percent in the past 60 seconds.

mvrForwardingPriority.name: mvrForwardingPriority
mvrForwardingPriority.description: Configure MVR multicast stream forwarding priority. If value is 65535, it means the priority is disabled.

mvrDomainTable.name: mvrDomainTable
mvrDomainTable.description: The table for configuring the MVR port.

mvrDomainEntry.name: mvrDomainEntry
mvrDomainEntry.description: The entry for configuring the MVR Domain.

mvrDomainId.name: mvrDomainId
mvrDomainId.description: Speicfies which MVR domain to configure.

mvrDomainStatus.name: mvrDomainStatus
mvrDomainStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable MVR(Multicast VLAN Registration) on the device.

mvrDomainRunningStatus.name: mvrDomainRunningStatus
mvrDomainRunningStatus.description: Describes the running status of MVR (Multicast VLAN Registration) to the switch. A value of active(1) indicates that all necessary conditions in the MVR environment are satisfied. A value of inactive(2) indicates that some necessary conditions in the MVR environment are not satisfied.

mvrDomainVlanId.name: mvrDomainVlanId
mvrDomainVlanId.description: To set VLAN for MVR.The VLAN identified by a particular value of this index is the same VLAN as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB.

mvrDomainUpstreamSourceIp.name: mvrDomainUpstreamSourceIp
mvrDomainUpstreamSourceIp.description: Set the source IP address which MVR will carry in IP header when send IGMP packet to upstream router through MVR source port.

mvrDomainPortTable.name: mvrDomainPortTable
mvrDomainPortTable.description: The table for configuring the MVR port.

mvrDomainPortEntry.name: mvrDomainPortEntry
mvrDomainPortEntry.description: The entry for configuring the MVR port.

mvrPortDomainId.name: mvrPortDomainId
mvrPortDomainId.description: Speicfies which MVR domain to configure.

mvrDomainIfIndex.name: mvrDomainIfIndex
mvrDomainIfIndex.description: The port interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mvrDomainPortType.name: mvrDomainPortType
mvrDomainPortType.description: For configuring the MVR port type. To disable the MVR port type, use the none(0).

mvrDomainPortImmediateLeave.name: mvrDomainPortImmediateLeave
mvrDomainPortImmediateLeave.description: To enable immediate leave on MVR port.

mvrDomainPortActive.name: mvrDomainPortActive
mvrDomainPortActive.description: To indicate if the port is associated with the MVR group. If the port is the MVR receiver port or the MVR source port in MVR vlan, the status is active(1); otherwise the status is inactive(2).

mvrDomainPortImmediateLeaveByHostIp.name: mvrDomainPortImmediateLeaveByHostIp
mvrDomainPortImmediateLeaveByHostIp.description: To enable immediate leave by host IP on MVR port.

mvrProfileCtlTable.name: mvrProfileCtlTable
mvrProfileCtlTable.description: The entry for configuring the MVR profile.

mvrProfileCtlEntry.name: mvrProfileCtlEntry
mvrProfileCtlEntry.description: The entry for configuring the MVR profile.

mvrProfileCtlId.name: mvrProfileCtlId
mvrProfileCtlId.description: Profile ID to index which MVR profile

mvrProfileName.name: mvrProfileName
mvrProfileName.description: MVR Profile name which identify a group range. NOTE: All mvrProfileCtlEntry use the same buffer to temply store the mvrProfileName before mvrProfileCtlAction really creat the profile.

mvrProfileCtlAction.name: mvrProfileCtlAction
mvrProfileCtlAction.description: Set this object to create(2) to create profile. Set this object to destory(3) to delete profile. When the action is complete, this object becomes noAction(1).

mvrProfileGroupCtlTable.name: mvrProfileGroupCtlTable
mvrProfileGroupCtlTable.description: The entry for configuring the MVR group ranges for MVR profile.

mvrProfileGroupCtlEntry.name: mvrProfileGroupCtlEntry
mvrProfileGroupCtlEntry.description: The entry for configuring the group ranges on MVR profile.

mvrProfileGropuCtlProfileId.name: mvrProfileGropuCtlProfileId
mvrProfileGropuCtlProfileId.description: Profile ID to index which MVR profile

mvrProfileGroupCtlId.name: mvrProfileGroupCtlId
mvrProfileGroupCtlId.description: Profile ID to index which group range in MVR profile

mvrProfileGroupStartIPAddress.name: mvrProfileGroupStartIPAddress

dhcpSnoopEnable.name: dhcpSnoopEnable
dhcpSnoopEnable.description: This object indicates whether the DHCP Snooping feature is enabled.

dhcpSnoopVerifyMacAddressEnable.name: dhcpSnoopVerifyMacAddressEnable
dhcpSnoopVerifyMacAddressEnable.description: This object indicates whether DHCP Snooping Mac address verification is enabled.

dhcpSnoopInformationOptionEnable.name: dhcpSnoopInformationOptionEnable
dhcpSnoopInformationOptionEnable.description: This object indicates whether the DHCP snooping information option(option 82) feature is enabled.

dhcpSnoopInformationOptionPolicy.name: dhcpSnoopInformationOptionPolicy
dhcpSnoopInformationOptionPolicy.description: This object indicates which reforwarding policy shall be used for DHCP snooping information option(option 82). A value of drop(1) means to drop the DHCP request packet which has the information option(option 82). A value of keep(2) means to keep the existing information option(option 82) of the DHCP request packet. A value of replace(3), which is the default value, means to replace the existing information option(option 82) of the DHCP request packet.

dhcpSnoopBindingsTableCtlAction.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsTableCtlAction
dhcpSnoopBindingsTableCtlAction.description: Set this to store(2) to store DHCP snooping binding entries to flash. Set this to clear(3) to clear DHCP snooping binding entries from flash. noAction(1) will always be obtained when reading this variable.

dhcpSnoopLimitRate.name: dhcpSnoopLimitRate
dhcpSnoopLimitRate.description: This object indicates the limit rate that DHCP packet redirected to CPU. Set this to 0 means no rate limit for DHCP packet.

dhcpSnoopVlanConfigTable.name: dhcpSnoopVlanConfigTable
dhcpSnoopVlanConfigTable.description: A table contains DHCP Snooping configurations of existing VLANs.

dhcpSnoopVlanConfigEntry.name: dhcpSnoopVlanConfigEntry
dhcpSnoopVlanConfigEntry.description: An instance contains the configuration to enable or disable DHCP Snooping at each existing VLAN.

dhcpSnoopVlanIndex.name: dhcpSnoopVlanIndex
dhcpSnoopVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID on which DHCP Snooping feature is configured.

dhcpSnoopVlanEnable.name: dhcpSnoopVlanEnable
dhcpSnoopVlanEnable.description: This object indicates whether DHCP Snooping is enabled in this VLAN.

dhcpSnoopPortConfigTable.name: dhcpSnoopPortConfigTable
dhcpSnoopPortConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state of each port or trunk for DHCP Snooping purpose.

dhcpSnoopPortConfigEntry.name: dhcpSnoopPortConfigEntry
dhcpSnoopPortConfigEntry.description: An instance contains the configuration to enable or disable trust state of each port or trunk for DHCP Snooping purpose.

dhcpSnoopPortIfIndex.name: dhcpSnoopPortIfIndex
dhcpSnoopPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the port or trunk.

dhcpSnoopPortTrustEnable.name: dhcpSnoopPortTrustEnable
dhcpSnoopPortTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the port or trunk is trusted for DHCP Snooping purpose.

dhcpSnoopBindingsTable.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsTable
dhcpSnoopBindingsTable.description: A table contains the DHCP bindings information learnt by the device.

dhcpSnoopBindingsEntry.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsEntry
dhcpSnoopBindingsEntry.description: An instance contains the Mac address, IP address type, IP address, VLAN number, interface number, leased time and status.

dhcpSnoopBindingsVlanIndex.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsVlanIndex
dhcpSnoopBindingsVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN which a DHCP client host belongs to.

dhcpSnoopBindingsMacAddress.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsMacAddress
dhcpSnoopBindingsMacAddress.description: This object indicates the MAC address of a DHCP client host.

dhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType
dhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType.description: This object indicates the type of IP address denoted in dhcpSnoopBindingsIpAddress type.

dhcpSnoopBindingsEntryType.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsEntryType
dhcpSnoopBindingsEntryType.description: This object indicates that this binding is obtained from dynamically learning or is a static configuraion.

dhcpSnoopBindingsIpAddress.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsIpAddress
dhcpSnoopBindingsIpAddress.description: This object indicates the allocated IP address of a DHCP client host.

dhcpSnoopBindingsPortIfIndex.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsPortIfIndex
dhcpSnoopBindingsPortIfIndex.description: This object indicates the port or trunk where a DHCP client host connects to.

dhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime.name: dhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime
dhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime.description: This object indicates the leased time of this DHCP bindings.

dhcpSnoopTotalForwardedPkts.name: dhcpSnoopTotalForwardedPkts
dhcpSnoopTotalForwardedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of packets subjected to DHCP Snooping is forwarded.

dhcpSnoopUntrustedPortDroppedPkts.name: dhcpSnoopUntrustedPortDroppedPkts
dhcpSnoopUntrustedPortDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the number of packets subjected to DHCP Snooping is dropped because they come from untrusted interface.

clusterEnable.name: clusterEnable
clusterEnable.description: Enables or disables clustering on the device.

clusterCommanderEnable.name: clusterCommanderEnable
clusterCommanderEnable.description: Enables or disables the device as commander in a cluster.

clusterIpPool.name: clusterIpPool
clusterIpPool.description: The start internal IP address of a cluster pool.

clusterClearCandidateTable.name: clusterClearCandidateTable
clusterClearCandidateTable.description: Setting this object to clear(2) starts to clear the candidate table.

clusterRole.name: clusterRole
clusterRole.description: The current role of the device in a cluster. commander(1) : The switch is the controlling device in a cluster. candidate(2) : The switch has been discovered by the commander, but it has not been manually configured for access from the commander. activeMember(3): The switch has been manually configured for access from the commander and it is active in the cluster. disabled(5) : The switch has clustering disabled.

clusterMemberCount.name: clusterMemberCount
clusterMemberCount.description: The total number of members in a cluster.

clusterCandidateCount.name: clusterCandidateCount
clusterCandidateCount.description: The total number of candidates in a cluster.

clusterCandidateEntry.name: clusterCandidateEntry
clusterCandidateEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the information of the candidate.

clusterCandidateMacAddr.name: clusterCandidateMacAddr
clusterCandidateMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the candidate.

clusterCandidateRole.name: clusterCandidateRole
clusterCandidateRole.description: The role of the candidate. candidate(2) : The switch is discovered by the commander, but it has not been manually configured for access from the commander. activeMember(3) : The switch is manually configured for access from the commander and it is active in the cluster. inactiveMember(4): The switch is manually configured for access from the commander, but it is inactive in the cluster.

clusterMemberEntry.name: clusterMemberEntry
clusterMemberEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the information of the member.

clusterMemberMacAddr.name: clusterMemberMacAddr
clusterMemberMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the member.

clusterMemberActive.name: clusterMemberActive
clusterMemberActive.description: The active status of the member. activeMember(3) : The switch is manually configured for access from the commander and it is active in the cluster. inactiveMember(4): The switch is manually configured for access from the commander, but it is inactive in the cluster.

clusterMemberAddCtlMacAddr.name: clusterMemberAddCtlMacAddr
clusterMemberAddCtlMacAddr.description: The MAC address of the device associated with clusterMemberAddCtlAction.

clusterMemberAddCtlId.name: clusterMemberAddCtlId
clusterMemberAddCtlId.description: The member id associated with clusterMemberAddCtlAction.

clusterMemberAddCtlAction.name: clusterMemberAddCtlAction
clusterMemberAddCtlAction.description: Adds the device to members that can be accessed from the commander. The MAC of the device is the current value of clusterMemberAddCtlMacAddr and the assigned member ID is the current value of clusterMemberAddCtlId. Set this object to add(2) to begin adding the member.

clusterMemberRemoveCtlId.name: clusterMemberRemoveCtlId
clusterMemberRemoveCtlId.description: The member ID associated with clusterMemberRemoveCtlAction.

clusterMemberRemoveCtlAction.name: clusterMemberRemoveCtlAction
clusterMemberRemoveCtlAction.description: Removes the device from members that can be accessed from the commander. The member ID is the current value of clusterMemberRemoveCtlId. Set this object to remove(2) to begin removing the member.

ipSrcGuardConfigTable.name: ipSrcGuardConfigTable
ipSrcGuardConfigTable.description: A table contains the configurations to enable or disable IP Source Guard at each port or trunk.

ipSrcGuardConfigEntry.name: ipSrcGuardConfigEntry
ipSrcGuardConfigEntry.description: An instance contains the configuration to enable or disable IP Source Guard at each port or trunk.

ipSrcGuardPortIfIndex.name: ipSrcGuardPortIfIndex
ipSrcGuardPortIfIndex.description: This object idents the port or trunk which is capable of IP Source Guard feature.

ipSrcGuardMode.name: ipSrcGuardMode
ipSrcGuardMode.description: This object indicates whether Ip Source Guard is enabled at this interface. If the value equals 0, it means Ip Source Guard is disabled. If the value equals 1, it means Ip Source Guard is enabled, and packets are filtered by checking source ip. If the value equals 2, it means Ip Source Guard is enabled and packets are filtered by checking source ip and source mac.

ipSrcGuardTableMode.name: ipSrcGuardTableMode
ipSrcGuardTableMode.description: This object indicates the table mode IP Source Guard select. If the value equals 1, it means IP Source Guard choose ACL mode to filter packet. If the value equals 2, it means IP Source Guard choose MAC mode to filter packet.

ipSrcGuardAclMaxBinding.name: ipSrcGuardAclMaxBinding
ipSrcGuardAclMaxBinding.description: This object indicates the maximum binding number in ACL mode. The number of IP Source Guard bindings in ACL mode will be limited by this value.

ipSrcGuardMacMaxBinding.name: ipSrcGuardMacMaxBinding
ipSrcGuardMacMaxBinding.description: This object indicates the maximum binding numer in MAC mode. The number of IP Source Guard bindings in MAC mode will be limited by this value.

ipSrcGuardAclTable.name: ipSrcGuardAclTable
ipSrcGuardAclTable.description: A table contains the IP Source Guard ACL binding information learned by the device or configured by the user.

ipSrcGuardAclEntry.name: ipSrcGuardAclEntry

ipSrcGuardAclBindingIpAddress.name: ipSrcGuardAclBindingIpAddress

ipSrcGuardAclBindingMacAddress.name: ipSrcGuardAclBindingMacAddress
ipSrcGuardAclBindingMacAddress.description: This object indicates the MAC address of a ACL binding entry.

ipSrcGuardAclBindingEntryType.name: ipSrcGuardAclBindingEntryType
ipSrcGuardAclBindingEntryType.description: This object indicates that this binding is obtained from dynamically learning or is a static configuraion.

ipSrcGuardAclBindingVlanIndex.name: ipSrcGuardAclBindingVlanIndex
ipSrcGuardAclBindingVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN which a ACL binding belongs to.

ipSrcGuardAclBindingPortIfIndex.name: ipSrcGuardAclBindingPortIfIndex
ipSrcGuardAclBindingPortIfIndex.description: This object indicates the port or trunk where a ACL binding associated.

ipSrcGuardAclBindingStatus.name: ipSrcGuardAclBindingStatus
ipSrcGuardAclBindingStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row entry. This object issued to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device.

ipSrcGuardMacTable.name: ipSrcGuardMacTable
ipSrcGuardMacTable.description: A table contains the IP Source Guard MAC binding information learned by the device or configured by the user.

ipSrcGuardMacEntry.name: ipSrcGuardMacEntry
ipSrcGuardMacEntry.description: An instance contains the IP address, Mac address, VLAN number, interface number and status.

ipSrcGuardMacBindingMacAddress.name: ipSrcGuardMacBindingMacAddress
ipSrcGuardMacBindingMacAddress.description: This object indicates the MAC address of a MAC binding entry.

ipSrcGuardMacBindingIpAddress.name: ipSrcGuardMacBindingIpAddress
ipSrcGuardMacBindingIpAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address of a MAC binding entry.

ipSrcGuardMacBindingStartVlan.name: ipSrcGuardMacBindingStartVlan
ipSrcGuardMacBindingStartVlan.description: This object indicates the start VLAN which a MAC binding belongs to.

ipSrcGuardMacBindingEndVlan.name: ipSrcGuardMacBindingEndVlan
ipSrcGuardMacBindingEndVlan.description: This object indicates the end VLAN which a MAC binding belongs to.

ipSrcGuardMacBindingPortList.name: ipSrcGuardMacBindingPortList
ipSrcGuardMacBindingPortList.description: This object indicates the port or trunk where a MAC binding associated.

ipSrcGuardMacBindingStatus.name: ipSrcGuardMacBindingStatus
ipSrcGuardMacBindingStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row entry. This object issued to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device.

upnpStatus.name: upnpStatus
upnpStatus.description: Sets enabled(1) to enable UPnP device, and sets disabled(2) to disable UPnP device.

upnpAdvertisingDuration.name: upnpAdvertisingDuration
upnpAdvertisingDuration.description: The interval(in seconds) between available UPnP device advertising messages sent by the switch.

upnpTtl.name: upnpTtl
upnpTtl.description: Specifies the TTL value of the UPnP advertising messages sent by the switch. When the TTL value is greater than 1, it is possible to send UPnP advertising messages to traverse multiple routers; at the same time, the UPnP device will send an IGMP Join message to the traverse multiple routers so that the routers will forward multicast messages to the UPnP device.

oamPortClearStatTable.name: oamPortClearStatTable
oamPortClearStatTable.description: A table contains the information of clear OAM statistics at each port.

oamPortClearStatEntry.name: oamPortClearStatEntry
oamPortClearStatEntry.description: An entry contains the information of clear OAM statistics at each port.

oamPortClearStatIndex.name: oamPortClearStatIndex
oamPortClearStatIndex.description: This object shows the ifIndex value of the port excluding trunk.

oamClearStatistics.name: oamClearStatistics
oamClearStatistics.description: This variable is used to clear the counters for OAM. Set this variable to clear(2) to perform the clear operation, noClear(1) will always be displayed when reading this variable.

oamLoopbackTable.name: oamLoopbackTable
