oamLoopbackEntry.name: oamLoopbackEntry
oamLoopbackEntry.description: Entry for OAM remote loopback test.

oamLoopbackTestIfIndex.name: oamLoopbackTestIfIndex
oamLoopbackTestIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the port (excluding trunk and trunk members). The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

oamLoopbackTestPacketNumber.name: oamLoopbackTestPacketNumber
oamLoopbackTestPacketNumber.description: Setting the packet number when performing loopback test.

oamLoopbackTestPacketSize.name: oamLoopbackTestPacketSize
oamLoopbackTestPacketSize.description: Setting the packet size when performing loopback test.

oamLoopbackTestAction.name: oamLoopbackTestAction
oamLoopbackTestAction.description: Setting this object to test(2) to begin the loopback test. This object will be noTest(1) when the loopback test is canceled or the loopback test has finished.

oamLoopbackTestResultTx.name: oamLoopbackTestResultTx
oamLoopbackTestResultTx.description: A count of the the total number of loopback frames transmitted at last loopback test on this interface.

oamLoopbackTestResultRx.name: oamLoopbackTestResultRx
oamLoopbackTestResultRx.description: A count of the the total number of loopback frames received at last loopback test on this interface.

oamLoopbackTestResultLossRate.name: oamLoopbackTestResultLossRate
oamLoopbackTestResultLossRate.description: Packet loss rate of this loopback test operation in hundredths of a percent. This variable is calculated by oamLoopbackTestResultRx and oamLoopbackTestResultTx.

oamPrivateEventLogType.name: oamPrivateEventLogType
oamPrivateEventLogType.description: This object augments the dot3OamEventLogType of dot3OamEventLogTable in DOT3-OAM-MIB. When the OUI (dot3OamEventLogOui) is 0x0012CF, the following event types are defined: connectionToRemoteDeviceUp(1001), connectionToRemoteDeviceDown(1002), linkFaultClear(1003), dyingGaspEventClear(1004), criticalLinkEventClear(1005) All these events are not threshold crossing events.

oamPortClearEventLogTable.name: oamPortClearEventLogTable
oamPortClearEventLogTable.description: A table containing the information of clear OAM event log at each port.

oamPortClearEventLogEntry.name: oamPortClearEventLogEntry
oamPortClearEventLogEntry.description: An entry containing the information of clear OAM event log at each port.

oamPortClearEventLogIndex.name: oamPortClearEventLogIndex
oamPortClearEventLogIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the port (excluding trunk and trunk members). The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

oamPortClearEventLogAction.name: oamPortClearEventLogAction
oamPortClearEventLogAction.description: This variable is used to clear the event log for OAM. Set this variable to clear(2) to perform the clear operation. noClear(1) will always be displayed when reading this variable.

daiGlobalStatus.name: daiGlobalStatus
daiGlobalStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable dynamic ARP inspection. Set disabled(2) to disable dynamic ARP inspection.

daiGlobalSrcMacValidation.name: daiGlobalSrcMacValidation
daiGlobalSrcMacValidation.description: Set enabled(1) to enable validation of source MAC address. Set disabled(2) to disable validation of source MAC address.

daiGlobalDestMacValidation.name: daiGlobalDestMacValidation
daiGlobalDestMacValidation.description: Set enabled(1) to enable validation of destination MAC address. Set disabled(2) to disable validation of destination MAC address.

daiGlobalIpAddrValidation.name: daiGlobalIpAddrValidation
daiGlobalIpAddrValidation.description: Set enabled(1) to enable validation of IP address. Set disabled(2) to disable validation of IP address.

daiGlobalLogNumber.name: daiGlobalLogNumber
daiGlobalLogNumber.description: The number of log buffers for saving log message. The value 0 means not generating system messages.

daiGlobalLogInterval.name: daiGlobalLogInterval
daiGlobalLogInterval.description: The value of the time interval for saving log messages.

daiGlobalAdditionalValidStatus.name: daiGlobalAdditionalValidStatus
daiGlobalAdditionalValidStatus.description: The vaule of this object is disabled(2) when the status of daiGlobalSrcMacValidation, daiGlobalDestMacValidation, and daiGlobalIpAddrValidation are disabled; enabled(1) when one or more of these variables are enabled.

daiVlanTable.name: daiVlanTable
daiVlanTable.description: A table contains dynamic ARP inspection configurations for existing VLANs.

daiVlanEntry.name: daiVlanEntry
daiVlanEntry.description: An instance containing the configuration of dynamic ARP inspection for each existing VLAN.

daiVlanIndex.name: daiVlanIndex
daiVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID on which dynamic ARP inspection is configured.

daiVlanStatus.name: daiVlanStatus
daiVlanStatus.description: This object indicates whether dynamic ARP inspection is enabled in this VLAN.

daiVlanArpAclName.name: daiVlanArpAclName
daiVlanArpAclName.description: Specifies the ARP ACL name bound to the interface. The default value of daiVlanArpAclStatus is dynamic(2).

daiVlanArpAclStatus.name: daiVlanArpAclStatus
daiVlanArpAclStatus.description: Set to static(1) means packets not matching the ACL are dropped. Set to dynamic(2) means packets not matching the ACL are validated by the DHCP snooping binding table. When daiVlanArpAclName is configured, the default value of daiVlanArpAclStatus is dynamic(2).

daiPortTable.name: daiPortTable
daiPortTable.description: A table containing dynamic ARP inspection configurations for port interfaces.

daiPortEntry.name: daiPortEntry
daiPortEntry.description: An instance containing the configuration of dynamic ARP inspection at each port interface.

daiPortIfIndex.name: daiPortIfIndex
daiPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the port.

daiPortTrustStatus.name: daiPortTrustStatus
daiPortTrustStatus.description: This object indicates whether the port is trusted for dynamic ARP inspection.

daiPortRateLimit.name: daiPortRateLimit
daiPortRateLimit.description: The value of rate limit threshold per second of disposing ARP messages. Set the value 0xFFFFFFFF as no rate limit.

daiLogTable.name: daiLogTable
daiLogTable.description: A table containing dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogEntry.name: daiLogEntry
daiLogEntry.description: An instance containing log information of dynamic ARP inspection at each VLAN interface.

daiLogIndex.name: daiLogIndex
daiLogIndex.description: This object indicates the index of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogVlan.name: daiLogVlan
daiLogVlan.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogPort.name: daiLogPort
daiLogPort.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogSrcIpAddress.name: daiLogSrcIpAddress
daiLogSrcIpAddress.description: The source IP address of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogDestIpAddress.name: daiLogDestIpAddress
daiLogDestIpAddress.description: The destination IP address of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogSrcMacAddress.name: daiLogSrcMacAddress
daiLogSrcMacAddress.description: The source MAC address of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiLogDestMacAddress.name: daiLogDestMacAddress
daiLogDestMacAddress.description: The destination MAC address of dynamic ARP inspection log information.

daiTotalReceivedPkts.name: daiTotalReceivedPkts
daiTotalReceivedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets received before rate limiting.

daiTotalDroppedPkts.name: daiTotalDroppedPkts
daiTotalDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets dropped due to rate limt.

daiTotalProcessedPkts.name: daiTotalProcessedPkts
daiTotalProcessedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets processed by ARP inspection.

daiTotalSrcMacDroppedPkts.name: daiTotalSrcMacDroppedPkts
daiTotalSrcMacDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets dropped by source MAC address validation.

daiTotalDestMacDroppedPkts.name: daiTotalDestMacDroppedPkts
daiTotalDestMacDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets dropped by destination MAC address validation.

daiTotalIpAddrDroppedPkts.name: daiTotalIpAddrDroppedPkts
daiTotalIpAddrDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets dropped by IP address validation.

daiTotalArpAclDroppedPkts.name: daiTotalArpAclDroppedPkts
daiTotalArpAclDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets dropped by ARP ACL.

daiTotalDhcpSnoopingDroppedPkts.name: daiTotalDhcpSnoopingDroppedPkts
daiTotalDhcpSnoopingDroppedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of ARP packets dropped by DHCP snooping.

pppoeiaGlobalStatus.name: pppoeiaGlobalStatus
pppoeiaGlobalStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable global status of PPPoE Intermediate Agent. Set disbaled(2) to disable global status of PPPoE Intermediate Agent.

pppoeiaGlobalAccessNodeId.name: pppoeiaGlobalAccessNodeId
pppoeiaGlobalAccessNodeId.description: Specifies access node identifier. Use empty to revert to default value.

pppoeiaGlobalGenericErrorMsg.name: pppoeiaGlobalGenericErrorMsg
pppoeiaGlobalGenericErrorMsg.description: Specifies generic error message. Use empty to revert to default value.

pppoeiaGlobalClearStatisticsAction.name: pppoeiaGlobalClearStatisticsAction
pppoeiaGlobalClearStatisticsAction.description: This variable is used to clear the counters of all interfaces. Set clear(1) to perform the clear operation. The value noClear(2) will always be displayed when reading.

pppoeiaPortTable.name: pppoeiaPortTable
pppoeiaPortTable.description: Table for port configuration in PPPoE Intermediate Agent.

pppoeiaPortEntry.name: pppoeiaPortEntry
pppoeiaPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in PPPoE Intermediate Agent.

pppoeiaPortIndex.name: pppoeiaPortIndex
pppoeiaPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

pppoeiaPortStatus.name: pppoeiaPortStatus
pppoeiaPortStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces.

pppoeiaPortTrustStatus.name: pppoeiaPortTrustStatus
pppoeiaPortTrustStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable trust mode of PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces.

pppoeiaPortVendorTagStrip.name: pppoeiaPortVendorTagStrip
pppoeiaPortVendorTagStrip.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable stripping of vendor tag status of PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces.

pppoeiaPortCircuitId.name: pppoeiaPortCircuitId
pppoeiaPortCircuitId.description: Specifies circuit ID of PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces. Use empty to revert to default value.

pppoeiaPortOperCircuitId.name: pppoeiaPortOperCircuitId
pppoeiaPortOperCircuitId.description: The operational circuit ID of PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces.

pppoeiaPortRemoteId.name: pppoeiaPortRemoteId
pppoeiaPortRemoteId.description: Specifies remote ID of PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces. Use empty to revert to default value.

pppoeiaPortOperRemoteId.name: pppoeiaPortOperRemoteId
pppoeiaPortOperRemoteId.description: The operational remote ID of PPPoE Intermediate Agent on interfaces.

pppoeiaPortStatsTable.name: pppoeiaPortStatsTable
pppoeiaPortStatsTable.description: Table for port statistics in PPPoE Intermediate Agent.

pppoeiaPortStatsEntry.name: pppoeiaPortStatsEntry
pppoeiaPortStatsEntry.description: Entry for port statistics in PPPoE Intermediate Agent.

pppoeiaPortStatsIndex.name: pppoeiaPortStatsIndex
pppoeiaPortStatsIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPkts.description: Indicates the total number of received packets of the interface.

pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadiPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadiPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadiPkts.description: Indicates the total number of received PPPoE Active Discovery Initiation packets of the interface.

pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadoPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadoPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadoPkts.description: Indicates the total number of received PPPoE Active Discovery Offer packets of the interface.

pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadrPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadrPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of received PPPoE Active Discovery Request packets of the interface.

pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadsPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadsPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of received PPPoE Active Discovery Session-confirmation packets of the interface.

pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadtPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadtPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsRecvPadtPkts.description: Indicates the total number of received PPPoE Active Discovery Terminate packets of the interface.

pppoeiaPortStatsDropUntrustRespPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsDropUntrustRespPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsDropUntrustRespPkts.description: Indicates the total number of response packets dropped because they were untrusted.

pppoeiaPortStatsDropUntrustReqPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsDropUntrustReqPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsDropUntrustReqPkts.description: Indicates the total number of request packets dropped because they were untrusted.

pppoeiaPortStatsDropMalformedPkts.name: pppoeiaPortStatsDropMalformedPkts
pppoeiaPortStatsDropMalformedPkts.description: Indicates the total number of malformed packets dropped because they were untrusted.

pppoeiaPortStatsClearAction.name: pppoeiaPortStatsClearAction
pppoeiaPortStatsClearAction.description: This variable is used to clear the counters of specified interface. Set clear(1) to perform the clear operation. The value noClear(2) will always be displayed when reading.

erpsGlobalStatus.name: erpsGlobalStatus
erpsGlobalStatus.description: Configures the ERPS function for an entire switch. Note that the ERPS domain will not take effect unless it becomes active and the global status is enabled.

erpsGlobalClearStatisticsAction.name: erpsGlobalClearStatisticsAction
erpsGlobalClearStatisticsAction.description: This variable is used to clear the counters of all ERPS domains. Set to clear(1) to perform the clear operation. The value noClear(2) will always be displayed when reading.

erpsDomainIndex.name: erpsDomainIndex
erpsDomainIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the erpsDomainTable.

erpsDomainName.name: erpsDomainName
erpsDomainName.description: The domain name that uniquely identifies an entry in the erpsDomainTable.

erpsDomainMegLevel.name: erpsDomainMegLevel
erpsDomainMegLevel.description: Configures the maintenance entity group (MEG) level which is used to provide a communication channel for ring automatic protection switching (R-APS) information.

erpsDomainNodeId.name: erpsDomainNodeId
erpsDomainNodeId.description: Configures the node id whcih is a MAC address unique to the ring node.

erpsDomainWestRingPort.name: erpsDomainWestRingPort
erpsDomainWestRingPort.description: Each node on the ring connects to the ring through two ports. As part of the protection switching scheme, one port can be configured as the west port for the specified domain. The east port and west port can not be configured as the same port. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB. A value of 0 means no west ring port configured for this domain.

erpsDomainEastRingPort.name: erpsDomainEastRingPort
erpsDomainEastRingPort.description: Each node on the ring connects to the ring through two ports. As part of the protection switching scheme, one port can be configured as the east port for the specified domain. The east port and west port can not be configured as the same port. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB. A value of 0 means no east ring port configured for this domain.

erpsDomainRplPort.name: erpsDomainRplPort
erpsDomainRplPort.description: This value displays the port for ring protection link which under normal conditions, i.e., without any failure or request, is blocked for traffic channel, to prevent the formation of loops.

erpsDomainGuardTimer.name: erpsDomainGuardTimer
erpsDomainGuardTimer.description: Configures the value of the guard timer which is used to prevent ring nodes from receiving outdated R-APS messages. The range is in 10 ms steps between 10 ms and 2 seconds, with a default value of 500 ms.

erpsDomainHoldoffTimer.name: erpsDomainHoldoffTimer
erpsDomainHoldoffTimer.description: Configures the value of the holdoff timer which is used to prevent reporting error event immediately to protection switching if the provisioned holdoff timer value is non-zero. The range is in 100 ms steps between 0 and 10 seconds, with a default value of 0 ms.

erpsDomainWtrTimer.name: erpsDomainWtrTimer
erpsDomainWtrTimer.description: Configures the value of the wait-to-restore timer which is used by the RPL owner node to prevent frequent switching operations that may be caused by intermittent failures. The range is in 1 minute steps between 5 and 12 minutes with a default value of 5 minutes. This object will not take effect for the non RPL owner node.

erpsDomainControlVlanID.name: erpsDomainControlVlanID
erpsDomainControlVlanID.description: This is defined as dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. Configures one control VLAN for each ERPS domain. The control VLAN is used only to send and receive ERPS message. A control VLAN can not belong to more than one ERPS domain. A value of 0 means no control VLAN configured for this domain.

erpsDomainNodeState.name: erpsDomainNodeState
erpsDomainNodeState.description: This value displays the node's current state. It displays one of the following states (1) init -- The node is in the init state. (The node state will stay in init state if global status or domain status is not enabled.) (2) idle -- The node is in idle state (i.e., no detected failures, and receiving only 'NR, RB' R-APS frames). (3) protection -- The node is in protection state. (4) manualSwitch -- The node is in manual switch state. (5) forcedSwitch -- The node is in forced switch state. (6) pending -- The node is in pending state.

erpsDomainWestRingPortState.name: erpsDomainWestRingPortState
erpsDomainWestRingPortState.description: This value displays the west ring port's current state. It displays one of the following states (1) unknown -- The port's current state is unknown. (The port's current state will stay in unknown state if the node's current state is in init state.) (2) blocking -- The transmission and reception of traffic are blocked. (3) forwarding -- The traffic can be transmitted and received normally.

erpsDomainEastRingPortState.name: erpsDomainEastRingPortState
erpsDomainEastRingPortState.description: This value displays the east ring port's current state. It displays one of the following states (1) unknown -- The port's current state is unknown. (The port's current state will stay in unknown state if the node's current state is in init state.) (2) blocking -- The transmission and reception of traffic are blocked. (3) forwarding -- The traffic can be transmitted and received normally.

erpsDomainRowStatus.name: erpsDomainRowStatus
erpsDomainRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row entry. This object is used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. The status column has six defined values: - 'active', which indicates that the conceptual row is available for use by the managed device; - 'notInService', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is unavailable for use by the managed device (see NOTE below); - 'notReady', which indicates that the conceptual row exists in the agent, but is missing information necessary in order to be available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndGo', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device; - 'createAndWait', which is supplied by a management station wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row (but not make it available for use by the managed device); and, - 'destroy', which is supplied by a management station wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row. Whereas five of the six values (all except 'notReady') may be specified in a management protocol set operation, only three values will be returned in response to a management protocol retrieval operation: 'notReady', 'notInService' or 'active'. That is, when queried, an existing conceptual row has only three states: it is either available for use by the managed device (the status column has value 'active'); it is not available for use by the managed device, though the agent has sufficient information to make it so (the status column has value 'notInService'); or, it is not available for use by the managed device, and an attempt to make it so would fail because the agent has insufficient information (the state column has value 'notReady'). For a detailed description of this object, please refer to SNMPv2-TC MIB. Note that other objects can not be modified when the status is active.

erpsDomainMajorDomainIndex.name: erpsDomainMajorDomainIndex
erpsDomainMajorDomainIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the erpsDomainTable. A value of 0 means this domain has no major domain. Notes: This objest can not be configured if erpsDomainRingPortEast has a vaule other than 0.

erpsDomainPropagateTC.name: erpsDomainPropagateTC
erpsDomainPropagateTC.description: Set to enabled(1) to transmit topology change signal to the major domain. It will not take effect, if erpsDomainMajorDomainIndex has a value of 0.

erpsDomainWestMepId.name: erpsDomainWestMepId
erpsDomainWestMepId.description: Configures a CFM Down MEP on west ring port. A down MEP can be uniquely select by given a MEPID, domain's MEG level, and domain's control VLAN ID. A value of 0 means no west MEP is not configured for this domain.

erpsDomainEastMepId.name: erpsDomainEastMepId
erpsDomainEastMepId.description: Configures a CFM Down MEP on east ring port. A down MEP can be uniquely select by given a MEPID, domain's MEG level, and domain's control VLAN ID. A value of 0 means no east MEP is not configured for this domain.

erpsDomainNonErpsDevProtect.name: erpsDomainNonErpsDevProtect
erpsDomainNonErpsDevProtect.description: Set to enabled(1) to use non-standard protection mechanism for network containing non-ERPS devices.

erpsDomainNodeType.name: erpsDomainNodeType
erpsDomainNodeType.description: Set to none(1) to make this node act as a normal node. Set to owner(2) to make this node act as an RPL owner. Set to neighbor(3) to make this node act as an RPL neighbor.

erpsDomainNonRevertive.name: erpsDomainNonRevertive
erpsDomainNonRevertive.description: Set to enabled(1) to enable non-revertive mode operation.

erpsDomainRapsDefMac.name: erpsDomainRapsDefMac
erpsDomainRapsDefMac.description: Set to enabled(1) to use R-APS default MAC.

erpsDomainRapsWithoutVc.name: erpsDomainRapsWithoutVc
erpsDomainRapsWithoutVc.description: Set to enabled(1) to enable R-APS sub ring without virtual-channel for a sub domain.

erpsDomainVersion.name: erpsDomainVersion
erpsDomainVersion.description: Set to v2(2) to enable ERPS v2 operation.

erpsDomainForcedSwitch.name: erpsDomainForcedSwitch
erpsDomainForcedSwitch.description: Set to west(2) to perform the forced switch command on west ring port of specified domain. Set to east(3) to perform the forced switch command on east ring port of specified domain. The value none(1) will be displayed if no forced switch command is issued on local node.

erpsDomainManualSwitch.name: erpsDomainManualSwitch
erpsDomainManualSwitch.description: Set to west(2) to perform the manual switch command on west ring port of specified domain. Set to east(3) to perform the manual switch command on east ring port of specified domain. The value none(1) will be displayed if no manual switch command is issued on local node.

erpsDomainClear.name: erpsDomainClear
erpsDomainClear.description: Set to clear(1) to perform the clear command on specified domain. The value noClear(2) will always be displayed when reading.

erpsDomainStatsClearAction.name: erpsDomainStatsClearAction
erpsDomainStatsClearAction.description: This variable is used to clear the counters of specified domain. Set to clear(1) to perform the clear operation. The value noClear(2) will always be displayed when reading.

erpsDomainWtbTimer.name: erpsDomainWtbTimer
erpsDomainWtbTimer.description: Displays the value of the wait-to-block timer in ms which is used by the RPL owner node when recovering from an operator command (i.e. FS or MS). This object will not take effect for a non RPL owner node.

erpsDomainWtbExpire.name: erpsDomainWtbExpire
erpsDomainWtbExpire.description: Displays the time remaining in ms until the wait-to-block timer countdown expires. A value of 0 means no countdown is running.

erpsDomainWtrExpire.name: erpsDomainWtrExpire
erpsDomainWtrExpire.description: Displays the time remaining in seconds until the wait-to-restore timer countdown expires. A value of 0 means no countdown is running.

erpsDomainWestRingPortSf.name: erpsDomainWestRingPortSf
erpsDomainWestRingPortSf.description: This value displays the west ring port's current SF state. It displays one of the following states (1) none -- No SF is detected. (2) detected -- SF is detected.

erpsDomainEastRingPortSf.name: erpsDomainEastRingPortSf
erpsDomainEastRingPortSf.description: This value displays the east ring port's current SF state. It displays one of the following states (1) none -- No SF is detected. (2) detected -- SF is detected.

erpsDomainMultiRplOwnerWarn.name: erpsDomainMultiRplOwnerWarn
erpsDomainMultiRplOwnerWarn.description: This value displays the multiple PPL owner warning state. It displays one of the following states (1) none -- No multiple PPL owner warning is detected. (2) detected -- Multiple RPL owner warning is detected.

erpsPortStatsTable.name: erpsPortStatsTable
erpsPortStatsTable.description: Table for port statistics in ERPS.

erpsPortStatsEntry.name: erpsPortStatsEntry
erpsPortStatsEntry.description: Entry for port statistics in ERPS.

erpsPortStatsDomainIndex.name: erpsPortStatsDomainIndex
erpsPortStatsDomainIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the erpsDomainTable.

erpsPortStatsPortIndex.name: erpsPortStatsPortIndex
erpsPortStatsPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port in an ERPS domain. The value west(1) means the west ring port. The value east(2) means the east ring port.

erpsPortStatsLocalSfCount.name: erpsPortStatsLocalSfCount
erpsPortStatsLocalSfCount.description: Indicates the total number of local SF events that occurred on this ring port.

erpsPortStatsLocalClrSfCount.name: erpsPortStatsLocalClrSfCount
erpsPortStatsLocalClrSfCount.description: Indicates the total number of local Clear SF events that occurred on this ring port.

erpsPortStatsSentSfPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentSfPkts
erpsPortStatsSentSfPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS SF messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsSentNrPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentNrPkts
erpsPortStatsSentNrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS NR messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsSentNrRbPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentNrRbPkts
erpsPortStatsSentNrRbPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS NR-RB messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsSentFsPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentFsPkts
erpsPortStatsSentFsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS FS messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsSentMsPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentMsPkts
erpsPortStatsSentMsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS MS messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsSentEventPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentEventPkts
erpsPortStatsSentEventPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS EVENT messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsSentHealthPkts.name: erpsPortStatsSentHealthPkts
erpsPortStatsSentHealthPkts.description: Indicates the total number of non-standard health-check messages sent via this ring port (not including the forwarded ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvSfPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvSfPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvSfPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS SF messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvNrPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvNrPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvNrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS NR messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvNrRbPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvNrRbPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvNrRbPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS NR-RB messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvFsPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvFsPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvFsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS FS messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvMsPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvMsPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvMsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS MS messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvEventPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvEventPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvEventPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS EVENT messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsRecvHealthPkts.name: erpsPortStatsRecvHealthPkts
erpsPortStatsRecvHealthPkts.description: Indicates the total number of non-standard health-check messages received via this ring port (not including the ignored ones).

erpsPortStatsIgnoreSfPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreSfPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreSfPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS SF messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

erpsPortStatsIgnoreNrPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreNrPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreNrPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS NR messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

erpsPortStatsIgnoreNrRbPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreNrRbPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreNrRbPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS NR-RB messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

erpsPortStatsIgnoreFsPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreFsPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreFsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS FS messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

erpsPortStatsIgnoreMsPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreMsPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreMsPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS MS messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

erpsPortStatsIgnoreEventPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreEventPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreEventPkts.description: Indicates the total number of R-APS EVENT messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

erpsPortStatsIgnoreHealthPkts.name: erpsPortStatsIgnoreHealthPkts
erpsPortStatsIgnoreHealthPkts.description: Indicates the total number of non-standard health-check messages ignored by this ring port because they have been timed out or for other reasons.

ipv6RaGuardPortTable.name: ipv6RaGuardPortTable
ipv6RaGuardPortTable.description: Table for IPv6 RA Guard port configuration.

ipv6RaGuardPortEntry.name: ipv6RaGuardPortEntry
ipv6RaGuardPortEntry.description: Entry for IPv6 RA Guard port configuration.

ipv6RaGuardPortIndex.name: ipv6RaGuardPortIndex
ipv6RaGuardPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

ipv6RaGuardPortStatus.name: ipv6RaGuardPortStatus
ipv6RaGuardPortStatus.description: A value of enabled (1) indicates that IPv6 RA Guard feature is enabled on interfaces. A value of disabled (2) indicates that the feature is disabled.

lbdGlobalStatus.name: lbdGlobalStatus
lbdGlobalStatus.description: Set enabled(1) to enable global LBD status. Set disabled(2) to disable global LBD status.

lbdTransmitInterval.name: lbdTransmitInterval
lbdTransmitInterval.description: The transmission interval for LBD control frames.

lbdRecoverTime.name: lbdRecoverTime
lbdRecoverTime.description: The recover time used by LBD auto recovery mechanism. A value of 0 disables auto recovery.

lbdTrap.name: lbdTrap
lbdTrap.description: The kind of SNMP traps for LBD will be sent.

lbdPortTable.name: lbdPortTable
lbdPortTable.description: A table containing LBD configurations for all interfaces.

lbdPortEntry.name: lbdPortEntry
lbdPortEntry.description: An instance containing the configuration of LBD at each interface.

lbdPortIfIndex.name: lbdPortIfIndex
lbdPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the port.

lbdPortLoopedVlan.name: lbdPortLoopedVlan
lbdPortLoopedVlan.description: The list of VLANs on which loopback is detected. Only when oper state is looped and mode is VLAN-based, the value is nonzero.

udldGlobalMessageInterval.name: udldGlobalMessageInterval
udldGlobalMessageInterval.description: The message interval (in seconds) between UDLD probe messages on ports that are in advertisement phase and are determined to be bidirectional.

udldGlobalDetectionInterval.name: udldGlobalDetectionInterval
udldGlobalDetectionInterval.description: The detection interval (in seconds) used for UDLD detection process.

udldGlobalRecoveryInterval.name: udldGlobalRecoveryInterval
udldGlobalRecoveryInterval.description: The recovery interval (in seconds) used to recover interface shut down by UDLD automatically.

udldGlobalRecovery.name: udldGlobalRecovery
udldGlobalRecovery.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable auto recovery feature.

udldPortTable.name: udldPortTable
udldPortTable.description: Table for port configuration of UDLD.

udldPortEntry.name: udldPortEntry
udldPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration of UDLD.

udldPortIndex.name: udldPortIndex
udldPortIndex.description: The port (excluding trunk and trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

udldPortStatus.name: udldPortStatus
udldPortStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable UDLD on this interface.

udldPortAggressiveStatus.name: udldPortAggressiveStatus
udldPortAggressiveStatus.description: This parameter is used to enable/disable aggressive mode of UDLD on this interface.

udldPortOperState.name: udldPortOperState
udldPortOperState.description: The operational state of UDLD on this interface.

udldPortPortState.name: udldPortPortState
udldPortPortState.description: The port state of UDLD on this interface.

udldPortOperMessageInterval.name: udldPortOperMessageInterval
udldPortOperMessageInterval.description: The operational message interval (in seconds) used by UDLD on this interface.

udldPortOperTimeout.name: udldPortOperTimeout
udldPortOperTimeout.description: The operational timeout interval (in seconds) used by UDLD to decide the basic length of the detection phase on this interface.

udldPortNeighborDevCount.name: udldPortNeighborDevCount
udldPortNeighborDevCount.description: The total number of neighbor devices discovered on this interface.

udldPortNeighborDevTable.name: udldPortNeighborDevTable
udldPortNeighborDevTable.description: Table of neighbor devices discovered by UDLD for each interface.

udldPortNeighborDevEntry.name: udldPortNeighborDevEntry
udldPortNeighborDevEntry.description: A conceptual row containing the information of a neighbor device.

udldPortNeighborDevPortIndex.name: udldPortNeighborDevPortIndex
udldPortNeighborDevPortIndex.description: The port (excluding trunk and trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

udldPortNeighborDevIndex.name: udldPortNeighborDevIndex
udldPortNeighborDevIndex.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the nieghbor device discovered by UDLD on a port interface.

udldPortNeighborDevDevID.name: udldPortNeighborDevDevID
udldPortNeighborDevDevID.description: The device ID of this neighbor device.

udldPortNeighborDevPortID.name: udldPortNeighborDevPortID
udldPortNeighborDevPortID.description: The port ID of this neighbor device.

udldPortNeighborDevDevName.name: udldPortNeighborDevDevName
udldPortNeighborDevDevName.description: The device name of this neighbor device.

udldPortNeighborDevNeighborState.name: udldPortNeighborDevNeighborState
udldPortNeighborDevNeighborState.description: The neighbor state of this neighbor device.

udldPortNeighborDevExpire.name: udldPortNeighborDevExpire
udldPortNeighborDevExpire.description: The amount of time remaining (in seconds) before this entry should expire. Whenever this period expires, this entry will be removed.

udldPortNeighborDevMessageInterval.name: udldPortNeighborDevMessageInterval
udldPortNeighborDevMessageInterval.description: The message interval (in seconds) of this neighbor device.

udldPortNeighborDevTimeout.name: udldPortNeighborDevTimeout
udldPortNeighborDevTimeout.description: The timeout interval (in seconds) of this neighbor device.

mldSnoopStatus.name: mldSnoopStatus
mldSnoopStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable MLD snooping on the device. When enabled, the device will examine MLD packets and set up filters for MLD ports.

mldSnoopQuerier.name: mldSnoopQuerier
mldSnoopQuerier.description: Enables (disables) whether the switch acts as an MLD querier.

mldSnoopRobustness.name: mldSnoopRobustness
mldSnoopRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. MLD is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses. The discussion of the Robustness Variable is in Section 7.1 of RFC 2710.

mldSnoopQueryInterval.name: mldSnoopQueryInterval
mldSnoopQueryInterval.description: The interval (in seconds) between MLD host-query messages sent by the switch.

mldSnoopQueryMaxResponseTime.name: mldSnoopQueryMaxResponseTime
mldSnoopQueryMaxResponseTime.description: The time after a query, during which a response is expected from an endstation. If a querier has sent a number of queries defined by mldSnoopRobustness, but an endstation has not responded, a countdown timer is started using an initial value set by mldSnoopQueryMaxResponseTime. If the countdown finishes, and the endstation still has not responded, then that the endstation is deemed to have left the multicast group.

mldSnoopRouterPortExpireTime.name: mldSnoopRouterPortExpireTime
mldSnoopRouterPortExpireTime.description: Sets the time (in seconds) the switch waits after the previous querier has stopped querying before the router port (which received query packets from previous querier) expires.

mldSnoopUnknownMcastMode.name: mldSnoopUnknownMcastMode
mldSnoopUnknownMcastMode.description: Sets the mldSnoopUnknownMcastMode to define the flooding behavior when receive the unknown multicast traffic.

mldSnoopRouterCurrentVlanIndex.name: mldSnoopRouterCurrentVlanIndex
mldSnoopRouterCurrentVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to mldSnoopRouterStaticTable.

mldSnoopRouterCurrentPorts.name: mldSnoopRouterCurrentPorts
mldSnoopRouterCurrentPorts.description: The set of ports which are current router ports, including static router ports. Please refer to mldSnoopRouterStaticTable.

mldSnoopRouterStaticVlanIndex.name: mldSnoopRouterStaticVlanIndex
mldSnoopRouterStaticVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to mldSnoopRouterStaticTable.

mldSnoopRouterStaticPorts.name: mldSnoopRouterStaticPorts
mldSnoopRouterStaticPorts.description: The set of ports which are static router ports.

mldSnoopMulticastCurrentVlanIndex.name: mldSnoopMulticastCurrentVlanIndex
mldSnoopMulticastCurrentVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to mldSnoopMulticastStaticTable.

mldSnoopMulticastCurrentPorts.name: mldSnoopMulticastCurrentPorts
mldSnoopMulticastCurrentPorts.description: The set of ports which are members of a multicast group, including static members. Please refer to mldSnoopMulticastStaticTable.

mldSnoopMulticastStaticVlanIndex.name: mldSnoopMulticastStaticVlanIndex
mldSnoopMulticastStaticVlanIndex.description: The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. The entry will only appear here after a configure to mldSnoopMulticastStaticTable.

mldSnoopMulticastStaticPorts.name: mldSnoopMulticastStaticPorts
mldSnoopMulticastStaticPorts.description: The set of ports which are members.

mldSnoopCurrentVlanTable.name: mldSnoopCurrentVlanTable
mldSnoopCurrentVlanTable.description: Table for configuring MLD snooping for each VLAN which exists in the device by (local or network) management, or dynamically created as a result of GVRP requests received.

mldSnoopCurrentVlanIndex.name: mldSnoopCurrentVlanIndex
mldSnoopCurrentVlanIndex.description: Same is dot1qVlanIndex in the Q-BRIDGE-MIB. This table has only one entry - the entry for the VLAN of the management interface.

mldSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeave.name: mldSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeave
mldSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeave.description: The parameter to enable or disable the Immediate-Leave feature on this VLAN.

mldSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeaveByHostI.name: mldSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeaveByHostIp
mldSnoopCurrentVlanImmediateLeaveByHostI.description: The parameter to enable or disable the Immediate-Leave by-host-ip feature on this VLAN.

mldSnoopProxyReporting.name: mldSnoopProxyReporting
mldSnoopProxyReporting.description: Parameter to enable or disable MLD snooping proxy reporting on the device.

mldSnoopUnsolicitedReportInterval.name: mldSnoopUnsolicitedReportInterval
mldSnoopUnsolicitedReportInterval.description: Setting this value to specify how long (in seconds) the uplink ports should transmit unsolicited reports.

mldSnoopPortTable.name: mldSnoopPortTable
mldSnoopPortTable.description: Table of MLD Snooping service per port.

mldSnoopPortEntry.name: mldSnoopPortEntry
mldSnoopPortEntry.description: Entry of MLD Snooping service per port.

mldSnoopPortIndex.name: mldSnoopPortIndex
mldSnoopPortIndex.description: The port and the trunk (excluding trunk members) interface of the mldsnpPortTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mldSnoopQueryDrop.name: mldSnoopQueryDrop
mldSnoopQueryDrop.description: Parameter to enable or disable dropping MLD Query packet.

mldSnoopMulticastDataDrop.name: mldSnoopMulticastDataDrop
mldSnoopMulticastDataDrop.description: Parameter to enable or disable dropping IPv6 multicast data

mldSnoopFilterStatus.name: mldSnoopFilterStatus
mldSnoopFilterStatus.description: Parameter to enable or disable MLD filtering on the device.

mldSnoopProfileTable.name: mldSnoopProfileTable
mldSnoopProfileTable.description: The table for configuring the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopProfileEntry.name: mldSnoopProfileEntry
mldSnoopProfileEntry.description: The entry for configuring the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopProfileId.name: mldSnoopProfileId
mldSnoopProfileId.description: The ID of the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopProfileAction.name: mldSnoopProfileAction
mldSnoopProfileAction.description: The access mode of the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopProfileStatus.name: mldSnoopProfileStatus
mldSnoopProfileStatus.description: Setting this to valid(1) creates an entry. Setting this to invalid(2) destroys an entry.

mldSnoopProfileCtlId.name: mldSnoopProfileCtlId
mldSnoopProfileCtlId.description: The ID of the MLD snooping profile. The default value is zero, meaning that no ID is specified. In order to create a profile, a non-zero value must be specified.

mldSnoopProfileCtlInetAddressType.name: mldSnoopProfileCtlInetAddressType
mldSnoopProfileCtlInetAddressType.description: The address type is associated with this agent. Only ipv4(1) type is supported.

mldSnoopProfileCtlStartInetAddress.name: mldSnoopProfileCtlStartInetAddress
mldSnoopProfileCtlStartInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the start of the controlled IP multicast addresses.

mldSnoopProfileCtlEndInetAddress.name: mldSnoopProfileCtlEndInetAddress
mldSnoopProfileCtlEndInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the end of the controlled IP multicast addresses.

mldSnoopProfileCtlAction.name: mldSnoopProfileCtlAction
mldSnoopProfileCtlAction.description: Setting it to create(2) creates the range of the controlled IP multicast addresses. Setting it to destroy(3) destroys the range of the controlled IP multicast addresses. When the action is completed, this object becomes noAction(1).

mldSnoopProfileRangeTable.name: mldSnoopProfileRangeTable
mldSnoopProfileRangeTable.description: The table for configuring the range of the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopProfileRangeEntry.name: mldSnoopProfileRangeEntry
mldSnoopProfileRangeEntry.description: The entry for configuring the range of the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopProfileRangeInetAddressType.name: mldSnoopProfileRangeInetAddressType
mldSnoopProfileRangeInetAddressType.description: The address type is associated with this agent. Only ipv6(2) type is supported.

mldSnoopProfileRangeStartInetAddress.name: mldSnoopProfileRangeStartInetAddress
mldSnoopProfileRangeStartInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the start of the controlled IPv6 multicast addresses.

mldSnoopProfileRangeEndInetAddress.name: mldSnoopProfileRangeEndInetAddress
mldSnoopProfileRangeEndInetAddress.description: The specified addresses in the end of the controlled IPv6 multicast addresses.

mldSnoopProfileRangeAction.name: mldSnoopProfileRangeAction
mldSnoopProfileRangeAction.description: The access mode of the MLD snooping profile.

mldSnoopFilterPortTable.name: mldSnoopFilterPortTable
mldSnoopFilterPortTable.description: Table for port configuration in MLD filtering.

mldSnoopFilterPortEntry.name: mldSnoopFilterPortEntry
mldSnoopFilterPortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in MLD filtering.

mldSnoopFilterPortIndex.name: mldSnoopFilterPortIndex
mldSnoopFilterPortIndex.description: The port and trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mldSnoopFilterPortProfileId.name: mldSnoopFilterPortProfileId
mldSnoopFilterPortProfileId.description: The mldSnoopProfileEntry identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of the mldSnoopProfileId object. If there is no corresponding entry in the mldSnoopProfileTable, then no association exists. In particular, if this value is zero, no associated profile will be generated, as zero is not a valid profile index.

mldSnoopThrottlePortTable.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortTable
mldSnoopThrottlePortTable.description: Table for port configuration in MLD throttling.

mldSnoopThrottlePortEntry.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortEntry
mldSnoopThrottlePortEntry.description: Entry for port configuration in MLD throttling.

mldSnoopThrottlePortIndex.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortIndex
mldSnoopThrottlePortIndex.description: The port and trunk (including trunk members) interface of the portTable. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface identified by the same value of ifIndex in the IF-MIB.

mldSnoopThrottlePortRunningStatus.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortRunningStatus
mldSnoopThrottlePortRunningStatus.description: Describes the running status of the MLD throttling to the switch. A value of true(1) indicates the MLD throttling mechanism is active. A value of false(2) indicates the MLD throttling mechanism is inactive.

mldSnoopThrottlePortAction.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortAction
mldSnoopThrottlePortAction.description: The action mode of the MLD throttling. A value of replace(1) means to replace a joined multicast group randomly when an interface receives an MLD report and the number of current joined multicast groups is equal to the maximum number of MLD groups that the interface can join. A value of deny(2) means to deny the MLD report request when an interface receives an MLD report and the number of current joined multicast groups is equal to the maximum number of MLD groups that the interface can join.

mldSnoopThrottlePortMaxGroups.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortMaxGroups
mldSnoopThrottlePortMaxGroups.description: The maximum number of MLD groups that the interface can join.

mldSnoopThrottlePortCurrentGroups.name: mldSnoopThrottlePortCurrentGroups
mldSnoopThrottlePortCurrentGroups.description: The current number of MLD groups that the interface has joined.

mldSnoopClearDynamicGroups.name: mldSnoopClearDynamicGroups
mldSnoopClearDynamicGroups.description: The current number of MLD groups that the interface has joined.

mldSnoopVlanTable.name: mldSnoopVlanTable
mldSnoopVlanTable.description: Table of MLD Snooping service per port.

mldSnoopVlanEntry.name: mldSnoopVlanEntry
mldSnoopVlanEntry.description: Entry of MLD Snooping service per VLAN.

dhcpv6SnoopEnable.name: dhcpv6SnoopEnable
dhcpv6SnoopEnable.description: This object indicates whether the DHCPv6 Snooping feature is enabled.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingTableClearAction.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingTableClearAction
dhcpv6SnoopBindingTableClearAction.description: Action for clearing dhcpv6SnoopBindingTable. When this object is set to clear(2), all dynamic entries in dhcpv6SnoopBindingTable will be cleared. When this object is read, the value of this object is always noClear(1).

dhcpv6SnoopStatisticsClearAction.name: dhcpv6SnoopStatisticsClearAction
dhcpv6SnoopStatisticsClearAction.description: Action for clearing dhcpSnoopStatistics. When this object is set to clear(2), statistics in dhcpSnoopStatistics will be cleared. When this object is read, the value of this object is always noClear(1).

dhcpv6SnoopVlanConfigTable.name: dhcpv6SnoopVlanConfigTable
dhcpv6SnoopVlanConfigTable.description: A table contains DHCPv6 Snooping configurations of existing VLANs.

dhcpv6SnoopVlanConfigEntry.name: dhcpv6SnoopVlanConfigEntry
dhcpv6SnoopVlanConfigEntry.description: An instance contains the configuration to enable or disable DHCPv6 Snooping at each existing VLAN.

dhcpv6SnoopVlanIndex.name: dhcpv6SnoopVlanIndex
dhcpv6SnoopVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID on which DHCPv6 Snooping feature is configured.

dhcpv6SnoopVlanEnable.name: dhcpv6SnoopVlanEnable
dhcpv6SnoopVlanEnable.description: This object indicates whether DHCPv6 Snooping is enabled in this VLAN.

dhcpv6SnoopPortConfigTable.name: dhcpv6SnoopPortConfigTable
dhcpv6SnoopPortConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state of each port or trunk for DHCPv6 Snooping purpose.

dhcpv6SnoopPortConfigEntry.name: dhcpv6SnoopPortConfigEntry
dhcpv6SnoopPortConfigEntry.description: An instance contains the configuration to enable or disable trust state of each port or trunk for DHCPv6 Snooping purpose.

dhcpv6SnoopPortIfIndex.name: dhcpv6SnoopPortIfIndex
dhcpv6SnoopPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the port or trunk.

dhcpv6SnoopPortTrustEnable.name: dhcpv6SnoopPortTrustEnable
dhcpv6SnoopPortTrustEnable.description: This object indicates whether the port or trunk is trusted for DHCP Snooping purpose.

dhcpv6SnoopPortMaxBinding.name: dhcpv6SnoopPortMaxBinding
dhcpv6SnoopPortMaxBinding.description: The maximum number of binding entries of the port or trunk

dhcpv6SnoopPortCurrentBinding.name: dhcpv6SnoopPortCurrentBinding
dhcpv6SnoopPortCurrentBinding.description: The number of dynamic binding entrires learned on the port or trunk.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingTable.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingTable
dhcpv6SnoopBindingTable.description: A table contains the DHCPv6 binding entries information learned by the device.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingEntry.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingEntry
dhcpv6SnoopBindingEntry.description: An instance contains the link-layer address, ia type, ia id, IPv6 address, VLAN number, interface number, lifetime.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingLinkLayerAddress.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingLinkLayerAddress
dhcpv6SnoopBindingLinkLayerAddress.description: This object indicates the link-layer address of a DHCPv6 client host.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingIaType.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingIaType
dhcpv6SnoopBindingIaType.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address ia type of a DHCPv6 client host. na - Non-temporary address, ta - temporary address

dhcpv6SnoopBindingIaId.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingIaId
dhcpv6SnoopBindingIaId.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address ia id of a DHCPv6 client host.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingIpv6Address.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingIpv6Address
dhcpv6SnoopBindingIpv6Address.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of a DHCPv6 client host.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingVlanIndex.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingVlanIndex
dhcpv6SnoopBindingVlanIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN which a DHCPv6 client host belongs to.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingPortIfIndex.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingPortIfIndex
dhcpv6SnoopBindingPortIfIndex.description: This object indicates the port or trunk where a DHCPv6 client host connects to.

dhcpv6SnoopBindingLifeTime.name: dhcpv6SnoopBindingLifeTime
dhcpv6SnoopBindingLifeTime.description: This object indicates the life time of this DHCPv6 binding.

dhcpSnoopRecvClientPkts.name: dhcpSnoopRecvClientPkts
dhcpSnoopRecvClientPkts.description: Indicates the received number of client packets

dhcpSnoopSentClientPkts.name: dhcpSnoopSentClientPkts
dhcpSnoopSentClientPkts.description: Indicates the sent number of client packets

dhcpSnoopDroppedClientPkts.name: dhcpSnoopDroppedClientPkts
dhcpSnoopDroppedClientPkts.description: Indicates the dropped number of client packets

dhcpSnoopRecvServerPkts.name: dhcpSnoopRecvServerPkts
dhcpSnoopRecvServerPkts.description: Indicates the received number of server packets

dhcpSnoopSentServerPkts.name: dhcpSnoopSentServerPkts
dhcpSnoopSentServerPkts.description: Indicates the sent number of server packets

dhcpSnoopDroppedServerPkts.name: dhcpSnoopDroppedServerPkts
dhcpSnoopDroppedServerPkts.description: Indicates the dropped number of server packets

dhcpSnoopRecvRelayPkts.name: dhcpSnoopRecvRelayPkts
dhcpSnoopRecvRelayPkts.description: Indicates the received number of relay packets

dhcpSnoopSentRelayPkts.name: dhcpSnoopSentRelayPkts
dhcpSnoopSentRelayPkts.description: Indicates the sent number of relay packets

dhcpSnoopDroppedRelayPkts.name: dhcpSnoopDroppedRelayPkts
dhcpSnoopDroppedRelayPkts.description: Indicates the dropped number of relay packets

snmpAuthenInfoTrapStatus.name: snmpAuthenInfoTrapStatus
snmpAuthenInfoTrapStatus.description: Whether the SNMP authentication information trap is enabled(1) or disabled(2).

swPowerStatusChangeTrap.name: swPowerStatusChangeTrap
swPowerStatusChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent when the power state changes.

swPortSecurityTrap.name: swPortSecurityTrap
swPortSecurityTrap.description: This trap is sent when the port is being intruded. This trap will only be sent when the portSecActionTrap is enabled.

swIpFilterRejectTrap.name: swIpFilterRejectTrap
swIpFilterRejectTrap.description: This trap is sent when an incorrect IP address is rejected by the ipfilter.

swAtcBcastStormAlarmFireTrap.name: swAtcBcastStormAlarmFireTrap
swAtcBcastStormAlarmFireTrap.description: When the broadcast traffic is detected as the storm, this trap will be fired.

swAtcBcastStormAlarmClearTrap.name: swAtcBcastStormAlarmClearTrap
swAtcBcastStormAlarmClearTrap.description: When the broadcast storm is detected as the normal traffic, this trap will be fired.

swAtcBcastStormTcApplyTrap.name: swAtcBcastStormTcApplyTrap
swAtcBcastStormTcApplyTrap.description: When the ATC is activated, this trap will be fired.
